title: cheese ball
directions: Combine the Kraft, the Philly and the Hidden Valley.
Mix well and shape into a ball.
Roll in the nuts.
Chill at least an hour before serving.

title: french creme frosting
directions: Mix first 2 ingredients over medium heat until thickened; set aside.
Beat butter, Crisco, salt and sugar until fluffy.
Add first 2 ingredients and vanilla.
Beat until peaks form. Refrigerate 20 minutes before using.

title: greeting card cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add egg.
Beat until light and fluffy. Stir flour with spices and soda.
Add to creamy mixture.
Mix well.
Cover; chill until firm, about 2 hours.

title: cabbage goulash
directions: Brown hamburger and sausage; drain. Saute chopped bell pepper and onions. Combine hamburger, sausage, pepper and onions. Add water, crushed red pepper and garlic. Bring to boil. Add shredded cabbage. Cook until cabbage is tender. Serve with hush puppies or corn bread. Prep time: 25 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Remove bones.
Chop chicken into small pieces.
Saute onion and cook spaghetti as usual.
In a large casserole dish, combine chicken, mushrooms, onion, soups, chicken broth and cooked spaghetti, mixing thoroughly.
Arrange slices of Mozzarella cheese on top and bake in 350° oven about 20 minutes.

title: easy pound cake
directions: Coat Bundt pan with cooking oil and brown sugar and cinnamon mix.
Mix cake and applesauce until batter is smooth.
Pour into Bundt pan and bake as directed on box.

title: beau monde dip
directions: Make 24 hours ahead.
Blend all ingredients but the bread. Refrigerate overnight.
Before serving, cut slice from top of bread and tear out center int bite sized pieces. Fill centers with dip.
Place in center of tray and surround with the center pieces. To eat, dip bread pieces into dip.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: In bowl, combine all ingredients except chicken; add chicken and toss to coat.
Cover bowl and refrigerate for at least 8 hours, occasionally tossing chicken in marinade.
Remove chicken from marinade; remove and discard garlic and ginger.
In blender container pureed marinade.
Arrange chicken parts in disposable aluminum roasting pan; grill over hot coals until tender, basting occasionally with pureed marinade.
Transfer chicken and pan juices to serving platter.
In small saucepan bring remaining marinade to a boil; serve with chicken.
May also substitute turkey for chicken.

title: cheese dogs in a blanket
directions: Slit dogs down the middle.
Place 1/2 cheese strip in each dog.
Wrap dog with crescent roll dough.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.
Spray baking sheet with Pam before placing dogs in dough on it.

title: chicken and pepper jelly
directions: Mix
juice
and
jelly; baste chicken while grilling or broiling.
Boil remaining marinade and serve with chicken.

title: wet chocolate cake
directions: Mix flour and sugar; set aside.
Bring to a boil the butter, cocoa, oil and water.
Add to flour and sugar mixture.
Then add buttermilk, baking soda, vanilla and eggs.
Pour in square pan and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: seafoam salad
directions: Mash cream cheese with cream.
Heat 1 cup pear juice to boiling and pour over gelatin.
Stir until dissolved.
While hot, add to cheese mixture.
When cool and thick, add pears mashed with fork. Fold in whipped cream.

title: karo pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and butter (or margarine).
Add eggs and pecans.
Pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 40 to 45 minutes, or until knife inserted in the center of pie comes out clean.

title: mexican wedding cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well, in the order listed, and roll into balls in the palm of your hand, about a half-teaspoonful.
Flatten cookies with spatula that has been dipped in flour.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Mix sour cream and mushroom soup together and place in casserole dish or roaster.
Add dried beef, cut up finely.
Add dash of pepper and sliced mushrooms; place chicken breasts on top. Bake at 350° for about 2 1/2 hours.
Serve over rice.

title: ham and cheese party rolls
directions: Saute onion in butter until tender.
Add mustard, Worcestershire sauce and poppy seed.
Spread mixture on top and bottom of party rolls, after split in half.
Layer ham and Swiss cheese.
Cover with foil.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: lemon meringue cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package except add lemon peel before beating.
Bake in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan as directed.
Cool. Prepare Lemon Filling; reserve 1/3 cup.
Spread remaining filling over cake.
Prepare frosting mix as directed on package, except add nutmeg before beating.
Frost cake.
Swirl reserved filling on frosting or make lattice design.
Thin reserved filling with small amount of water if necessary.

title: bean casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Mix together with other ingredients.
Top with bacon.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: tuna stroganoff
directions: Combine tuna, soup and mushrooms in casserole dish.
Cook on Full power for 6 to 8 minutes or until mixture is heated through and bubbling.
Stir twice during cooking time.
Stir in sour cream.
Garnish with parsley and serve over noodles or rice as desired.

title: avocado salad
directions: String celery and chop in small pieces. Peel avocados. Quarter, then cut quarters in half. Use only blade part of green onions. Chop fine. Peel tomatoes and cut in small pieces. Chop garlic extra fine. Chop eggs small. Mix all ingredients in large bowl. Pour Italian dressing in. Mix. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla.
Sift flour with dry ingredients.
Combine bananas with milk; add alternately with sifted dry ingredients.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: ice cream dessert
directions: Melt oleo in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add the rest of ingredients. Bake at 300° for 30 minutes, stirring every 10 minutes.
Cool; leave half in pan and fill with softened ice cream.
Place rest of mix on top.
Freeze.

title: shrimp etouffee
directions: Saute onions and bell peppers in melted butter.
Add flour and cook 5 minutes.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes and cook approximately 10 minutes.
Add shrimp.
Cook until shrimp turn pink.
Add chicken broth to desired thickness.
Cook on low heat for 10 more minutes. Serve over rice.

title: lovefeast coffee
directions: Drop the bag of coffee into the boiling water. Reduce heat and let stand without boiling about 15 minutes, stirring bag through the water with a wooden spoon now and then.
Remove the coffee bag when the liquid is strong enough.
Stir in sugar until dissolved. Add milk and keep hot until ready to serve.
Makes 3 1/2 gallons.

title: baked apple rolls
directions: Mix Jiffy pie crust according to directions and separate into two balls of dough.
Roll out dough and place half the apples on one edge of each piece of dough.
Roll into logs.
Place log rolls into a baking dish or a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Cut through the rolls, making 2-inch sections.
Place them randomly in pan. (Don't worry about keeping it neat!)

title: vegetables with pasta
directions: Cook linguini per package directions.
Cut squash and zucchini into 1/4-inch thick slices; then cut slices into thin strips (leave peel on).
Cut red pepper into thin strips.
Stir-fry vegetables in olive oil with garlic for 2 to 3 minutes.
Mix with cooked linguini, wine, salt, basil, tarragon and red pepper.
Top with grated Parmesan cheese and serve.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat the eggs.
Add sugar, pecans, vanilla and salt; mix together.
Put in unbaked pie shell and bake at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: zucchini ratatouille
directions: Brown beef and put in another dish.
Saute onion, garlic and green pepper until tender, in same pan beef was browned in.
Add tomato sauce and seasonings; bring to a boil.
Add mushrooms and zucchini.
Cover and simmer over medium heat until zucchini is tender.
Add water, if necessary.
Add meat.
Pour into 2-quart casserole dish and sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: salsa
directions: Drain one large can tomatoes.
Place tomatoes in blender or food processor and add the ingredients.
Chop in blender and serve with chips.
(Add more pepper and salt to your taste.
If you use frozen onions and pepper, the salsa will be almost frozen-delicious!
For chunkier salsa, add bell pepper after removing from blender.)

title: sweet and sour kielbasa
directions: Cook sausage over low heat in a large skillet 8 to 10 minutes; drain.
Set aside.

title: baked chilies, rice and cheese casserole
directions: Combine rice and sour cream.
Spread 1/2 in buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle grated cheese and green chilies and repeat.
Bake at 350° until hot through, about 20 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: saucepan brownies
directions: Blend the granulated sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Stir in cherries; cook over medium-low heat, stirring frequently until thick and clear.
Reduce heat; cook 2 minutes more.
Stir in rum extract; chill thoroughly.

title: pina colada dip
directions: Mix all ingredients until blended well.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serve with fresh fruit.

title: pineapple curry hors d'oeuvres
directions: Scoop out center of pineapple; use this pineapple for other use.
Combine crushed pineapple, cream cheese, curry powder and toasted coconut.
Stuff in pineapple shell.
Serve with crackers such as Wheat Thins or Sociables.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Place in greased and floured loaf pan and bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta; drain and cool.
Add cucumbers and onion.
Toss with Italian dressing and Salad Supreme seasoning to taste.
Add tomato, green peppers and ripe olives.
Toss gently and chill.

title: mrs. blake's date nut loaf
directions: Divide flour in half.
Cream sugar, Wesson oil and egg yolks until fluffy.
Mix nuts and dates with 1/2 cup flour.
Add 1 teaspoon baking powder to other 1/2 cup flour.
Add salt with creamed egg yolks.
Add vanilla, flour, nuts and dates.
Mix well. Add beaten egg whites.
Mixture will be very stiff.
Place in greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 300° for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: pronto pups
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add milk.
Mix well.
Dip each hot dog in batter, coat well and fry in oil until golden brown.
Turn to brown evenly.

title: old fashioned apple pie
directions: Prepare apples in large bowl. Combine Splenda (or sugar), cornstarch, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt in a bowl. Sprinkle this mixture over apples and toss. Spoon apple mixture into crust. Place second crust over filling. Seal edges, trim and flute. Makes 4 slits in top crust. Bake in a 425° preheated oven until top is golden brown, about 40 to 50 minutes.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all together in a large container.
Use 2 to 3 heaping spoons for 1 cup.

title: rich cocoa fudge
directions: Butter 8 or 9-inch square pan; set aside.
In heavy 4-quart saucepan, combine sugar, cocoa and salt.
Stir in milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture comes to full rolling boil.
Boil without stirring to 234° on candy thermometer (soft ball stage).
Remove from heat.
Add butter, vanilla and nuts.
Do not stir.
Cool at room temperature to 110°.
Beat until fudge thickens and loses some of its gloss.
Quickly spread into prepared pan.
Cut into squares.
Makes about 3 dozen candies.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Mix cake mix, pudding, 4 eggs, oil and 7-Up; cook like cake batter.
Makes 4 layers.
Mix remaining ingredients; cook until sugar melts.
Spread between layers and on top of cake.

title: delores' zucchini bars
directions: Cream sugars with butter and beat until fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well after each addition. Fold in vanilla. Blend in flour, salt and baking powder.
Fold in coconut, raisins, nuts and zucchini.
Pour batter into a lightly greased 10 x 15-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until cake tests done. Cool and frost with the following.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Combine flour and sugar.
Add to 1 can pineapple tidbits (do not drain juice).
Fold in grated cheese.
Spread in casserole dish.
Cover with Ritz crackers; place butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: washboards
directions: Stir soda mixture in first 4 ingredients.
Sift together and add the flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix in chocolate chips, nuts and coconut.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 400°.
Makes about 10 dozen cookies.

title: salmon soup
directions: Clean and flake salmon.
Cook with diced onion and butter or oleo until onion is soft.
Add milk; add salt and pepper.
Heat until milk is hot.
Do not boil because milk will curdle.
Serve with crackers.

title: chicken elegante
directions: Combine stuffing mix, water and 2 tablespoons margarine.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Mix gravy, mushrooms and wine. Set aside. Lightly brown chicken in 2 tablespoons margarine.
Place in baking dish. Top each piece with stuffing, broccoli and gravy mixture. Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Bring cream cheese to room temperature.
Beat first 3 ingredients together.
Fold in the whipped topping.
Pour into a baked crust or a graham cracker crust.
Refrigerate.
Freezes well.

title: sauteed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms. Trim ends of stems.
Melt butter in large skillet.
Add mushrooms; sprinkle with marjoram and salt.
Saute mushrooms, turning frequently, 15 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Bake pie shells.
Fry bacon until crisp.
Saute onions in butter.
Layer bacon, onions, mushrooms, ham and cheese in the two pie shells.
Mix the remaining ingredients.
Pour mixture in shells and bake for 35 minutes in 350° oven or until knife comes out clean when inserted in center.

title: easy sweet and sour chicken
directions: Mix ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve with rice.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Roll out crescent rolls and then place on a large pizza pan that has been sprayed with Pam.
Bake in 350° oven for 8 to 9 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Combine sugar, flour, cinnamon, salt and lemon juice.
Mix with peaches.
Place in deep nine-inch pie pan and dot with butter.
Roll out crust.
Fold in half, then fourths.
Slash pastry 2 or
3 times on each fold.
Place over peach mixture. Trim edges and crimp.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 425°.

title: ann's scones
directions: Cut butter into first five ingredients until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Mix in raisins.
Add milk and egg and stir until dough follows fork around bowl. Knead lightly.

title: peach and cream cheesecake
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and beat.
Spread in a greased 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Top with drained peaches; reserve juice.

title: max's sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream together the butter, margarine and sugar.
Beat in the eggs. Add the flour, salt and soda; mix well, then add the sour cream.
Mix well. Add another 1 1/2 cups flour; mix well. Add vanilla and mix well.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan and bake 1 1/4 hours at 350° or until pick inserted in cake comes out clean.

title: bagels
directions: Combine flour, powdered milk and salt. Mix butter, sugar, yeast with lukewarm water. Add the well beaten egg white and flour mixture; knead; let rise. Roll in small pieces the width of a finger and twice the length, tapering at the ends. Shape into rings. Pinch ends together; let stand on floured board only until they begin to rise. Fill a large, shallow pan half full of water. When very hot, but not boiling, drop rings in carefully, one at a time. Let cook under the boiling point on one side, then turn, and let other side cook at a simmer. They must be light, keep their shape and not break apart when handled. Place in hot oven (400 degrees) on baking sheet. If desired, sprinkle with salt, caraway seed, poppy seed, etc. and bake at 400 degrees for 25 minutes or until crisp and golden brown.

title: sweetheart cookies
directions: Beat butter at medium speed with a mixer until creamy; gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add eggs and almond extract, beating well.
Combine flour and soda; add to creamed mixture, mixing well.
Roll to 1/4-inch thickness on a floured surface. Cut with a 2 1/2-inch heart-shaped or round cookie cutter.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool on wire racks.
Spread with buttercream frosting. Yield:
4 dozen.

title: cranberry coffee cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, dry ingredients, sour cream and flavoring.
Pour 1/2 the batter into a Bundt pan; top with 1/2 the cranberry sauce and 1/2 the walnuts.
Pour in rest of batter. Top with cranberry sauce and walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: m m's cheesy corn casserole
directions: Melt oleo; add milk and cream cheese (in micro together).
Add remaining ingredients and bake at 350° for 25 minutes, uncovered. Serves 8 to 10.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut lean part of steak in small cubes. Saute in margarine at medium heat for about 2 minutes. Put cubes of steak into a baking dish along with sour cream and mushroom soup. Bake for 25 minutes at 350°. Serve over egg noodles.

title: miniature skillet meat loaves
directions: Mix all ingredients together as you would a regular meat loaf. Form into individual loaves similar to salmon croquettes.
In large skillet, mix 1/2 cup ketchup and 1/2 cup water.
Place loaves in mixture.
Cover and simmer on medium heat for about 30 minutes.
Baste and turn one time while cooking.

title: pumpkin chiffon pie
directions: Combine slightly beaten egg yolks, 1/2 cup sugar, pumpkin, milk, sherry, salt and spices in double boiler.
Cook until thickened.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Add other ingredients and put in casserole.
Sprinkle with Ritz crackers on top and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mayonnaise rolls
directions: Grease muffin tins.
Spoon in mixture.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 6 rolls.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes in water.
When soft, drain and mash.
Mix all ingredients together well.
Put in casserole dish and put topping on.

title: shoney's strawberry pie
directions: Boil slow until thick.
While hot, pour in 1 small pack strawberry jello and dissolve.
Cool slightly and pour over strawberries in pie shell.

title: chocolate custard
directions: Put all ingredients in a blender (melt butter first) and blend thoroughly.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook pie in unbaked pie crust for 10 minutes.
Turn oven to 300°.
Cook until firm, approximately 45 minutes.

title: spicy ranch crackers
directions: Mix oil, seasoning mix and pepper in a bowl, or shake in a jar.
Place crackers in a gallon-size Ziploc bag.
Pour oil mixture into bag and shake until crackers are well covered.
Drain crackers on paper towels and store in a clean Ziploc bag.
(These are incredibly good and stay fresh and crispy "forever", contrary to what you might think.)

title: potato pancakes
directions: Peel large potatoes; cover with cold water.
Let stand overnight.
Drain well.
Add eggs and mix.
Stir in rest of ingredients.
Drop from tablespoon onto hot, well-greased skillet.
Brown on both sides.
Serve with applesauce.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients; press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.
Mix cheese, Cool Whip and sugar; cream until fluffy.
Spread on top of pretzel mixture.
Mix last 3 ingredients and put on top.
Chill.

title: mom's strudel coffee cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and vanilla; add eggs and beat well. Add dry ingredients alternately with sour cream.
Spread half of the batter into greased and floured pan.
Then, cream butter, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Add nuts.
Sprinkle half of this mixture over batter.
Spread remaining half of batter over mixture in pan. Spread the rest of brown sugar mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Bake in cast-iron Bundt pan.

title: fancy green salad
directions: Tear lettuce and/or spinach 1/3 to 1/2-inch deep in dish. Make fairly complete layers of the 8 ingredients over the greens.

title: microwave bacon-cheese macaroni
directions: Place bacon and onion in 2-quart glass casserole.
Cover and microwave (High setting) 4 minutes.
Stir.
Microwave 4 minutes more or until bacon is crisp.
Add soup and milk well.
Cover. Microwave (High setting) 15 minutes or until hot and bubbly, stirring every 5 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: nut and poppy seed rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Divide into 4 balls.
Place in pan and raise for 1 hour.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Use filling desired.

title: blt pasta salad
directions: Combine the first four ingredients.
Then combine the mayo and ranch to your taste and/or desired creaminess.
Wa! La!! Enjoy!!

title: new england crab and lobster soup
directions: In a large saute pan or Dutch oven at medium heat, melt butter. Add celery, onion, parsley, paprika and cayenne pepper.
Saute until it begins to soften and brown.
Add flour to roux consistency.
Add crab meat and lobster meat, stirring until hot. Slowly stir in white wine.
Cook for 2 minutes and then add the half and half.
Bring just to boiling point and stir 30 seconds. Remove from heat and let stand for 5 minutes.
Serve in your best soup bowls with toast points on side.
Garnish with fresh, chopped parsley.
Serves 6.

title: orange mandarin cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into 3 (9-inch) greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.

title: three cheese pie
directions: Mix cheeses, onion and flour.
Spread half in each of two (10-inch) greased quiche dishes.
Beat eggs slightly; beat in milk, salt, mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour half over each cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° until set, about 35 to 40 minutes. Let stand 10 minutes; arrange tomato slices around the edge of pie, overlapping slightly.

title: savory pork roast
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Coat roast with oil; rub sage over entire roast.
Place roast flat side up on rack in roasting pan. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Bake for 2 to 3 hours or until meat thermometer reaches 170°.

title: moo shu pork
directions: Place mushrooms, golden lilies and fungus in separate bowls. Pour boiling water over each.
Soak separately at least 20 minutes. Remove stems from mushrooms, hard tips from golden lilies and hard part of fungus.
Discard.
Cut ingredients julienne.
Mix pork with 1 tablespoon of soy sauce and cornstarch.
Heat 2 tablespoons of oil in wok to 275°.
Add scallion and ginger.
Stir-fry 1 minute. Add pork.
Stir-fry at 400° for about 1 minute or until color changes.
Add 1 tablespoon of soy sauce, sherry and sugar.
Remove.

title: meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large bowl, combine meat, onion soup mix, eggs, catsup, bread crumbs and water.
Shape into loaf and place in baking pan.
Bake about 45 minutes or until done. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Brown pork in a small amount of hot fat.
Add 1/2 cup water. Cover and simmer until tender, about 1 hour.
Drain pineapple, reserving the syrup.

title: delightful date bread
directions: Combine dates, nuts and soda in a bowl.
Add oleo and water. Stir until oleo is melted, then set aside.
Beat eggs until foamy. Add vanilla, sugar and flour.
Add date mixture and mix well. Pour batter into loaf pan and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Enjoy!

title: fiesta rice
directions: Heat the can of chicken broth, water and salsa in a saucepan. Bring to a boil. Stir in the uncooked instant rice. Cover and remove from heat. Let stand 5 minutes. Fluff with fork.

title: refrigerator mashed potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in salted water until done, drain and mash.
Add sour cream, cream cheese, onion salt, salt, pepper and margarine. Beat until smooth and fluffy.
Stores 2 weeks in refrigerator.
To serve, place desired amount in greased casserole.
Dot with margarine and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 8 cups.
To bake entire amount, use a 2 quart casserole.

title: orange salad
directions: Dissolve orange Jello in hot water.
Stir thoroughly.
Add pineapple and orange juice concentrate.
Mix well.	Pour into large serving bowl and refrigerate at least 30 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese (christopher's way)
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese according to package directions. Add remaining ingredients.
Stir until peas are warmed through.

title: baked squash
directions: Slice squash. Put squash and onion in small amount of water and boil until tender.
Mash and add butter, pepper, eggs, milk, 4 crushed saltines and grated cheese.
Put in casserole dish, top with crushed crackers and more grated cheese.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Salt to taste.
Serves eight.

title: apricot nut bread
directions: Soak dried fruit for 20 minutes in warm water.
Cream together 1 cup sugar, shortening and egg.
Stir in 1/4 cup sugar and the orange juice.
Add dry ingredients; blend well.
Drain apricots and stir into batter.
Add nuts.
Bake in greased and floured loaf pan at 350° for 65 minutes or until done.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: whipped cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries; add sugar and refrigerate overnight. Add grapes which have been halved and seeded, nuts and whipped cream. Refrigerate for two to three hours before serving.

title: cucumber dip
directions: Drain all the water from the cucumber.
Mix all ingredients. Serve cold with favorite chips. Makes 3 cups.

title: lemon squares
directions: Make crust:
Heat oven to 350°.
In a medium bowl, beat the butter and sugar until creamy.
Gradually stir in the flour. Press evenly into the bottom of an ungreased 9-inch square baking pan.
Bake until golden, 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chicken divan(club member: kristi mayfield)
directions: Cook broccoli in boiling salted water until tender; drain. Place spears crosswise in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Melt butter in saucepan; blend in flour. Add broth all at once and cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens. Stir in cream, sherry, salt and dash of pepper. Pour half the sauce over broccoli. Top with chicken slices. To remaining sauce, add 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese. Pour over chicken and sprinkle with additional Parmesan cheese. Bake for about 20 minutes or until hot at 350°. Broil just until sauce is golden brown. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cocoa cake
directions: Cream the sugar, shortening and eggs.
Add the rest and mix. Bake at 350°.

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: In a mixing bowl or blender, beat together cottage cheese and Blue cheese until fairly smooth.
Blend in milk, lemon juice and salt.
Cover and chill.

title: baked eggplant
directions: Peel and dice eggplant.
Cook in a little water until tender over low heat.
Make a cream sauce with butter or drippings, flour and milk.
Add cheese and melt over low heat.
Drain eggplant and mash it.
Add cracker crumbs, tomatoes, beaten egg yolks and salt. Mix together with the cream sauce and fold in egg whites and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: lemon cake top pudding
directions: Combine butter and sugar.
Add flour, salt, lemon juice and rind.
Stir egg yolks, mixed with milk.
Fold stiffly beaten egg whites in.
Pour in custard cups or large bowl or dish.
Set in pan of water.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Arrange chicken in layers, skin side up, in large shallow baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over chicken. Bake for one hour or so at 350°, then turn and finish baking until tender.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Top with nuts and coconut.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Microwave the frozen broccoli bits for eight minutes.
While broccoli is cooking, mix the beaten eggs, diced onion, soup and stuffing mix in a large bowl.
Add broccoli to other ingredients and mix well.
Pour mixture into a greased casserole dish.
Top with the shredded Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serve warm.

title: barbecue beef(makes 40 sandwiches)
directions: Place chuck roast in large roasting pan.
Combine remaining ingredients in a large bowl.
Pour over beef.
Cover and bake slow (300°) for 6 hours.
One hour before finishing baking, remove bones and mash beef with potato masher to shred beef.
Freezes well.

title: italian meat balls
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients; season to taste.
Form into 1-inch balls and brown in hot olive oil.
Add to spaghetti sauce and cook about 1 hour.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix together both ingredients.
Add salt to taste, if desired. Do not add real shrimp to this recipe because it will not taste good.
Serve with crackers.

title: sour cream enchiladas
directions: (Shredded chicken may be added if you want Sour Cream Chicken Enchiladas.)

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Utensils Needed:
Large mixing bowl, egg beater, mixing spoon, measuring cup, measuring spoons, ice cream freezer, rock salt and ice (one part rock salt to eight parts ice)

title: seafoam candy(like divinity)
directions: Combine sugars, water, corn syrup and salt in a 2-quart saucepan.
Cook, covered, until mixture boils rapidly.
Remove lid and cook, without stirring, until temperature reaches 260° or until it forms a soft ball in cold water.
Remove from heat.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Cook hamburger patties until done, not brown.
Cut potatoes in slices.
Put in a large casserole dish (3-quart).
Add milk and onion.
Cover and bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: cold cherry soup
directions: Mix the water, wine, sugar and lemon juice in a pan and heat. Add pitted cherries (reserve about 1/4 cup for garnish).
Bring to a boil; reduce and simmer for about 5 minutes.
Puree the cherries in a food mill, blender or food processor.
Transfer to a mixing bowl.
Add lemon zest and Kirsch.
Let cool to room temperature, then chill for 3 or 4 hours at least.

title: stuffed jewish rye bread
directions: Cut rectangle out of the top of the bread. Take the cut-out top and cut into 1-2 inch pieces. Mix all the ingredients together and place in the center of the bread. Use the bread cubes for dipping.

title: bourbon balls
directions: Combine crumbs, sugar, nuts and cocoa.
Mix well. Stir in corn syrup and bourbon. Blend thoroughly. Set in refrigerator for 2 to 3 hours. Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in powdered sugar. Store in airtight container in refrigerator.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Combine flour, baking powder, soda and cinnamon; set aside.
In separate larger bowl, whisk together applesauce, sugar, egg whites, bananas and vanilla.
Add flour mixture all at once.
Stir gently to blend.
Pour batter into prepared pan and bake for 1 hour or until knife inserted into center comes out clean.

title: mayonnaise
directions: Blend cashews and water in blender.
Cook until thick.
Add lemon juice, garlic powder, onion and salt.
Mix well.
Cool and store.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease loaf pan.
Cream the shortening and sugar.
Beat eggs until light and fluffy.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add bananas and lemon juice.
Add dry ingredients.
Stir nuts into mixture.
Pour into loaf pan.
Bake 1 1/4 hours at 375°. Cool on rack.

title: lemon iced tea
directions: Microwave tea bags in 1 cup water on High for 3 minutes and 50 seconds.
Mix tea, sugar, lemonade and water together.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: "mighty mix"
directions: Fry and mix.
Put in crock-pot.
Serve with Tostitos (corn chips).

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients.
Sift together the flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and vanilla.
Pour the boiling water over the oatmeal; stir well and let set.
Mix together the sugar mixture with the flour mixture.
Add oatmeal and bake at 350° until done.

title: fudge muffins
directions: Melt chocolate and butter gently in Teflon pan.
Add sugar, salt and flour.
Stir well.
Add eggs one at a time.
Stir in (don't beat).
Add vanilla and nuts.
Fill muffin pans (lined with paper baking cups) 3/4 full.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes (20 minutes for mini muffins).
Makes 2 dozen.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Melt yeast in 1/4 cup warm water.
Mix dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening; add milk and yeast mixture.
Knead.
While you're kneading, say the Lord's Prayer and bless it for everyone who eats it.
Put it in covered bowl and place in refrigerator and use whenever you want.
Roll and cut.
Put in pan and let rise 30 minutes.
Then cook at 450° or 475° in dark pans for about 10 minutes or until browned as desired.
Makes around 36 biscuits. Dough may be stored in refrigerator for several days.

title: stuffed date cookies
directions: Stuff dates with nuts.
Cream shortening and sugar until light; beat in egg.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add alternately with sour cream to creamed mixture.
Stir in dates.
Drop onto greased cookie sheet (a date per cookie).
Bake in 375° oven.
Watch closely; do not overbrown.
Cool.
Top with Golden Frosting. Makes 5 1/2 dozen.

title: special k bars
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients and heat to dissolve the sugar.
Pour over Special K and mix thoroughly.
Pack into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt together the butterscotch and chocolate chips; spread over the top of the bars.
Cut and serve.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Bake cake according to package instructions in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish that is suitable for storage in the refrigerator, using amounts of egg and water indicated on the box.
Cool cake, then poke holes in cake with a metal skewer.
Dilute jello with hot water and slowly pour over cake.
Prepare pudding according to package instructions.
Spread over cake.
Mash frozen strawberries (thaw slightly in microwave) and mix with Cool Whip.
Spread strawberry mixture over cake.
Cover and refrigerate for 2 hours before serving.

title: corn bread
directions: Grease a heavy pan well.
Heat oven to 375°.
Mix all ingredients together and put in hot pan.
Bake until brown.

title: poor man's cake
directions: Cook raisins in 2 cups water until 1 cup water remains.
Add shortening and vanilla.
Let cool.
Sift together the following: flour, soda, baking powder, cinnamon, allspice, nutmeg, cloves and salt.
Add to the raisin mixture.
Pour into a greased and floured cake pan and bake in slow 250° oven until done, about 1 hour.

title: pineapple cheese cake
directions: Mix first three ingredients together, reserving 1/2 cup. Press remainder in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together jello and water and chill until slightly set.
Mix together softened cream cheese, sugar and pineapple and add to jello mixture.
Whip 1 can chilled evaporated milk.
Fold cheese and jello mixture into the whipped milk.
Pour into crust and sprinkle with remaining graham crumbs. Chill several hours.

title: instant russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Use 2 tablespoons to 1 cup hot water per serving.
Stir well.
Two teaspoons really enough.

title: chocolate jello cake
directions: Cream shortening and eggs.
Add Jell-O pudding, dry ingredients and milk.
Pour into greased cake pans and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: corn meal pancakes
directions: Mix together the corn meal, flour, sugar, salt and baking powder.
In a separate bowl, beat together egg and milk.
Add dry ingredients and blend together.
Pour some batter (enough to make a pancake) onto a hot lightly greased griddle.
Bake until golden brown, turning only once.

title: lemon poppy tea cake
directions: Beat butter until light.
Gradually add sugar and eggs, one at a time.
Mix in lemon rind, vanilla and poppy seed.
Sift together dry ingredients (flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt).
Add alternately with yogurt and mix until smooth.
Pour into buttered and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix all together and bake in oblong pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or
until done.

title: clam chowder
directions: Mix together and serve very hot.

title: sweet 'n sour chicken
directions: Arrange chicken in baking dish.
Mix Russian dressing, preserves, soup mix and water.
Pour over chicken.
Bake, covered with foil, for 1 hour at 350°.
Uncover.
Add pineapple and green pepper.
Bake another 1/2 hour.

title: sweet-sour red cabbage
directions: Melt margarine in skillet and saute onion until tender.
Add cabbage, cloves, salt and boiling water.
Cover tightly and simmer 15 minutes.
Core, but do not pare, the apples; slice thinly.
Add to cabbage and simmer 1 hour.
Add more water, if necessary.
Stir in vinegar and brown sugar.
Simmer 15 minutes longer.
Can use Sugar Twin brown sugar for diabetic.

title: chili egg puffs
directions: Beat eggs until light and lemon colored.
Add other ingredients.
Butter well a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.
Serves 10.

title: scalloped pineapple casserole
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in the pineapple and lemon juice.
Gently fold in bread cubes.

title: janet's glazed fresh blueberry pie
directions: Stir cheese until smooth.
Spread on bottom of cooled pie shell.
Combine 1 cup berries with water, sugar, cornstarch and lemon juice.
Bring to boil over medium heat.
Cook until thick and glossy, stirring constantly.
Cool completely.
In large bowl mix 4 cups berries with cooled glaze, carefully folding together. Spoon into pie shell.
Garnish or cover with whipped cream or topping.

title: nappa cabbage salad
directions: Combine the first 2 ingredients and refrigerate until ready to use.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Line oblong dish or pan with 1 layer of graham crackers.
Mix pudding with milk, then fold with Cool Whip.
Continue with layer of pudding and the crackers until all mixture is used, ending with crackers on top.
Spread icing on crackers.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in greased pans.
Makes 3 small loaves.
Bake 25 minutes at 325° or 2 bread loaf size pans for 60 minutes at 325°.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Let all stand in a dark place for 10 days.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Wash chicken or thaw diced chicken.
Cook fresh chicken in water to cover in saucepan until tender.
Drain, reserving 1 1/2 cups broth.
(If you use frozen diced chicken, use 1 1/2 cups canned broth.)
Chop chicken in bite size pieces.
Saute onion in a small amount of butter in large skillet.
Add soups, green chilies and broth; mix well.
Stir in chicken.
Layer tortillas, chicken mixture and cheese 1/2 at a time in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Garnish with salsa and sour cream.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Combine ingredients, mashing artichoke hearts with fork.
(Or combine in food processor.)
Do not puree too finely.
Bake in 1 1/2-quart casserole at 350° for 20 minutes until bubbly.
Serve with crackers.

title: busby's broccoli dip
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Combine all ingredients with broccoli.
Cook over very low heat until all ingredients are melted.
Serve hot with chips.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and cream cheese until fluffy.
Add sugar; cream until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time.
Use desired flavoring.
To creamed mixture, add flour, about 1/3 at a time. Mix thoroughly.
Pour into greased tube pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: summer sausage
directions: Mix well and put in covered bowl in refrigerator for 4 to 5 days.
Form into rolls and bake 4 to 6 hours (175° or 200°).

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients well, except cabbage, using season according to taste.
Dip cabbage leaves into boiling water until tender.
Roll small amount of mixture into cabbage leaves.
Place in Dutch oven.
Pour 2 cans stewed or plain tomatoes over rolls. Add water to cover and cook until done.

title: easy beef or chicken kabobs
directions: Whisk first 7 ingredient in large bowl.
Add peppers and mushrooms.
Use to marinate meat also.
Place meat and vegetables on skewers in an alternating manner.
Broil or barbecue.
Enjoy!

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Make sure all fruit is drained well.
Blend all ingredients and store in the refrigerator.
Salad is best made 24 hours ahead.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken, cut into medium pieces and put in bottom of 9 x 13 inch pan.
Mix soup and sour cream and pour over chicken pieces.
Crush Ritz crackers, put on top and then spoon melted margarine on top.
Bake at 350° about 40 minutes or until brown and bubbly. Serve over cooked rice.

title: date and nut kisses
directions: Add salt to egg whites.
Whip until stiff.
Whip in sugar, a tablespoonful at a time.
Beat constantly.
Fold in other ingredients.
Drop batter from teaspoon onto greased paper.
Bake kisses in slow 225° oven until they will retain their shape.

title: sausage stars
directions: Put wonton wraps in cupcake tins.
Brush tips with vegetable oil.
Bake in 350° oven for 5 minutes.
Mix all ingredients well. Fill wonton wraps with ingredients.
Place wontons on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake 5 minutes at 350°.

title: roast beef casserole
directions: Line a greased casserole with cubed potatoes.
Add a layer of cubed carrots and then a layer of onions.
Salt and pepper to taste. Add mushroom soup and water.
Then add roast beef.
Bake at 350° until potatoes and carrots are done.
Top with shredded cheese and put under broiler until cheese melts.

title: quick southwestern pizza
directions: Move oven rack to lowest position and heat oven to 450°.
Mix the Bisquick and water; beat vigorously 20 strokes.
Turn onto floured surface and knead about 60 times or until not sticky. Press into a 12-inch greased pizza pan.
Mix chicken and salsa. Sprinkle crust with 1 cup cheese.
Top with onion, chicken mixture and pepper.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt enough margarine in a glass cake dish to cover the bottom.
Cover with brown sugar.
Arrange pineapple rings and cherries on bottom.
Add the cake (could be homemade also) mix. Bake according to cake directions.
After cake is finished, flip onto another dish so pineapple is on top.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and butter in pan.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly until butter melts.
Remove from heat and add syrup to eggs.
Add pecans and vanilla.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: pie crust
directions: In food processor, combine ingredients. Blend well until crumbly (like cornmeal). Slowly add 5 Tbsp. of cold water in one at a time.

title: lemon butter potatoes
directions: Boil as many red skinned potatoes as necessary for 2 people. Drain when cooked.
Place back in pan and cook with diet margarine and lemon until coated.
Sprinkle with salt, lemon pepper, paprika and last, parsley flakes.

title: vegetable bake
directions: In the bottom of a 9 x 9-inch glass casserole dish, pour thawed veggies.
Top with grated cheese.
Empty can of mushroom soup over cheese.

title: bean salad
directions: Bring oil, sugar and vinegar to a boil.
When mixture cools, pour over beans and onion and marinate overnight.

title: company beans(serves about 12 people)
directions: Mix ingredients.
Place in large baking dish covered with bacon strips.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 1 hour.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees.
After chicken is cooled, chop up 3 cups.
Add to 4 cups hot chicken broth.
Add rotel tomatoes, then add velveeta cheese cut into chunks.
Stir until cheese is melted. Add cooked pasta.
Store in covered dish in refrigerator overnight.
Bake for 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: easy heavenly dessert
directions: Combine flour, sugar, melted margarine and nuts in bowl; mix well.
Press over bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.
Cream confectioners sugar and cream cheese in mixer bowl until light.
Mix in 1 cup whipped topping.
Spread over baked layer.
Combine chocolate pudding mix and vanilla pudding mix with cold milk in large bowl; mix until smooth. Spread over cream cheese layer.
Top with remaining 2 cups whipped topping.
Chill overnight.
Yield:
15 servings.

title: meat balls in stewed tomatoes
directions: In a large pot, simmer tomatoes, 1 cup water, salt and pepper. Meanwhile, prepare meat.
Mix meat, bread, onions, salt and pepper.
Shape into meat balls and drop into stewed tomatoes. Simmer for about 1 hour.

title: hearty chicken stew
directions: Toss chicken with flour, salt and pepper in plastic bag.
Coat well.
Melt margarine in large skillet.
Add chicken with a little more flour.
Saute until brown.
Add onion and celery; saute 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to boil and simmer until vegetables are tender.
Serves 4.
Serve with salad and rolls.
Enjoy!

title: taco dip
directions: Cook hamburg; add other ingredients except cheese.
Heat through over low heat.
Layer half of mixture in dish; layer half of cheese.
Repeat.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: witches' brew
directions: Brown bacon, hamburger, onions and green pepper.
Boil egg noodles; drain.
Mix meat mixture and noodles together.
Add mushroom soup, kidney beans and tomatoes.
Mix and place in baking dish.
Grate yellow cheese on top.
Bake to heat through and melt cheese.

title: sweet and sour pork or chicken
directions: Combine soy sauce and garlic in medium bowl.
Cut pork into 1-inch piecs.
Toss in mixture.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat well the first 5 ingredients.
Mix together the remaining ingredients and add to first mixture.
Mix.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in 2 loaf pans, greased and floured.

title: cream cheese squares
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, sugar and butter.
Press in 8-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Cool.
Beat cheese until fluffy; add 1/2 cup sugar, beating constantly.
Add salt, lemon juice and vanilla.
Blend in Cool Whip and milk.
Put in crumbs and chill 3 hours.

title: brown sugar pie
directions: Combine sugar and flour.
Add eggs, milk and butter.
Pour into uncooked 10-inch pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pluck it cake
directions: Grease Bundt or tube pan.
Preheat oven to 300°.
Cut biscuits into quarters and place half in pan.
Combine remaining ingredients in saucepan and boil 1 minute.

title: plum cake
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: lemon fluff
directions: Combine lemonade with condensed milk.
Fold in Cool Whip; pour lemonade mixture in crust.
Refrigerate for at least 20 minutes.

title: tasty vegetable soup(meatless)
directions: Cut vegetables into bite size pieces.
Add enough water to cover, and simmer covered until desired doneness.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: raspberry bounce
directions: A few drops of vanilla in pan immediately after frying fish will help eliminate odor.

title: bob's chocolate pie
directions: Combine chocolate instant pudding and milk in bowl; whisk until smooth.
Let sit for 5 minutes to get firm.
Add Cool Whip and chopped peanut butter cups. Pour into crumb crust.
Freeze overnight.
Get out 10 minutes before serving.

title: spicy spaghetti with broccoli and sun-dried tomatoes
directions: In a large pot start the water boiling for the spaghetti.
In a large pan heat oil and red pepper flakes over low heat.
Add onion and cook 2 minutes.
Add yellow and red peppers and cook 2 more minutes.

title: ice cream
directions: Mix Pet milk, water, sugar and eggs together well.
Then add vanilla and put into ice cream freezer.

title: chocolate applesauce no egg cake
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together on medium speed in large mixer bowl.
Add oil, raisins and nuts; mix on medium speed.
Add flour and vanilla by hand until thoroughly mixed.
Pour into a well-greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Cool.
Store in refrigerator for optional freshness.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Mix well and refrigerate.

title: crock-pot baked beans
directions: Brown, crumble and drain ground beef.
Mix with all other ingredients in crock-pot.
Cook 2 hours.
Serves 6. Great over cornbread.

title: coconut rice
directions: Rinse and soak rice for up to 15 minutes.
Add coconut milk, salt, onion, sugar, water and oil. Set to cook in a rice cooker. When cooked, let rice sit for 15-20 minutes.
Remove lid and mix well.
Serve with
Burmese Red Curry.

title: tuna burgers
directions: Combine in bowl and mix well.
Split and butter 6 hamburger buns.
Fill buns with tuna mixture and replace tops.
Heat in paper sandwich bags on cookie sheet at 350°.

title: lye soap
directions: Prepare grease.
Heat together fat and drippings; strain.
If fat contains meat juices or lots of dark particles, allow to cool, then use fat which rises to the top.
Discard dark particles which settle on bottom.
In large iron kettle, mix lye, Borax and water. Slowly add warm grease.
Stir, stir, stir frequently throughout the day with wooden spoon.
When the mix becomes firm and can no longer be stirred easily, wear gloves and pour soap into forms.
Do not double recipe.
Shave off to wash clothes.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Sprinkle fried eggplant slices with garlic powder, salt, pepper and crushed red pepper as desired.

title: jello cubes
directions: Combine gelatine with cold water; set aside.
Mix jello powder with
sugar;
add	boiling
water.
Stir
in
gelatine mixture. When completely
dissolved,
pour
into a 9 x 9-inch pan (easier if	pan
is already in the refrigerator, then pour in jello). Refrigerate until firm, about 4 hours.
Slice into 1 or 2-inch cubes.

title: party chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place on lettuce leaves and serve with finger sandwiches.

title: grandma's potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes until done.
Drain.
Add next 3 ingredients, if desired.

title: impossible ham and cheese pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 10 x 1 1/2-inch pie plate.
Rinse peas under cold running water to separate; drain.
Mix peas, ham and cheese in plate.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth (15 seconds in blender on high or 1 minute with hand mixer).
Pour into plate.
Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean, 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: dump cake
directions: In 9 x 13-inch cake pan, spread pie filling over bottom. Spread pineapple over pie filling.
Pour dry cake mix evenly over pineapple.
Cut butter in pads and place on cake mix.
Sprinkle nuts over tops.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: maple walnut muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter.
Mix with nuts and toast in oven until golden brown.
Beat together eggs, milk, syrup and shortening.
In separate bowl, combine dry ingredients.
Stir into egg mixture.
Do not overbeat!
Add raisins and most of the nuts. Pour into well-greased muffin tins.
Drizzle each muffin with extra syrup; top with nuts.
Bake for 20 minutes.

title: old fashioned tea cakes
directions: Cream
butter,	sugar,	baking	powder,
salt,	eggs and vanilla
together
in
mixing
bowl.
Add
a
little milk and a little
flour
alternately until all milk is used; then work in enough flour to make a stiff dough.
Chill.
Then roll out thin and cut.
Bake at 350° about 8 minutes until light brown.

title: mocha cocoa frosting(from an old hershey recipe)
directions: Cream butter thoroughly.
Add vanilla.
Sift together the powdered sugar, cocoa and salt.
Add alternately with coffee to the butter mixture, beating to a spreading consistency.
Spread on warm cake.
Yields 1 3/4 cups icing (enough for an 8 or 9-inch) layer cake.

title: easy pasta bake
directions: Brown and drain hamburger.
Combine hamburger, pasta, sauce and Parmesan.
Spread in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread Mozzarella over the top.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: white chocolate cream cheese frosting
directions: Melt chocolate on low heat in heavy saucepan; stir constantly. Cool 10 minutes; stir occasionally.
Beat cream cheese and butter at medium speed with electric mixer.
Gradually add chocolate, beating constantly until blended.
Gradually add powdered sugar; beat until smooth.
Stir in vanilla.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine and add flavoring; add one egg yolk at a time.
Add 3 cups flour, a little at a time, and beat.
Put fruit mix and nuts, minced, in 1 cup of flour.
(Don't cut cherries.)
Beat egg whites and fold in.
Bake in tube or loaf pan lined with wax paper.
Bake in 250° oven for 3 hours.
While still hot, put wine on it.
Wrap in cloth for 24 hours.
Remove from cloth and wrap in foil.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Marinate overnight.
Stir in bacon before serving.

title: savory steak sauce
directions: Melt butter; add mushrooms and onion and saute lightly.
Add all remaining ingredients and simmer about 5 minutes.
Serve over broiled steak or hamburger patties.
Serve with beef tenderloin. Makes about 1 cup sauce.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers, onions and peppers in salt water for 3 hours. Drain well.
Heat vinegar and sugar.
Add spices and mustard and celery seed.
Add cucumbers (etc.) and boil 10 minutes.
Hot pack in quarts or pints.
Seal.

title: baked cinnamon bread custard
directions: Arrange bread in a double layer in a lightly greased 9 inch by 13 inch baking pan. (Cut bread as needed to cover bottom of pan.) Whisk together eggs, egg yolks and sugar. Gradually add milk, half and half and vanilla. Pour mixture over bread. Bake in a 375° oven for 25 to 30 minutes, or until a knife inserted in the center comes out clean. Dust with powdered sugar while warm and serve.

title: meat and potato cakes
directions: Combine all ingredients, except the flour and drippings.
Shape into 6 patties or cakes.
Roll very lightly in the flour; saute in drippings until nicely browned.
These are delicious served with tomato sauce, canned beef gravy or canned steak sauce.

title: sour cream raisin pie
directions: Line
pie
plate
with crust, if you make you own.
Mix sugar and
sour cream;
add eggs.
Combine cinnamon, salt and raisins; add
to mixture.
Pour into crust.	Bake at 450° for 10 minutes; reduce heat to 350° for 30 minutes longer.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Cook and drain hamburger.
Add other ingredients and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve on hamburger buns.

title: vegetable stock
directions: Scrub and cut vegetables and apple or pear.
Place in a stockpot with the bay leaves, peppercorns and water.
Cover; bring to a boil and simmer for 1 hour or more.
Strain the stock through a colander, pressing out the liquid from vegetables.
Vegetable stock will keep in refrigerator for 3 to 4 days.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and butter; add sugar and beat.
Cream until well blended.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat after each addition. Sift flour and dry ingredients together.
Add to other mixture alternately with milk to which vanilla has been added.
Blend thoroughly.
Turn into greased, lightly floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: sweet potato and cranberry casserole
directions: Mix together flour, brown sugar, oatmeal and cinnamon.
With a fork, cut the margarine into the flour mixture as with pie crust. This mixture should be crumbly.
Put yams and cranberries in casserole dish with 1 cup of flour mixture.
Put the rest of flour mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Last 10 minutes, put marshmallows on top and brown.
Cranberries will pop when done.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter. Thaw out hash browns in microwave. Combine all ingredients in mixing bowl.
Pour into casserole dish sprayed with nonstick cooking spray. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Take
out of oven and pour crushed corn flakes on top. Dab with squeeze butter.
Bake 5 more minutes.

title: marinated squash medley
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in a jar. Cover and shake well. Pour dressing over squash. Toss gently. Cover and chill 4 hours. Serve with a slotted spoon.

title: good salad
directions: Mix jello as usual.
Add drained pineapple and nuts; chill until hard set.
Blend the Cool Whip and cream cheese together and spread over jello mixture.
Cook the pineapple and lemon juices, sugar, flour and eggs until thick; cool.
Spread over cream cheese.
Sprinkle nuts over top.
Use a 9 x 12-inch dish. Refrigerate.

title: veggie bake
directions: Prepare vegetables according to package directions. Drain. Place half vegetables in ungreased 11 x 7 x 2 baking dish.

title: glazed salami
directions: Slice salami into 1/4-inch slices, but not through the bottom of salami.
Combine marmalade, brown sugar and mustard in a small bowl, stirring well.
Spread marmalade mixture over top of salami and between each slice; wrap in aluminum foil.
Place on baking sheet and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Uncover and bake 10 more minutes.
Serve with bread rounds.
Yields 16 appetizers.

title: christmas pickles
directions: Cut cucumbers into bite-sized pieces.
Cook with water to cover in saucepan until tender; drain.
Bring next 5 ingredients to a boil in saucepan.
Pour over cucumbers.
Let stand overnight. Drain and reserve syrup.
Bring reserved syrup to a boil in saucepan; pour over pickles.
Let stand overnight.
Mix cherries with cucumbers and syrup.
Bring to a boil.
Ladle into hot sterilized 1-pint jars.
Seal with 2 piece lids.
Process in boiling water bath for 10 minutes.
Yield: 6 to 8 pints.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Remove chicken from bone and place in bottom of casserole pan. Salt and pepper chicken to taste.
Mix together celery soup and chicken broth.
Pour over chicken.
Melt margarine and mix the flour and milk.
Pour this over chicken.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Beat butter and sugar until light.
Add eggs and vanilla; blend well.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to mixture and mix well.

title: french dressing
directions: Beat at high speed with mixer about 10 minutes.
Very Good!

title: daisy biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In mixing bowl cut cream cheese and butter into flour until mixture looks coarse.
Add milk all at once.
Stir just until dough clings together.
Knead gently on floured surface 4 to 5 strokes.
Roll or pat to less than 1/2 inch thick.
Cut with biscuit cutter.
To make daisy, make 6 slits around edge of each biscuit to within 1/4 inch from center.
Place on baking sheet.
Press down center with thumb; spoon 1/2 teaspoon marmalade or jam in center.
Bake 10 minutes.
Makes 11 or 12 biscuits.

title: ham, asparagus and cheese sandwich
directions: Slightly toast bread; then place slice of ham on toast. Arrange 3 or 4 asparagus spears on top of ham slice; top with slice of cheese.
Broil until cheese melts.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix together butter, cream cheese and confectioners sugar. In another bowl, beat French vanilla pudding, milk and Cool Whip. Add two mixtures together.
Put some of the crushed Oreos in the bottom of a pan or flower pot.
Add mixture.
Repeat layers, ending with Oreos on top.
Put gummy worms around top of the cake or an artificial flower in the center.

title: blushing peach pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Prepare pastry.
Mix peaches, sugar, flour and candies; turn into pastry-lined pie plate.

Dot with margarine. Cover with top crust that has slits cut in it; seal and flute. Cover edge with 2 to 3-inch strip of aluminum foil to prevent excessive browning; remove foil during last 15 minutes of baking. Bake until crust is golden brown and juice begins to bubble through slits in crust, 40 to 50 minutes.

title: crab casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter.
Add mushrooms.
Saute about 5 minutes.
Blend flour in well.
Add milk slowly.
Stir constantly.
Add remaining ingredients but crab meat and cheese. Cook 5 minutes.
Turn off heat.
Add crab meat.
Place in casserole dish and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: walnut pie
directions: Beat together all ingredients, except nuts.
Mix in nuts. Pour into pastry-lined pie pan.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes, until filling is set and pastry is nicely browned. Cool.
Serve slightly warm or cold.

title: broccoli cauliflower salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar together and pour over broccoli, cauliflower, onion and raisins mixed together. Refrigerate.

title: apple milkshake
directions: Blend cold milk, applesauce and ice cream in blender until smooth.
Sprinkle lightly with nutmeg or cinnamon after pouring into a large glass.

title: hot potato salad
directions: In covered pan, cook potatoes in small amount of boiling water 15 to 20 minutes or until tender. Drain. Set potatoes aside.

In the same pan, cook bacon over medium-high heat until bacon is crisp. Remove bacon. Drain, reserving 3 tablespoons drippings in pan. Add onion to pan. Stir-fry for 3 minutes. Stir in flour. Stir in sugar, salt, celery seed and pepper. Add water and vinegar. Cook and stir 1 minute longer. Stir in potatoes. Cover and simmer for 5 to 10 minutes or until heated through.
Top with reserved bacon and parsley. Makes 6 servings.

title: old fashioned banana cake
directions: Grease and
flour
2 (8-inch) cake pans or a 13 x 9-inch pan. Sift
flour,
sugar,
baking powder, baking soda and salt together in
a
large
mixing
bowl.
Mix
evaporated milk with lemon juice.
Add
alternately
to dry ingredients with butter and bananas.
Beat
at
medium
speed for 2 minutes.
Add eggs, beat 2 minutes.
Stir
in
chopped pecans.
Bake 40 minutes at 350° or until cake springs back when touched lightly in center with finger.
Frost with cream cheese or your favorite icing.

title: almond pudding crunch
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Put in shallow pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Stir every 5 minutes.
Blend pudding and milk.
Add 12 ounces Cool Whip into pudding.
Layer in oblong dish, crunchies on bottom, pudding in middle, crunchies on top; or put in parfait glasses in layers with whipped cream and cherry on top.

title: canadian sugar-cream pie
directions: Beat brown sugar, egg yolks, milk, syrup and butter.
Add vanilla, then egg whites, beaten stiff.
Pour into uncooked pie crust (1 crust).
Bake at 375° until golden, 1/2 hour to 45 minutes.

title: fudge
directions: Cook first four ingredients over medium heat to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat, do not stir.
Add vanilla and butter. Cool about an hour, add nuts and beat until it starts to lose its gloss.
Spread onto buttered plate.
Score while hot and cut when cool.

title: chicken dressing casserole
directions: In long buttered casserole
x
9-inch),
layer the following:	place chicken breasts (debone).
In saucepan, heat soups and
milk;
pour
this mixture over chicken breasts.	In saucepan, heat
broth, margarine and seasoning mix.
Pour over casserole.	Heat at 325° for 15 minutes or until bubbly.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix water with contents of both packets in the package.
Spread in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Cut up fryer into serving pieces.
Place raw chicken on top of rice.
Salt and pepper chicken to taste.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until chicken is tender.
Fifteen minutes before serving, spread 1 can cream of mushroom soup over chicken (direct from the can).

title: june weaver's cake mix cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and drop by teaspoon onto sifted powdered sugar.
Roll and shape, coating in sugar.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet and bake 8 to 10 minutes in 350° oven. (Baking time depends on size of cookies.)

title: skillet pudding
directions: Beat eggs. Add sugar and melted butter.
Mix cocoa and flour and sift together. Add milk and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Place 1-inch of water underneath dish while cooking. Serve hot with whipped cream.

title: no bake, chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine butter, sugar, cocoa and milk in sauce pan.
Bring to a boil, cook for 2 minutes or until sugar is dissolved and mixture is well blended, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter and vanilla, mix well.
Stir in oats.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper.
Let stand until firm.

title: stuffed mushrooms with crabmeat
directions: Remove stems from 18 mushrooms.
Rub the caps with a lemon half and place in baking dish. Set aside.
Mince stems and remaining 6 mushrooms.
Heat butter in skillet and add shallots and garlic.
Cook 2 minutes.
Add minced mushrooms.
Cook slowly 8 to 10 minutes. Add sherry and stir in crabmeat, parsley and bread crumbs; should be moist.
Add salt and pepper. Fill each cap with crab mixture. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 18 appetizers.

title: lobster sauce with shrimp, rice and vegetables
directions: In a large skillet, brown pork.
Cook until well done; drain. Stir-fry snow peas in a little olive oil; set aside.
Add carrot, celery, garlic, water and bouillon cube to pork.
Combine cornstarch with cold water and soy sauce; set aside.
Add shrimp and cook until almost firm, then add beaten egg and keep stirring. Stir in cornstarch mixture and stir until sauce thickens.
Place snow peas, rice and bean sprouts on dinner plates.
Spoon sauce over everything.

title: quick and delicious bread
directions: Combine sugar, warm water and yeast in large mixing bowl; let stand 10 minutes.
Combine cooking oil and egg; add to yeast mixture.
Stir in salt and 1 1/2 cups flour; mix well.
Stir in additional 1 1/2 cups flour; mix well.
Add enough of remaining flour to make a soft sticky dough.
Cover bowl and allow dough to rise to double bulk.
Punch down.
Turn dough over in bowl.
Allow to rise again to double bulk (covered), about 45 minutes.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Add ingredients as listed.
Place on a serving plate and top with cocktail sauce.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, flour and milk (little at a time).
Stir in rest; will be real thick and heavy.
Bake at 250° for 2 hours.

title: pasta caprese(serves 4)
directions: Heat oil, add garlic and cook until golden.
Remove from heat. Chop tomatoes and mix with warm garlic oil.
Add basil and salt and pepper to taste.

title: potato doughnuts
directions: Mix and turn out onto floured board.
Dough will be sticky. Dust with flour.
Break off small portions of dough.
Flatten to size of a quarter.
With thumbs, push hole in center and drop into hot oil.
Fry until golden brown.

title: sweet and sour kraut
directions: Fry bacon and onion.
Pour off fat. Add sauerkraut, tomatoes and sugar.
Let cook down to desired consistency, about 45 minutes on low heat.

title: party peas
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Mix all ingredients and pour in a 3-quart Pyrex dish.
Bake in a preheated oven at 300° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: tony's tiger bites
directions: Melt margarine in a large saucepan over low heat.
Add marshmallows and stir until completely melted.
Remove from heat. Stir in peanut butter until mixture is smooth.
Add cereal, stirring until well coated.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add onion, then buttermilk and egg.
Mix well.
Drop by spoonful in deep, hot cooking oil. Brown, turning to make sure they are brown all over.
Drain on paper towels.

title: twinkie cake
directions: Bake cake mix as directed.
Cool completely.
Cut lengthwise. Cook flour and milk until thick.
Let cool.
Mix remaining ingredients until fluffy (will take a few minutes).
Add cooled flour and milk mixture; beat again until fluffy.
Spread between cake layers.

title: tomato and onion salad
directions: Place 2 cups thinly sliced onions in a shallow dish.
Pour water over them and enough vinegar to cover onions.
Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon sugar.
Cover the dish and chill 3 to 4 hours.
Just before serving, drain the onions and mix with mayonnaise, celery seed and salt.
Serve on a bed of greens and a circle of sliced tomatoes with the onions in the center.

title: combination pie
directions: Melt butter in pan that the cake is being baked in.
Pour into cup.
Spread pie filling in pan.
Sprinkle cake mix over the pie filling.
Pour butter over all.
Add chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Delicious with ice cream.

title: stuffed acorn squash
directions: Prepare and microwave squash as directed.
Crumble ground beef into 2-quart casserole.
Cover loosely and microwave on High 5 to 6 minutes, breaking up and stirring after 3 minutes, until no longer pink; drain.
Stir in apple, raisins, salt and nutmeg.
Remove stems and cut thin slice from pointed ends of squash, if necessary, to prevent tipping.
Scoop squash from rind, leaving 1/4-inch thick shell.
Stir squash into beef mixture; spoon into shells.
Sprinkle 1 teaspoon sugar over mixture in each shell; drizzle with margarine.
Cover loosely and microwave on High 7 to 9 minutes or until hot.
Uncover and let stand 3 minutes.

title: pepper jelly
directions: Seed the peppers, then grind or chop them.
Mix peppers with sugar and vinegar.
Bring to a boil and boil 1 minute.
Lower fire and cook for 5 minutes.
Add Certo and put in jars.
Makes 3 1/2 pints.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine butter and crackers;
spoon half the crumbs into a shallow 2 quart baking dish.
Top with chicken.
Combine sour cream, soups and chicken broth; add salt and pepper.
Pour over chicken
and
top with remaining crumbs.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Mix together the ground zucchini,
onions, green pepper and salt.
Let stand overnight.
In morning,
drain
and rinse in cold water and drain again.
Put in
large
kettle
and add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a
boil
and simmer uncovered for 30 minutes.
Put in hot jars and seal.

title: hermits
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Add spices, flour and soda; mix well.
Fold in raisins and walnuts.
Drop by teaspoonful onto baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: buttery biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Shred frozen butter into the flour very quickly.
Add the milk and stir just until mixed.
Roll out dough and cut with biscuit cutter.
Bake at 400° until golden brown.

title: green pepper beef steak
directions: Cut beef into thin strips 1/8-inch thick.
Combine soy sauce, garlic and ginger.
Add beef.
Toss and set aside.
Prepare vegetables.
Heat oil in large frypan or wok.
Add beef and toss over high heat until browned.
Taste meat; if it is not tender, cover and simmer 30 to 40 minutes on low heat.
Turn heat up and add vegetables.
Toss about 10 minutes.
Mix cornstarch with water.
Add to pan; stir and cook until thickened.
Add tomatoes and heat.

title: cheese roll
directions: In medium bowl, blend together softened cream cheese with onions, green chilies, Cheddar cheese and garlic salt.
Form 1 large or 2 small rolls.
Roll in pecans until covered. Refrigerate until firm.
Serve with crackers or chips.
This may also be frozen very nicely.

title: shrimp sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Blend with wire whisk and chill.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and bring to a boil.
Immediately turn off heat.
Stir occasionally to keep from sticking.

title: wiesbaden bread(cookies)
directions: In a large mixing bowl, beat together 1 cup sugar and butter until fluffy.
Separate one of the eggs, setting aside yolk to use in cookie glaze.
Add egg white and other egg to butter mixture, mixing until crumbled.
Stir together flour, 1 1/2 teaspoons cinnamon and baking powder.
Add to butter mixture, beating well. Cover and chill dough for 3 hours or overnight.
Roll out half the dough at a time on a lightly floured surface to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut into shapes with cookie cutters.
Place cookies 1 1/2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Stir together reserved egg yolk and milk.
Brush on cookies.

title: pea salad
directions: Drain peas.
Dice eggs, cheese and pickles.
Combine with onion and peas.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add mayonnaise; mix well.
Let stand in the refrigerator for several hours before serving.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Blend
all ingredients together well.
Pour into baking pan. Bake at 450° for about 30 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: nana's molasses sugar cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add molasses and egg.
Beat well. In separate bowl, sift together flour, baking soda, cinnamon, cloves, ginger and salt.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Take 1 cup of the flour to roll chopped fruit and nuts in. Cream butter and sugar.
Add well beaten eggs.
Add flour and baking powder.
Add fruit, nuts and flavoring.

title: bubble buns
directions: Grease 10 (2 1/2-inch) muffin cups.
Stir together walnuts, sugar and cinnamon.
Separate biscuits and cut into quarters; shape into balls.
Coat each ball with mayonnaise, then roll in walnut mixture.
Place 4 in each muffin cup.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 17 minutes or until brown.
Remove carefully and serve warm. Makes 10.

title: sweet-sour pineapple pork
directions: Combine pork, sherry, salt and 1 teaspoon of the cornstarch in a bowl.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Meanwhile, drain pineapple and pickles, saving juice of both.
Cut tomato into wedges.
Deep fry pork about 6 minutes.
Remove to a warming platter.
In a saucepan, saute the garlic in 1 tablespoon oil.
Add juices and soy sauce. Stir in remaining cornstarch.
Heat, stirring until thickened.
Add pineapple, pickles and tomato, stirring gently.
Pour over warm pork and serve at once.
Serve with rice for 4.

title: no fat, lo-cal baked apple dessert
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Wash and core the apples.
Place in lightly greased baking pan (or use Pam).
Pour about 3/4-inch soda into pan and sprinkle sweetener and cinnamon into center of each apple.
Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until soft.

title: parmesan pita crisps
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Split pitas and cut into quarters. Lay dough side up on cookie sheet close together. Sprinkle with cheese and bake 10 minutes.

title: salsa
directions: Mix in a bowl and refrigerate.
Add more vegetables as desired.

title: 7 layered salad
directions: Layer vegetables and eggs; mix mayo, salt, sugar and garlic powder.
Spread over layered vegetables and eggs; sprinkle cheese, crumbled bacon and croutons on top.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine
all ingredients, except marshmallows. Mix thoroughly and pour in baking dish. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes. Put marshmallows on top and brown.

title: sausage lentil soup
directions: In Dutch oven, brown and crumble sausage.
Drain fat.
Add everything else except mustard.
Cover and simmer 1 hour.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti.
Drain.
In a large bowl, toss spaghetti with oil.
Reserve 1 cup spaghetti for filling.
Toss remaining spaghetti with Parmesan cheese and eggs.
Put in a 10-inch pie plate.
Press into plate to make crust.
Set aside.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Cut bananas to make a layer in bottom of punch bowl.
Put a layer of pudding on top of bananas.
Slice pound cake and arrange slices to make layer.
Add 1 can pie filling to top of cake.
Add a layer of crushed pineapple.
Put one large container of Cool Whip on top of pineapple.
Spread evenly.
Add nuts to garnish.
Repeat layers in same order.
Makes full punch bowl of dessert.

title: apple rolls
directions: Grease 2 one pound coffee cans (or 4 No. 2 cans).
In medium bowl, mix apples, nuts and sugar.
Let stand 1 hour, stirring to let juice appear.
In large bowl, mix flour, soda, salt and spices.
Add apple mixture, butter and vanilla.
Stir in eggs. Fill cans 2/3 full.
Bake in a 325° oven until tester comes out clean.
Place cans on wire rack to cool for 10 to 15 minutes. Turn out onto wire rack to cool.
Serve warm as cake, or cold as a tea bread.

title: lime souffle cheesecake
directions: Spray "Pam" on an 8-inch spring-form pan.
Spread graham crackers on bottom.
In small bowl: dissolve jello in boiling water.
In blender, puree jello, cottage cheese and cream cheese. In a large bowl, fold whipped cream into first mixture.
Put in spring-form pan.
Chill, covered, for 4 hours.
To serve, remove sides of pan; garnish.

title: wisconsin holiday fondue
directions: In a saucepan over medium heat, brown onion and ground beef. Drain.
Add pizza sauce and seasonings; stir until heated.
Add cheese by handfuls.
Stir until smooth.
Pour into a fondue pot (or in a saucepan on a hot plate), keep warm while serving.
Serve with French or Italian bread, cut into pieces or over toasted English muffins.

title: beat beets
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Let sit overnight in refrigerator. Serve cold.
Do not use pickled beets.
Can use 15 ounces Harvard beets.
This is a colorful holiday buffet side dish.

title: skillet pork chops
directions: Saute pork chops in butter or margarine until brown; set aside, reserving the drippings.
Saute the onions in drippings until tender.
Add salt, pepper, cornstarch and mustard.
Stir well.
Add water, bouillon and Worcestershire sauce.
Stir until bouillon is dissolved.
Place pork chops in skillet and simmer 20 to 30 minutes or until done.
Yield:
2 servings.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl and store in gallon container.

title: bodacious broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli flowerets off into bowl.
Add tomatoes; cut mushrooms into fourths.
Add olives.
Add some salt, pepper, vegetable oil to mix and dash of vinegar.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Serve cold.

title: steak marinade
directions: Marinate steak for 15 minutes to 1 hour.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Mix hot water, sugar, salt and margarine. Cool to lukewarm. Put warm water into large bowl and sprinkle or crumble yeast. Stir until dissolved. Stir in lukewarm water mixture, egg and half the flour. Beat until smooth. Stir in enough flour to make a soft dough.

title: cracked sugar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease cookie sheets.
Sift together flour, soda and cream of tartar, set aside.
Beat together butter and sugar until fluffy, about 3 minutes.
Beat in egg yolks and vanilla.
Gradually add flour mixture in 4 parts, beating well after each addition.
Shape into balls, using 1 level tablespoonful for each ball.
Place balls 2 inches apart; do not flatten.
Bake on 350° for 12 minutes or until lightly golden around edges.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and take off bone.
Cook noodles in chicken broth after cooking chicken.
Melt oleo and blend in 3 tablespoons flour.
Gradually stir in milk and cook, stirring until thick. Saute onion and pepper.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and bring to slow boil, mixing frequently.
Let cool to warm.

title: pickled beets
directions: Wash beets, leaving part of stem on top and also on bottom of beets.
Cover with water and boil until tender, 20 to 30 minutes at full boil.
Pour off water and drain.
Cool with cold water.
Peel (skins fall off easily).
Slice beets.
Mix together sugar, vinegar, water, cinnamon sticks and whole cloves.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Then add beets and boil for 5 minutes on high heat, stirring occasionally.
Pack beets in sterile jars.
Pour same syrup over beets to fill jars.
Seal.
Wait about one week before serving.
Yields about 8 pints.

title: skillet potatoes
directions: In skillet, cook onion, celery and garlic in melted margarine until tender.
Add broth, water, potatoes, carrots and thyme. Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover; simmer 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Uncover.
