Over medium heat, simmer 5 minutes or until broth is slightly thickened, stirring often. Sprinkle with chopped parsley before serving.
Makes about 5 cups, 6 servings.
Contains 140 to 150 calories per serving.

title: deviled corn and crab
directions: In saucepan, melt the 1/4 cup butter; stir in flour, mustard, Worcestershire sauce, lemon juice, monosodium glutamate, salt and pepper.
Add milk all at once; cook and stir until mixture thickens and bubbles.
Remove from heat; carefully stir in crab meat, eggs, whole kernel corn and cream-style corn.
Spoon into a 1 1/2-quart casserole; sprinkle cheese over top.
Combine cracker crumbs and the 1 tablespoon melted butter; sprinkle over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until heated through.
Garnish with hard-cooked egg wedges and olive slices.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine sugar, milk, cocoa and butter.
Heat to boiling and boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and peanut butter.
Stir in oats.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: brushetta(grilled bread)
directions: Dice tomatoes.
Mix with basil, salt, garlic salt and crushed peppercorn and let marinate for 30 minutes.
Cut bread into 1/2-inch slices.
Toast bread about 2 inches from broiler until golden brown (about 15 minutes).
Rub toasted slices all over their browned bodies with garlic clove.
Brush the slices with olive oil and top with tomato mixture and return to 350° oven for 5 minutes.

title: cheesy beef macaroni(quick cooking)
directions: In large skillet, cook beef over medium heat until no longer pink; drain. Add the corn and soup. Set aside 1/2 cup cheese for topping. Stir remaining cheese into meat mixture until melted. Gently stir in macaroni until coated. Transfer to a greased 8-inch square baking dish. Top with reserved cheese. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until heated through.

title: ellie's curried chicken
directions: Boil chicken.
Debone and cut up chicken.
Cook broccoli according to directions.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan spread broccoli in bottom.
Top with cooked cut up chicken.
Mix together in a bowl the 3 cans of chicken soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Spread on top of chicken.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese, then cook for 30 minutes in a 400° oven.
Serve over rice.

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix all ingredients very good before serving. This is very delicious.

title: manhattan clam chowder
directions: Combine water, celery, onion, tomato juice, thyme, bay leaf, clam juice, chopped tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Let cook, then add clams and mixed vegetables.
This makes a lot.
Freeze some for later.

title: french dressing
directions: Place all ingredients in a quart jar with a tight lid and shake well.
Chill before serving.
Store in the refrigerator.

title: crab or shrimp dip
directions: Combine, mix, cover and chill.

title: tex mex
directions: Brown hamburger with
taco powder seasoning packet.
Do not add the water and mix with bean dip.

title: sweet and sour beans
directions: Fry bacon until crisp. Remove and set aside.
Saute onion in bacon drippings.
Mix sugar, vinegar, garlic salt, mustard and onions in saucepan and cook until blended.
Pour over beans in a large casserole dish. Add crumbled bacon. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: browned butter glaze
directions: Heat margarine; remove and add powdered sugar and vanilla. Stir in water until smooth.
Dip cookies.
Place on wax paper to cool.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat first 8 ingredients together. Fold in carrots and nuts. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: emerald chicken
directions: On low heat, combine jello, water and pineapple juice in a saucepan.
Add marshmallows and stir until marshmallows dissolve. Cool until it begins to set.
Add pineapple and cottage cheese. Whip the whipping cream and fold into mixture.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch dish and chill.
May be garnished with chopped nuts.

title: salad
directions: Layer lettuce, onion, peas and water chestnuts.
Seal with mayonnaise.
Let set at least 8 hours.
Then add chopped eggs, crumbled bacon bits and grated cheese.
Garnish with tomato wedges.

title: crispy mix
directions: Mix Fritos, Wheat Chex, Cheerios, mixed nuts and pretzels. Melt oleo; mix in the seasonings.
Pour over cereals.
Bake at 200° for 2 hours; stir every 15 minutes.
Add plenty of Accent.

title: icing
directions: Beat together canned milk, sugar, Dream Whip and vanilla until sugar dissolves.
Beat in egg.
Beat in margarine and Crisco. Continue beating until fluffy.
Makes a large amount.
Good for cake decorating.

title: onion hoe cakes
directions: Mix dry ingredients thoroughly.
Add cold milk to make a medium batter.
Drop one tablespoon of batter at a time into hot oil, 1/4-inch deep.
Turn only once as a pancake; drain on a paper towel.

title: walkie toffee bars
directions: Preheat oven at 350°.
Beat butter and brown sugar until fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla.
Mix in flour.
Spread into ungreased baking pan (9 x 13-inch or 15 x 10-inch).
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Let cool.
Chill in refrigerator until chocolate is firm.

title: pecan clusters
directions: Combine sugar, milk and butter in a large saucepan.
Bring mixture to a boil, then cook for 8 minutes.
Pour in kisses and marshmallow cream.
Stir until well blended, until it all melts. Pour in pecans and mix well.
Spoon on waxed paper.

title: creamy pumpkin dip
directions: Beat cream cheese at medium speed with electric mixer until creamy. Gradually add sugar and beat well. Stir in pumpkin, cinnamon and nutmeg. Serve immediately or cover and chill. Serve with gingersnap cookies. Yield: 5 cups.

title: morning coffee
directions: You will need an automatic drip coffeemaker.

title: cranberry ambrosia
directions: Chop cranberries in food processor. Drain, if necessary.

In a large bowl, combine pineapple, marshmallows, cranberries and pecans. Combine sour cream, powdered sugar and Cool Whip. Fold into cranberry mixture. Chill before serving. Will keep up to 5 days in refrigerator.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together except cheese.
Pour half of the batter in greased skillet; sprinkle cheese over the batter.
Pour rest of batter over cheese.
Cook at 375° for 1 hour or until golden brown.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: any time stir-fry
directions: Cut meat into thin, narrow strips.
Combine 1 tablespoon each: cornstarch, soy sauce, sugar and 1 clove garlic.
Stir in meat; let stand 30 minutes.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Combine peanuts, sugar, salt and syrup in bowl.
Stir well. Cook on High 4 minutes.
Stir.
Cook another 4 minutes on High; stir.
Add butter and vanilla and cook for 1 minute on High. Remove and add soda.
Stir.
Immediately pour onto greased cookie sheet; allow to cool.

title: cassia cucumber pickles
directions: Wash and stem cucumbers.
Cut lengthwise in half.
Place water and salt in enameled kettle.
Bring to a boil.
Cool.
Pour over cucumbers in stone crock.
Cover with plate.
Weigh down cucumbers.
Allow to stand 1 week.
Drain.
Cover with boiling water.
Let stand 24 hours.
Drain.
Cover with boiling water. Add alum.
Let stand 24 hours.
Drain.
Cover with syrup made of combined vinegar, sugar, celery seed and cassia oil or cinnamon sticks (tied in bag).
Bring ingredients to a boil.
Pour hot over cucumbers.

title: fudge candy
directions: Mix butter, milk and sugar in saucepan, place over medium heat and stir.
When mixture begins to boil, cool 8 minutes, stirring constantly (I use timer on my stove). Remove from heat. Add chocolate chips and marshmallows.
Whip until dissolved.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into buttered dish.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown the beef and pork.
Add the sauce, sugar and onion.
Put into a greased casserole dish. Pour cheese over the top.
Put biscuits on top of cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: ice cream layer cake
directions: In an 8-inch round cake pan evenly spread slightly softened vanilla ice cream.
Cover with plastic wrap and freeze until firm, about 2 hours.
Repeat in another pan with chocolate ice cream. In a small bowl, combine cookie crumbs and peanut butter.
Set aside.

title: sherbet punch
directions: Just before serving, place sherbet in a punch bowl.
Add remaining ingredients; stir until sherbet is almost dissolved.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix well. Use 2 teaspoons of mixture to 1 cup of boiling water.

title: mary alice's toffee bars
directions: Mix brown sugar, butter and vanilla.
Add flour and thoroughly mix.
Add chocolate chips.
Add nuts, if desired.
Spread in cake pan and bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: high energy granola fruit squares(a favorite of my athlete daughters and all their friends.)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease 9 x9 x2-inch baking dish or pan.
Combine dried fruits and water in small saucepan.
Bring to boil; lower heat and simmer, stirring occasionally until water is absorbed, about 5 minutes.
Let cool.
Stir lemon rind and juice and walnuts into apricot mixture.
Combine flour, soda, salt, oats and brown sugar in large bowl.
Stir in melted butter; mixture will be crumbly.
Reserve 1 cup crumb mixture.
Pat remainder evenly over bottom of prepared pan.
Spoon apricot mixture evenly over crumb base.
Sprinkle with reserved crumb mixture.
Press lightly.
Bake 25 minutes.
Remove to cool on rack.
Wrap in waxed paper or foil pockets.
Refrigerate to make ready to travel or send in college Care packages.

title: chicken dish dinner
directions: Melt margarine and pour into 9 x 12-inch dish.
Sprinkle rice into bottom of dish.
Lay chicken on rice.
Pour soup and water over chicken.
Cover and bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: dilly beans
directions: Wash beans, cut beans into length of pint jars, keep jars hot. In each jar place 1 dill head, 1 clove of garlic and 1 whole pepper.
Pack beans, leaving 1/2 inch headspace.
Heat water, vinegar and salt to boiling.
Pour over beans and leave 1/4 inch headspace.
Put plastic knife down in jars to get air bubbles out. Wipe rims of jars, put hot lids on and tighten.
Put in water bath. Keep water at 185° for 10 minutes.
Use meat thermometer to check temperature of water periodically to make sure temperature stays at 185°.
Makes 7 pints.

title: citrus fish nuggets
directions: Marinate fillets in orange juice for 30 minutes.
Mix citrus pepper with flour to taste.
Roll fillets in flour.
If flour runs out, make more!
Deep fry in oil.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Combine flour and next 4 ingredients; add to egg mixture.
Beat at medium speed with electric mixer 1 to 2 minutes.
Spoon batter into a well-greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Brush cake with glaze.

title: stuffed pork chops
directions: Saute onions and peppers in butter and margarine.
Mix onions and peppers with stuffing, water, butter and salt in small bowl until well blended.
For moist stuffing, add a little more water. Split chops to prepare for stuffing.
Insert stuffing in chops and place them in lightly buttered baking pan.
Bake for 30 minutes covered and 30 minutes more uncovered at 325° or cook on charcoal grill for 1 hour.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Mix together pineapple, flour and eggs.
Place in baking dish. Spread cubed bread over top.
Bake in oven at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: spiced holiday tea
directions: Boil water, cloves, cinnamon sticks and sugar for 10 minutes. Take out cloves.
Add orange juice, lime juice and pineapple juice.

title: noreen's summer squash
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Allow to marinate overnight or several hours. Enjoy!

title: cheddar cheese rolls
directions: Place hot water in a large bowl. Add sugar and salt. Cool to lukewarm.
Sprinkle yeast and sugar over 1/2 cup lukewarm water. Stir.
Cover and let stand until foaming and doubled in volume. Add to cooled water and sugar mixture.
Add egg, 3/4 cup cheese and enough flour to make a firm dough.
Toss onto a lightly floured board.
Knead lightly until smooth and easy to handle. Form into balls.
Arrange on a buttered cookie sheet.
Cover and let rise until tripled in size. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes. Brush with butter. Sprinkle with grated cheese and return to oven until cheese is melted.

title: spiced apple rings
directions: Combine water, sugar and candies in a large kettle.
Bring mixture to a boil.
Simmer until candies are dissolved.
Reserve; add food coloring, if desired.
Drop apples into slightly salted water; drain.
Add apples to syrup and simmer apples until slightly tender.
Pack mixture into sterilized jars.
Cover with syrup and seal.

title: cherry cheese cake
directions: Mix graham crackers, sugar and margarine.
Press in pie pan. Bake 5 to 8 minutes.
Beat jello with cold milk (5 minutes).
Add cream cheese, softened.
Blend.
Pour in cool crust and top with cherry pie filling.
Cool in refrigerator for 4 to 6 hours.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Depending on size of cabbage head, use 1/2 to whole cabbage. Mix all ingredients until well moistened.

title: pot roast
directions: Heat oil until hot in a 6 to 10-quart Dutch oven. Brown roast on all sides until nicely browned. Brown onions in oil; leave onions in pan. Pepper all sides of roast until evenly covered. Put water in pan until it raises halfway up the roast. Add beef bouillon (number of cubes/number of cups of water). Let come to a boil, then reduce heat. Cover and let simmer. Cook 4 to 5 hours. It is done when you try to lift the roast from the pan and it falls apart.

title: pot roast
directions: Sprinkle roast with salt, pepper, lemon pepper and garlic salt.
Can also add Worcestershire sauce.
Let set in pan 1/2 hour prior to cooking.

title: crabmeat mold and spread
directions: In saucepan, combine soup, cheese and onion.
Heat until cheese is melted.
Stir.
Blend in mayonnaise and remove from heat.
In small pan, sprinkle gelatin over water on low heat until dissolved.
Stir into soup mixture and add celery and crab meat. Pour into a 6-cup mold and refrigerate at least 6 hours.
Unmold on plate and serve with crackers.

title: taco salad
directions: Dice tomatoes and onion.
Chop lettuce, then mix all ingredients.
Serve immediately or chill.
Quantities of ingredients can be changed according to individual taste.

title: one gallon of ice cream
directions: Mix together, then pour in freezer bucket.
Fill with whole milk.
Add peaches, bananas, etc.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix sausage, Bisquick, Cheez Whiz and milk together.
Roll into balls.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: apple crunch
directions: Spread sliced apples in buttered baking dish.
Cover with sugar; sprinkle with cinnamon.
Mix flour and brown sugar; cut in butter until it resembles coarse cornmeal.
Cover apples with mixture.
Bake for 30 minutes at 325°.

title: barbecued deer
directions: Place deer meat into crock-pot.
Mix together remaining ingredients in a small bowl.
Pour over deer meat.
Cook on low for 12 hours or on high for 6 hours.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Blend slowly the first 5 ingredients, then blend well.
Pour into greased tube pan.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.
Cool 10 minutes, then place on cake plate.
Prick large holes with meat fork deep in cake.
Saturate cake in mixture of the apricot nectar and sugar that have been mixed well together.
Let refrigerate 2 days.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Melt margarine, add eggs and stir.
Add remaining ingredients, except chips and pecans.
Line unbaked pie shell with chips and pecans.
Pour mixture over chips and pecans.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Cream oil and sugar and add eggs one at a time alternately with the ingredients sifted together (flour, salt, soda, cinnamon and nutmeg).
Add mixture of diced apples, nuts and vanilla.
Bake in tube pan or oblong pan at 350° for 1 hour.
Grease and flour pan.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Melt margarine and cool. Add remaining ingredients; pour into pie shell. Bake 40 minutes.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift flour with salt.
Add flour alternately with milk to creamed mixture, beating after each addition.
Add coconut, lemon and vanilla flavorings.
Pour into a greased and floured pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until cake is done.
Cool 10 minutes then remove.

title: oven fried potatoes
directions: Arrange potatoes, peel side down in baking dish.
Mix ingredients together.
Brush on potatoes.
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes or until done.

title: beef and cheese pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Stir in barbecue sauce.
Lay one pie crust on bottom of ungreased pizza pan.
Top with ground beef mixture.
Lay sliced cheese over this. Top with ground beef mixture.
Lay sliced cheese over this.
Top with pie crust.
Seal edges and sprinkle with sesame seed.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until brown.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: kentucky butter cake
directions: Sift together the first 4 ingredients.
In separate large bowl, cream the butter.
Gradually add the sugar, creaming well. Blend in the unbeaten eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
In a third bowl, combine the buttermilk and vanilla extract.
Add third bowl ingredients and first bowl ingredients alternately to cream mixture, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Turn into 10-inch tube pan, greased and floured. Bake at 325° for 60 to 65 minutes, until cake springs back when touched in center.

title: cranberry pudding
directions: Grease an 8-inch pie plate.
Spread cut berries in it and sprinkle 1/2 cup of sugar over them.
Beat egg.
Add 1/2 cup of sugar; mix thoroughly with flour, melted butter and oil.
Beat well.
Fold in nuts.
Pour this batter over berries.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: peanut butter kisses
directions: Mix together honey and peanut butter.
Gradually stir in nonfat dry milk.
Mix well.
Roll into a log and slice.
Great snacks for children.

title: honey vinaigrette salad dressing
directions: In a bowl whisk together the vinegar, the honey to taste, the Worcestershire sauce, the garlic paste, the mustard, salt and pepper. Add the oil in a stream, whisking and whisk the dressing until emulsified.
Add the lettuce, spinach, tomatoes, mushrooms and toss the salad well.

title: peppers - side dish
directions: Clean peppers (take out seeds), then cut into chunks.
Heat oil and saute peppers until tender.
Don't overcook.
Serve while hot.

title: chocolate truffle squares
directions: Line square pan (8 x 8-inch) with heavy-duty foil.
In small microwaveproof bowl, combine vanilla milk chips and shortening. Microwave at High for 1 minute or just until chips are melted and smooth when stirred.
Pour about half of vanilla mixture into prepared pan.
Set aside remaining vanilla mixture.

title: cheesecake
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and put into spring-form pan. Whip cream cheese.
Add each item, one at a time.
Beat until smooth.
Add to pan.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes, until it tests done, at 300°.
Top with fruit if desired.

title: no bake fruitcake
directions: Mix all and press into an angel food pan to form and chill.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: *Can use carrots, green onions, broccoli, cauliflower, red and green bell pepper, olives, squash, tomatoes, etc.

title: double chocolate drops
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a large bowl, measure all ingredients except frosting.
With mixer at low speed, beat just until blended, scraping bowl constantly with rubber spatula. Increase speed to medium and beat 3 more minutes.
Drop batter by heaping teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheets.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes. When cool, top with frosting.
Decorate with colored sugars, if desired.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil. Yields 1 1/4 cups.
Brush on any meat near end of cooking in broiler or barbecue.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown 4 pork chops on both sides.
Spray casserole with Pam. Slice potatoes in casserole.
Pour 1/2 can cream of mushroom soup on potatoes.
Place pork chops on potatoes.
Slice onion on top of chops.
Pour rest of soup on top of onions.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: fat-free brownie cake
directions: Spray pan with cooking spray; set aside.
In a large bowl, mix flour, sugar, cocoa, cornstarch, baking soda and salt.
In another bowl, using a fork, mix egg whites, water, corn syrup and vanilla. Add to flour mixture.
Pour into pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool.

title: chicken divan
directions: Butter baking dish.
Drain broccoli well (may need to precook).
Make a sauce with the soups, mayonnaise, lemon juice, curry powder and shredded cheese.
Lay broccoli on bottom of dish. Lay partly cooked chicken on top and pour sauce over.
Top with bread crumbs, if desired.

title: date bars
directions: Mix oatmeal, margarine, soda, flour and brown sugar and divide into 2 parts.
Spread 1/2 on bottom of 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Cook dates, white sugar and water to make filling and place on top of bottom layer.
Spread remainder of crumble crust on top.
Bake for about 20 minutes at 350°.

title: pot pie dough
directions: Mix flour and shortening well.
Add beaten egg and milk.
Mix well and roll out.
Cut into squares and drop into boiling broth. After all dough is added to broth, reduce heat and cook for 10 to 15 minutes, occasionally stirring so as not to stick to bottom of cooking pan.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Salt and pepper the ground meats. Brown the pork ground meat, then the beef. Add onion, bell pepper and celery. Cook until vegetables are tender. Add mustard, Worcestershire sauce, liquid smoke, tomato sauce, barbecue sauce, ketchup and garlic powder. Simmer with 1/2 cup of water for 1/2 hour. Add beans and simmer 10 minutes more.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Bake in greased single loaf pans at 325° for 1 1/2 hours. Makes 2 loaves.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each one.
Add hot water.
Sift soda with flour.
Alternate flour and buttermilk when adding to the cream mixture.
Add vanilla.
Bake for 2 hours at 300°.

title: quick and easy creamed corn
directions: Put frozen corn in blender with 1/4 cup water and chop.
Put chopped corn in pan and add the butter, milk, salt and pepper. Cook on low, stirring regularly to keep it from sticking.
Cook between 45 to 60 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and onions; drain.
Place in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Melt butter, blend in flour, add milk and cook until it thickens; reduce heat.
Add cream cheese and 3/4 of Cheddar cheese.
Pour sauce over broccoli and mix.
Top with remaining cheese.
Cut bread into large cubes, dip in melted butter.
Place on top of casserole.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: bean salad
directions: Mix together in bowl; set aside.

title: green enchiladas
directions: Brown and drain ground meat.
Put back in skillet and soften onion and meat; add Cheddar cheese.
Cook into meat and heat until cheese melts into meat.
Heat tortillas in microwave until soft. Place soups and green chilies in double boiler and heat with milk and 1 pound Velveeta cheese.
Pour over tortillas.
Cook 20 minutes at 400°.

title: cabbage with a flair
directions: Saute bacon, green peppers, onion and celery.
Add tomatoes, cabbage, salt, pepper, garlic salt and enough water to cover. Simmer until cabbage is done.

title: sweet and pungent shrimp
directions: Clean and cook shrimp.
Drain syrup from pineapple into a saucepan.
Cut pineapple slices in half and reserve.
Add brown sugar, vinegar, soy sauce and 1 cup water to pineapple syrup. Bring to boil.
Combine cornstarch and 1/4 cup water.
Add to sugar mixture.
Cook stirring constantly until thickened.
Add green pepper, pineapple and tomato wedges.
Cook 2 minutes.
Add shrimp and cook to heat shrimp through.
Serve immediately.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown hamburger and onion. In large pot, combine browned burger and onion with remaining ingredients. Cook 2 hours on medium to medium-low heat. Serve over Fritos corn chips and top with shredded cheese, sour cream, olives, tomatoes and lettuce.

title: cream filling
directions: Beat all ingredients together over moderate to high heat until the mixture thickens and comes to a boil.
Continue beating over low heat for 2 minutes until mixture looks translucent.
This cream filling can be used as a cake frosting, dessert crepe filling or sweet spread for scones and biscuits.

title: fancy fruit salad
directions: Mix all together and serve.

title: jambalaya
directions: Cut all sausage across the link into 1/4 inch slices.
Brown sausage in a large skillet.
When sausage is done, remove from skillet, saving the grease.

title: banana flip - beverage
directions: Peel the bananas. Cut into small pieces. Place bananas and milk in blender. Blend for 30 seconds.
Add the cottage cheese and sugar.
Blend for a further 30 seconds.
Pour into chilled glasses and sprinkle with cinnamon. Serve immediately. Serves 4.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Put the chocolate chips on the dough.
Turn on the oven.
Put the whole pile on the cookie sheet and put in a very hot oven. Cook about 40 minutes.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread layer of sauce in bottom of pan.
Layer remaining ingredients in order given, as many layers as desired.
Use all the sauce.
Pour 1 cup water over all.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove foil and bake another 15 minutes.
Serve with hot French garlic bread.

title: onion topped beef bake
directions: Peel and thinly slice the onions into rings.
Saute in vegetable oil until just tender.
Set aside.
Brown ground beef (hamburger); drain.
Blend in salt and pepper.
Add green pepper and brown about 3 minutes longer.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Chill the cooked vegetables.
(If in a hurry can use drained, canned mixed vegetables or leftover vegetables.) Combine the chilled cooked vegetables and celery and onions; add seasonings and lemon juice.
Mix gently with 2 spoons or salad tossers.
Add just enough mayonnaise to mix well with all ingredients.
Place on romaine or lettuce leaves; garnish with egg and beet slices and lots of parsley.
Serve chilled.
Good with any meat, fowl or fish for lunch or dinner.
(An oil and vinegar dressing can be substituted for lemon juice.)

title: heath bars
directions: Line cookie sheet with foil (edges turned up).
Coat lightly with oil.
Line pan with saltine crackers.

title: venison in beer
directions: Salt and pepper the roast. Secure bacon around the meat with toothpicks and place in crock-pot. Dissolve bouillon cubes in boiling water. Add onion, bay leaves, bouillon and beer to the crock-pot. Cook for 4 to 5 hours.

title: nanny's doole cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into oiled pan.
Cook 30 minutes at 350°.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Mix eggs, milk, salt and dry mustard. Grease pan. Spread bread on bottom, sausage mixture on top and top with cheese. Chill overnight.
Bake at 350° for 35 or 40 minutes, uncovered.

title: onion casserole
directions: In buttered casserole place alternate layers of thinly sliced onions, crushed potato chips and grated cheese.
Pour soup and milk over the top.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Beat egg.
Blend in mayonnaise and soup.
Stir in cooked, drained broccoli and onion and put into baking dish.
Sprinkle with the bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: cream potatoes and green beans
directions: Cut up and boil potatoes and onions together, about 20 minutes.
After it comes to a boil add oleo, milk and green beans. Let it come to a near boil and add thickening; stir until thickens.

title: shipwreck stew
directions: *Can add tomato soup instead of tomatoes.

title: hot dog and potato bake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease a 2-quart casserole.
Place potato slices into casserole.
Sprinkle envelope of seasoning mix over potatoes.
Stir in water, milk, butter and onions.
Stir in frankfurters until well combined.
Cover and bake 30 minutes, uncovered, and bake 30 minutes longer or until golden brown and potatoes are fork-tender.

title: monkey bread
directions: You will need a Bundt pan.

title: blueberry buckle
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Bake 45 minutes.
Cream 1/4 cup[ of the butter and 1/2 cup of the sugar.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Sift 1 cup flour with baking powder and salt.
Add alternately with milk, flour mixture and creamed mixture.
Pour in a greased 9-inch square pan.
Combine remaining sugar, flour and nutmeg.
Sprinkle on top.

title: blonde brownies *
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla in bowl; add nuts.
Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt in same bowl.
Batter will be stiff.
Grease pan or Pyrex dish and spread batter into it, then place package of chips on top of batter and press them in the batter a little.
Bake in oven at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: microwave toasted butter pecans
directions: Put pecan halves into a 1-quart measuring cup.
Sprinkle with salt.
Cut oleo into 4 pieces and place over top of pecans.
Put in microwave and cook for 8 to 10 minutes on High.
Mix evenly to distribute oleo.
Drain on paper towels.
Yields 1 pound.

title: baked cranberry salad
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: special k bars
directions: Bring syrup and sugar to a slow boil and boil for 1 minute. Add peanut butter.
Stir in Special K and pat into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chocolate bits and butterscotch bits together and then spread over top of all.

title: crunchy cereal cookies
directions: Sift together first 4 ingredients.
Cream butter and sugars. Add egg and vanilla to creamed mixture.
Mix thoroughly.
Blend in dry ingredients plus cereals and coconut.
Shape dough by rounded teaspoonful into a ball.
Place on a greased baking sheet and flatten slightly.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes, until golden brown.

title: pistachio inside-outside cake
directions: Blend all cake ingredients together in large bowl.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Bake in greased and floured Bundt pan at 350° for 50 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes, remove from pan and cool on rack.
Cut cake into three layers.
Spread 1 cup of frosting between each layer and spoon rest on top of cake.
Garnish with chopped nuts.

title: salmon barbecue
directions: Melt butter and mix with lemon juice and oregano.
Brush mixture over salmon fillets.
Lightly salt and pepper fillets. Let salmon stand at room temperature for 1 hour.
Place fillets, skin side down, on a piece of aluminum foil.
Fold up sides of foil to form a side about 1/2-inch high.
Place foil on barbecue over wood or charcoal embers.
Cover salmon with grill lid or piece of foil.
Every 5 to 10 minutes, baste fish with sauce. Cooking time should be 25 to 30 minutes.
Fish is done when it flakes with fork.

title: chicken adobo (merlyn's style)(philippine cuisine)
directions: Saute garlic and onion in cooking oil; brown chicken parts. Add all other ingredients.
Cook until done or until juice reduced into sauce-like consistency, stirring occasionally.
Serve with steamed rice.

title: aunt gladys' chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and Quik.
Add milk and egg yolks.
Mix well. Cook on medium heat, stirring constantly, until thick.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into baked 9-inch pie crust.
Beat whites until stiff.
Add 1/2 cup sugar and 1/4 teaspoon cream of tartar. Beat until stiff peaks form.
Put on pie and cook for 15 minutes at 350° or until brown as desired.

title: mocha punch
directions: Mix together chocolate syrup, instant coffee, sugar and water in top of double boiler.
Place over low heat and cook, stirring constantly until well blended.
Remove from heat; stir in milk; chill.
Pour into punch bowl.
Spoon in ice cream; stir until partially melted.
Just before serving, pour in carbonated water. Spoon whipped cream or Cool Whip over the top.
Yields about 36 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: party punch
directions: For a different taste, add vodka to it.

title: cheese and potato casserole
directions: Pour into well-greased crock-pot.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and cook on low 7 to 9 hours (less) or on high 3 hours.
Sprinkle remaining onion rings over top before serving. Makes a large amount; can be cut in half.

title: butter cookies
directions: In mixing bowl, cream together oleo and cream cheese until fluffy; set aside.
Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Gradually blend into creamed mixture.
Add eggs, mixing to form stiff dough.
Chill at least 2 hours.
When dough is chilled, roll and cut into size big and thick enough for thumbprint.
Fill thumbprint with preserves.
Bake in 375° oven for about 15 minutes or until browned.

title: bacon-chestnut hors d'oeuvres
directions: Wrap chestnuts in bacon. Secure bacon with toothpick. Mix together ketchup and sugar. Cover chestnuts with mixture. Bake 375° for 40 minutes.

title: chili rellenos
directions: Wash chilies, remove seeds and pat dry.
Layer half the chilies, then half the cheese in pan.
Repeat this step.
Beat eggs, add flour, salt and can of milk.
Beat well and pour over top of cheese.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Watch baking time carefully toward end as ovens vary.

title: oven barbecue beef
directions: Place roast in large roasting pan.
Combine the remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour over roast.
Cover with top to the roaster or heavy-duty aluminum foil.
Bake at 300° for 6 to 7 hours.
Cool.
Slice very thin or shred in food processor for sandwiches.

title: "old fashioned" candy
directions: Combine ingredients.
Mixture should be consistency of hard dough and easy to handle.
Shape into pieces the size of a walnut, then lengthen the dough into the shape of an Idaho potato.
Roll in cinnamon.

title: hawaiian teriyaki steak
directions: Cut steak in pieces.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over steak.
Let stand overnight covered and refrigerated.
Fry in skillet, dipping meat into marinade when turning.

title: broccoli and rice
directions: Saute onion and celery in oil until done.
Meanwhile, cook rice and broccoli separately until done.
Drain broccoli.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes, or until hot throughout.
This is also good with cooked chicken added.

title: roast chicken
directions: Place chicken in crock-pot.
Mix soup and milk together and bouillon
cube.
Pour over chicken.
Roast on low all day or
all night.
Boil
rice
as
directed and spoon sauce over rice.

title: scalloped scallops
directions: Wash and drain the scallops and season with salt.
Toss the crackers with the melted butter.
In a greased 8 inch square baking dish, arrange alternate layers of crackers and scallops, beginning and ending with the crackers.
Pour the light cream over the top.
Sprinkle with pepper and paprika.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: black-eyed pea dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Drain peas and discard juices.

Mash peas with a fork, leaving some chunks. Do not use blender. Add remaining ingredients to the peas and mix well. Spread in a baking dish and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until the dip bubbles.
Serve warm with tortilla chips.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: peanut butter kiss cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat first 4 ingredients with an electric mixer until creamy.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
In another bowl, combine flour, soda, and salt; gradually add to peanut butter mixture, beating well.
Place 1/4 cup sugar into a small bowl. Shape dough into 1 inch balls, and roll in sugar to coat.
Place on greased cookie sheets.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven, and quickly press a Kiss into each cookie.
Bake 3 to 5 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool on wire racks.

title: chili cheese nacho dip
directions: Put Hormel chili, green and red chili, chopped chilies and Velveeta cheese in crock-pot and cook on low for 2 hours or cook slowly on stove.
Mix cream cheese with 1/2 cup chopped green chilies; spread over flour tortillas.
Roll and slice at an angle into bite size pieces.
Serve with corn chips.
Fabulous served over burritos.

title: velveeta jalapeno cheese roll
directions: Roll out Velveeta cheese between 2 sheets of wax paper.
Do the same with cream cheese.
Put cream cheese on top of Velveeta cheese.
Mix rest of ingredients out on cream cheese and roll up like a jelly roll.
Sprinkle with seasoned salt.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream the first ingredients together. Add eggs one at a time, mixing well after each one. Add cake flour and mix well. Put into a 10-inch greased angel food pan. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: spinach dish
directions: Potatoes should be cooked but remain firm.
Drain and set aside.

title: milk chocolate and peanut butter bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl mix peanut butter and butter; beat until smooth.
Add sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Blend in flour and salt.
Stir in one cup morsels. Spread in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes until it begins to brown.

title: hawaiian cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese; mix in next 5 ingredients, then chill at least 3 hours.
Roll cheese mixture into a ball, then roll in chopped nuts.
Serve with an array of crackers.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: party punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in warm water.
Add pineapple juice, orange juice, lemonade and bananas.
Stir together and freeze in quart containers.
When ready to use, take punch out of freezer.
Add 1 quart frozen punch to 1 quart of lemon-lime soda.
Makes 5 quarts of punch or 51 (5 ounce) cups.

title: dave's favorite dessert
directions: Crush chocolate wafers until very fine.
Mix with 2 tablespoons oleo (room temperature).
Reserve 1/3 cup for topping and press the remaining crumbs into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 5 to 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Combine in shallow baking dish.
Top with 1 cup brown sugar and 1 cup nuts with 1/2 cup flour (1/2 this topping is enough). Slice 1 stick oleo and put on top and brown in oven at 350°.

title: chilled chive and zucchini soup
directions: Combine zucchini, broth, milk, oats, carrots and salt in blender.
Blend until smooth, about 15 seconds.
Combine zucchini mixture, yogurt and chives in large bowl; mix well.
Cover and chill several hours.
Sprinkle with additional chopped chives to serve, if desired.
Additional milk may be added if soup becomes too thick upon standing.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: festive mixin's
directions: Heat oven to 250°.
Blend butter and seasonings.
Mix Kix, Cheerios, cheese crackers, pretzels and nuts in 13 x 9 1/2 x 2-inch pan.
Pour butter and seasonings over and stir.
Bake 1 hour, stirring carefully with wooden spoon every 15 minutes. Makes 6 cups.

title: egg nog
directions: Pre chill ingredients.
Blend in punch bowl by beating with wire whisk.
Dust with nutmeg.
Add ice and serve.

title: grape salad
directions: Mix sour cream and brown sugar until well blended.
Add grapes and pecans.
Let stand in refrigerator for at least 1 hour before serving.

title: pork-n-gravy
directions: Brown meat after rolling in flour.
Place in crock-pot.
Pour on soup.
Cook on low for several hours, until meat is tender and done.

title: chicken bits
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut chicken breasts into 1-inch triangles.
In medium mixing bowl, stir together Italian dressing, garlic powder and onion powder.
Stir in chicken triangles until all pieces are coated with dressing mixture.

In large mixing bowl, stir together Parmesan cheese, pecans and crushed crackers. Pour off any liquid from chicken pieces, then carefully stir chicken pieces into cracker mixture until each piece is coated. Cover large baking sheet with foil, then spray with nonstick spray.
Spread coated chicken pieces onto foil, keeping pieces from touching each other.
Bake in preheated oven for 20 minutes. Remove from foil.
Put a toothpick in each chicken bite to serve. Serve with your favorite dipping sauce.
Makes 8 servings.

title: sausage bread
directions: Combine warm water, yeast and sugar.
Cover and set aside. Combine flour and salt and cut in shortening.
Add yeast mixture. Knead about 5 minutes.
Let rise about 2 hours or until double in size.
Punch down and divide into thirds.
Roll each piece out until 1/4 inch thick.
You can refrigerate extra dough.
Cook 1 pound sausage or ham sausage per loaf.
Drain well.
Cover dough with sausage and cheese if desired.
Roll up into loaf and wet edges to seal.
This is important.
Let rise again.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
This freezes well.

title: mulled cider
directions: In a 6-quart saucepan or wok, combine all ingredients.
Heat over low heat or low setting at 200° for 10 minutes or until hot. Do not boil.
Add 1 thinly sliced navel orange and 1 cup apple brandy.
Serve hot in glass punch cups.

title: sour cream apple pie
directions: In large bowl beat eggs, add sour cream.
Stir in sugar, 2 tablespoons flour, vanilla and salt; mix well.
Stir in apples. Pour in pie shell.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 15 minutes.
Meanwhile combine butter, brown sugar and remaining flour.
Sprinkle on top. Bake 20 to 25 minutes more.

title: rj's sweet potato casserole
directions: Boil sweet potatoes for 20 minutes.
Drain.

In an ungreased baking dish layer sweet potatoes; then place apples over potatoes. Pour apple juice over apples; bake at 350° for 25 minutes uncovered.	Take the casserole out of the oven and mash the mixture with potato masher to desired consistency.	Stir in cinnamon and dot with butter slices.
Cover and bake an additional 15 minutes.

title: airways sponge cake
directions: Beat
egg yolks until thick and lemon colored.	Beat in sugar gradually.	Sift flour and salt together and add alternately
with water
to	first mixture;	add lemon extract and rind.
Beat
egg whites
until
foamy;
add baking powder and continue beating until they hold a point.
Fold into egg yolk mixture.
Pour into an ungreased aluminum angel food cake pan. Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: honey crumb muffins
directions: In a mixing bowl, sift together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix in corn flake crumbs.
In a separate bowl, combine egg, milk and honey.
Add egg mixture to dry ingredients.
Add shortening and stir only until combined.
Fill greased muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake at 425° for about 20 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen muffins.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Put whipped topping into a bowl.
Sprinkle pudding mix over top and add all other ingredients.
Mix well.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: jalapeno corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a greased pan.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: frozen fruit cups
directions: Combine all ingredients; do not drain fruits.
Spoon into 3 1/2-ounce paper or plastic cups.
Insert wooden sticks, if desired.
Freeze until solid.

title: no-cook banana pudding
directions: Beat pudding mix and milk until slightly thickened.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread half the mixture in bottom of a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Sprinkle with crushed vanilla wafers.
Slice bananas and put on top of wafers (as many as you want).
Cover with remaining pudding mix.
Chill before serving.

title: blueberry dessert
directions: Mix together vanilla wafers, butter and powdered sugar; pat into
bottom of a 9 x 13-inch buttered glass dish or pan. Blend together eggs, sugar and cream cheese; spread on top of crumb mixture.
Bake
at
350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.
Spread pie filling on top of cream cheese mixture.
Top with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Saute onion, garlic, green and red pepper and celery until glazed appearance; add parsley, red pepper sauce and Worcestershire and soy sauce.
Cook over medium heat; add tomatoes and shrimp and cook until pink.
Add frozen veggies and snow peas last and cook over medium heat for about 10 minutes.
Add cornstarch to thicken with the cold water.
Cover and steam for about 7 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: four layer dessert
directions: Beat and pour over.
Spread remaining Cool Whip mixture over top.
Sprinkle with flaked almonds.
Chill.

title: microwave carmel corn
directions: Combine sugars, margarine, syrup and salt in a 2-quart cup. Microwave on High 2 minutes; stir.
Microwave again 2 minutes.
Be careful.
Add baking soda.
Stir well with a wooden spoon. Immediately pour syrup over popcorn in bag.
(When you are pouring syrup over corn, put the popcorn in a brown bag.)
Fold the bag down 2 or 3 times.
Microwave on High 1 minute; remove and shake bag.
Microwave for 1 minute; remove and shake bag.
Microwave 1 minute; pour onto wax paper.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: Take 1 piece thin sliced ham, cut into 4 strips and set aside. Combine together cream cheese and Cheddar cheese until soft and creamy.
With a butter knife, take each strip of ham and spread cheese mixture on it.
Roll each strip of ham up and put a toothpick in to hold it together.

title: apple brownies
directions: Mix together apples and nuts with 1/2 cup sugar.
Set aside. Mix together remaining ingredients.
Fold in apple and nut mixture.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan (or one a little smaller). Bake 40 minutes.
Cool before cutting.

title: cracker snack
directions: Mix dill weed, Ranch dressing and oil.
Pour over crackers. Mix thoroughly.
Bake at 250° for 15 minutes.

title: curry stew beef
directions: Fry onion until transparent in margarine or butter.
Add meat and brown well.
Add all other ingredients.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Bring sugar and water to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer until syrupy, about 8 minutes.
Cool.
Combine other ingredients in large bowl.
Stir in cool syrup.
Spoon into 18 foil-lined muffin cups and freeze until firm, about 4 hours.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: sticky chicken
directions: Arrange wings in baking pan.
Mix
all other ingredients and pour over chicken.	Bake two hours at 325° or until sticky.

title: granola bites
directions: Combine cornflakes, oats, bran cereal and dates in large bowl.
Mix peanut butter, egg whites, Equal and vanilla in small bowl until smooth; pour over cereal mixture and stir until all ingredients are coated.
Shape mixture into 1-inch mounds; place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated 350° oven until cookies are set and browned, 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool on wire racks.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: imelda's banana bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Cream sugar, margarine and egg.
Beat well.
Stir in banana, cereal and vanilla.
Add nuts and wheat germ.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes in a well-greased metal loaf pan or for 60 minutes at 325° in glass loaf pan.

title: brown rice
directions: Mix all ingredients, except butter.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.
Last 15 minutes, add butter.

title: the best meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together; pour into loaf pan or casserole dish.

title: spinach dip
directions: Combine ingredients.
Place in center of cleaned out round of French bread.
Serve with French bread or Ritz crackers.

title: zucchini bake
directions: Mix in a large bowl.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan or casserole and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: rocky road halloween squares
directions: In double boiler, melt morsels with milk and butter.
Remove from heat. In large bowl, combine nuts and marshmallows. Fold in chocolate mixture. Spread in wax paper lined 13 x 9-inch pan. Chill 2 hours or until firm.
Remove from pan; peel off wax paper. Cut into 40 squares.
Cover and store at room temperature.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, toss hot spaghetti with olive oil.
In a small bowl, combine eggs and 1/2 cup grated Parmesan.
Stir in spaghetti.
Pour spaghetti mixture into a lightly greased 10-inch pie plate and form into a crust.
Spread Ricotta evenly over the crust, not quite to the edge, and top with spaghetti sauce.
Bake uncovered for 25 minutes.
Top with Mozzarella and bake for 5 more minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with remaining Parmesan.
Cool 10 minutes before cutting.

title: crazy cake
directions: Layer as listed.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes, or until golden brown.
Delicious when served with vanilla ice cream.

title: eggplant fritters
directions: Mix eggs and milk with eggplant.
Gradually add dry ingredients which have been sifted together.
Add onion and seasonings.
Mix well and add by teaspoons to hot oil.
Fry until golden and well done.

title: cracker salad
directions: Finely chop onion, bell pepper, pimento and pickles.
Add to chopped eggs.
Toss gently.
Serve on a bed of lettuce.

title: cuban rice and mushrooms
directions: Combine all ingredients and place in casserole dish (9 x 13-inch) and bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: chili dip
directions: Brown beef with the first 4 ingredients.
Add chili powder and soup.
Mix.
Add Velveeta cheese.
Stir until cheese melts.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: May use white wine vinegar or champagne vinegar.

title: shortbread
directions: Mix well and press in an ungreased pan.
Bake 5 minutes at 350°.
Turn oven down to 325° and bake 15 to 20 more minutes.

title: health salad
directions: In a large bowl, toss together cabbage, carrots, green pepper and onion.
Mix vinegar, corn oil, sugar, celery seed and garlic salt.
Pour over vegetables; toss to coat.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Makes 7 cups.

title: tiger butter
directions: Fill a seamless ring mold halfway with water.
Freeze, then arrange fruits on top of ice (peach slices, grapes or berries). Pour more water into mold, not covering fruit completely.
Freeze again, then unmold and float in punch.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix well.
Drop by tablespoon into hot grease.
Be sure grease is deep enough so that hush puppies will float and can be easily turned.

title: russian tea
directions: Dissolve sugar in hot tea and put in cloves tied in cheesecloth.
Add fruit juices and salt.
Keep piping hot but do not boil.
Take spices out after about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: delicious model clay
directions: Mix together thoroughly.
Let children mold it into small figures or roll into balls; any kind of shape they like.
Roll in chocolate sprinkles, powdered sugar or any kind of colored party sprinkles.
The children can make it and eat it, too.
Kids love it.

title: orange chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Add boneless chicken breasts.
Coat well.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour; baste frequently.

title: cheese blitzes
directions: Mix ingredients (1 minute, scrape sides; mix 30 seconds more) and store in closed container in refrigerator overnight.
The next morning, it is ready to be cooked.
Shake well or stir well.
Cook 1/4 cup liquid in small frying pan on medium heat for 1 minute or until lightly brown.
Place on wax paper.

title: creamed sweet potatoes with caramel sauce
directions: Wash and boil sweet potatoes in jackets until tender. Peel and rinse. Season with remaining ingredients and whip until fluffy.

title: down south wilted lettuce
directions: Wash the lettuce and thoroughly pat dry (I use terry cloth towels).
In a large salad bowl, tear lettuce into bite size pieces.
Clean onions, leaving about 1/3 to 1/2 of upper greens. Chop into small pieces and sprinkle over lettuce.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Press dough onto cookie sheet and bake at 400° for about 20-25 minutes. Cool completely.
Mix the next 5 ingredients and spread onto crust. Top with a mixture of chopped vegetables. Press gently. Refrigerate until serving time. Pizza cutter works well to cut into bars.
(May also add shredded Cheddar cheese to top of pizza.)

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Sift together dry ingredients into mixing bowl.
Blend lard in with pastry blender until mixture is the consistency of coarse cornmeal.
Add all buttermilk and stir with fork to form a soft dough but not sticky.

title: orange creamcicle cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°, grease and flour 2 - 9 inch cake pans. Mix cake mix oil, jello, eggs, milk and one tsp. orange extract. Pour into cake pans and bake for 25 minutes.
Let cool and split each cake in half, making four cakes.
Mix sour cream, sugar, sunny delight and one tsp. orange extract in a bowl on medium until well blended.
Fold in cool whip and spread between layers and on top and sides.
May have to refrigerate to firm before spreading on cake.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients. Add Cool Whip. Mix well. Pour in graham cracker crust. Refrigerate.

title: oreo cookie dessert(dirt pudding)
directions: Mix powdered sugar and softened cream cheese.
Mix pudding as directed on package.
Combine and add Cool Whip.
Layer with Oreo cookies.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil chicken; remove bones, then mix soups and Ro-Tel with chicken.
Top with crushed corn chips and grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes in casserole dish.

title: chicken corn soup
directions: Cook chicken slowly until tender.
Add salt 30 minutes before it is done.
Remove chicken and strain broth.
Take meat from bones and chop fine.
Add to broth.
Add corn (cut from cob) celery and seasoning.
Add noodles 10 minutes before done and cook until noodles are tender.

title: sugar cookies(over 100 years old)
directions: Roll into balls and press with a floured bottom glass. Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar of glaze.
Bake in oven at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: spankopita(spinach pie)
directions: Mix Ricotta, Feta, eggs, pepper and parsley with chopped spinach.
(Use hands to mix thoroughly.)
Cut fillo dough size of pan if needed.
Cover fillo dough when not being used to prevent drying out.
Butter pan and place one layer of fillo on bottom of pan; brush with butter.
Repeat until 8 to 10 layers have been used, brushing each with butter.
Add 1/2 of spinach-cheese filling and cover with one layer fillo.
Brush with butter and repeat until 7 to 8 layers of fillo are used.
Add remaining spinach-cheese filling and cover with one layer fillo.
Repeat layering process until 8 to 10 layers have been used.
Butter top sheet.
With sharp knife, cut through top layers of fillo only, in square or diamond-shaped pieces.
Sprinkle with a little water (to prevent cut edges from curling up) and bake in 350° oven for about an hour or until golden brown.
Cut pieces through when ready to serve.

title: chicken crescent rolls
directions: Mix all together.
Put 1/2 cup of mixture in crescent roll square (2 pinched together).
Sprinkle seasoned bread crumbs on chicken.
Fold dough over and pinch tops closed.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: crock-pot roast
directions: Place roast in crock-pot, fat side down.
Mix bouillon with water and pour in the crock-pot.
Sprinkle other ingredients on top of roast.
Place on high setting for 5 hours.

title: fried rice #2
directions: In 10-inch frying pan, saute onion and green pepper in oils until slightly transparent.
Add meat, rice and soy sauce.
Cook about 1 minute.
Stir in peas.
Add egg.
Cook thoroughly, about 1 minute.
Serves 6 people.

title: cheese cake
directions: Melt butter.
Add to crumbs, 2 tablespoons sugar and cinnamon. Line a spring-form pan and save some to sprinkle on top.
Beat together the remaining ingredients; add one egg at a time.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1/2 hour.
Shut oven off and leave in oven for 1 hour.
Do not open oven door.
Chill.
Cover with preserved canned fruit and serve.

title: lemon bisque
directions: Mix Jell-O, water, sugar, lemon juice and salt; let stand until almost set.
Whip milk, then add Jell-O mixture and mix. Spread crackers on bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish; pour in mixture.
Sprinkle crackers on top.
Put in refrigerator and let set until ready to eat.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Place rice in greased casserole dish.
Add chicken (meat side up). Sprinkle onion soup mix on chicken.
Add cream of mushroom soup.
Pour water over soup and cover.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes in a 400° oven.

title: broccoli, mushroom, cheese, scallop casserole
directions: Cook broccoli. Drain and spread in 1-quart baking dish.
Pour mushroom soup over broccoli. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 20 minutes in a 350° oven until broccoli
is tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: poppy seed chicken casserole
directions: Layer chicken in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish or pan.
Mix together all other ingredients except butter and cracker crumbs. Pour over top of chicken, and top with cracker crumbs.
Drizzle butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until good and bubbly.

title: tomato pie
directions: Peel and slice tomatoes.
Place tomatoes in baked pie shell. Dab mayonnaise on tomatoes.
Sprinkle with garlic powder. Place cheese on top.
Bake in 350° oven for approximately 10 minutes. Remove, cool and serve.

title: salad dressing cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spanish chicken
directions: Bring to a boil, soups, broth and tomatoes.
Add onion, chicken and crumbled Doritos.
Cover dish and bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Remove cover and top with grated sharp Cheddar cheese. Return to oven until cheese melts.

title: tomato marmalade
directions: Peel and quarter tomatoes; cover with sugar and allow to stand overnight.
Drain off syrup; bring to boiling and cook until syrup spins a thread (232°).
Add tomato sections and orange and lemon slices.
Cook over low heat until tomato is transparent.
Pour into hot, sterilized glasses and seal immediately.
This method cuts the cooking time for the fruit and gives a bright, colorful marmalade.
Makes 10 (8 oz.) glasses.

title: play dough
directions: Bring water and salt to a boil.
Take off heat and add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Oil palm of glove and counter. Knead dough until it looks like play dough.
Add fold coloring to get desired shade (takes lots).
Must be kept in refrigerator. Makes 7 play dough cans full.

title: cheese broccoli bake
directions: Combine butter and water.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat. Add crumbs; mix well.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir.
Spoon along both sides of shallow 2-quart baking dish.
Arrange broccoli spears down center.
Sprinkle salt over broccoli.

title: cheese and corn dip
directions: Mix all ingredients the day before and refrigerate overnight. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: borscht(russian soup)
directions: Grate beets and combine with onion and water in a heavy kettle. Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer about 45 minutes.
Add tomato puree, lemon juice, dill, salt and pepper.
Cook 45 minutes more. Heat but do not boil.
Serve hot or cold topped with sour cream (optional, omit for low cholesterol).
Serves 4 to 6. Low cholesterol.

title: fish courtbouillon
directions: Saute onions and bell peppers until tender.
Add all canned ingredients.
After about 5 minutes add fish and cook until tender.

title: fancy fruit dip
directions: Combine all 3 ingredients; serve with your favorite fresh fruit.
To make mixture thinner, add lemon juice in small amounts to get desired texture.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix pudding using fruit juice.
Add milk to equal fluid suggested on pudding box.
Add fruit and chill overnight.
You can add coconut and nuts if desired.

title: ambrosia
directions: Toss all ingredients together.
Chill and serve.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all together good in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes and brown on top.

title: chess cookie squares
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour into bowl.
To butter, add
cake mix, 1 egg and vanilla. Stir with fork.
Press into pan. In mixing bowl, combine softened cream cheese, powdered sugar and 2 eggs.
Beat on high speed for 5 minutes.
Pour over mixture in pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes. Cool completely before cutting into squares.

title: joy's red rice
directions: Melt the butter in 2 cups of boiling water.
After melting, dissolve dry onion soup mix in the mixture.
Stir in uncooked rice.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes. Serves 4 to 6.

title: marinated pork chops
directions: Simmer for 15 minutes.
Pour over 8 to 10 pork chops or 4 thick-cut pork chops and refrigerate several hours or overnight. Grill.

title: zack's fabulous fudge
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa and milk.
Stir together in a 2-quart saucepan.
Bring to a soft ball on candy thermometer.
Have prepared, greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan and 4 inches of cool water in sink.
Remove mixture from heat.
Add butter, Fluff and peanut butter.
Stir in while pan sits in water to cool.
As it starts to thicken, remove from water, stir in vanilla and quickly pour into 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: snickerdoodle cookies
directions: Mix oil, sugar and eggs.
Stir in flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt.
Roll into small balls and roll in a mixture of two teaspoons cinnamon and 2 tablespoons of sugar.

title: trish's irish potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes and cut into 1-inch wedges.
Combine ingredients and spread evenly, 1 layer thin, in a large roasting pan.
Bake at 450° for about 55 minutes, until brown.
Serve with Sherry Butter.

title: garlic bread
directions: Mix well and spread on sliced French bread.
Broil until golden brown.

title: hudler chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients for marinade.

title: mango nut bread
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Beat in dry ingredients, then fold in mango, lime juice and nuts.
Bake in 9-inch loaf pan at 375° for 1 hour.
Best a day after baking.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Mix together the cake mix, oleo, peanut butter and egg.
Press 2/3 of this mixture into a greased 9 x 13 inch pan.
Melt over low heat the condensed milk, 2 tablespoons of butter and chocolate chips.
Pour over mix, then spoon remainder of peanut butter mixture randomly over chocolate.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: seafoam icing
directions: Cook brown sugar, water and corn syrup over medium heat until it forms a soft ball in cold water.
Pour slowly over stiffly beaten egg whites, beating constantly until it is the right consistency.
Beat in vanilla.

title: zucchini pickles(bread and butter)
directions: Wash zucchini and cut into thin slices.
Peel and quarter onions, then slice very thin.
Add to zucchini.
Cover with water and add salt; let stand 2 hours.
Drain thoroughly.
Bring remaining ingredients to boiling.
Pour over zucchini and onions. Let stand 2 hours.
Bring all ingredients to boil and boil for 5 minutes.
Pack into clean pint or quart jars.
Leave 1/8-inch headspace.
Process in water bath canner for 15 minutes; cool. Test for seal; store.

title: kolacky(polish cookies)
directions: Mix cream cheese and butter until fluffy.
Beat in vanilla. Combine flour and salt; add to butter mixture, 1/2 cup at a time, while beating well after each addition.
Chill dough until easy to handle.

title: miniature pizza
directions: Mix all ingredients together with a small amount of mayonnaise to make a spread. Spread on party rye or pumpernickel. Cook in 300° oven for approximately 10 minutes or until cheese melts. Serve warm.

title: poulet d'artichoke
directions: Arrange artichokes in greased casserole or 8 individual ramekins.
Add crushed garlic cloves to olive oil and heat. Drizzle oil mixture over artichokes. Spread chicken on top. Combine mayonnaise, soup, lemon juice and curry powder.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese and top with bread cubes that have been tossed in the melted butter.
Bake at 350°
for 25 to 35 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, butter and milk.
Cook for 2 minutes at 300°.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla, peanut butter and oats. Stir until oats are coated.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Cool before serving.
Yields 3 dozen cookies.

title: sausage meatballs
directions: Roll hot sausage into bite size balls. Brown well. Mix together the catsup, brown sugar, water, lemon juice, soy sauce and drained pineapple tidbits. Put in crock-pot and cook on low for several hours.

title: 100th day snack
directions: Mix together the counted ingredients and the snack is ready to be served.

title: afternoon tea donuts
directions: Beat eggs until very light.
Add sugar, salt, nutmeg, shortening and milk.
Then add flour and baking powder, which have been sifted together.
Mix well.
Drop into deep, hot fat and fry (by teaspoonfuls) until golden brown.
Roll donuts in 10x sugar after frying.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add strawberries and pineapple.
Let chill until it begins to set.
Fold in mashed bananas.
Put half of mixture in mold or dish; let stand until firm.
Spread on whipping cream.
Add remaining jello mixture on top of whipping cream.

title: jiffy pickles
directions: Peel moderately hard kiwi, slice into crosswise slices.
Cover with sweet pickle syrup from commercial pickles or your own recipe. Store overnight before using.
Will keep for several days.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix soups and rice together and pour into pan.
Season chicken and place on top of rice mixture.
Bake at 250° for 3 1/2 hours.

title: lazy pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and water together.
Melt butter in bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan.
Add batter on top of butter, then add peaches with juice on top of mixture.
Bake at 300° until it is golden brown on top.
Serve with ice cream.
You can substitute any fruit you wish.

title: carrot cake with mandarin cream
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 2 (9-inch) round layer cake pans.

title: tangy lime-pecan salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Blend in pineapple; add cottage cheese, mayonnaise and condensed milk, mixing thoroughly. Add nuts, horseradish, lemon juice, salt and food coloring; mix well.
Pour into large mold and refrigerate until firm. (Horseradish is a must to give it zing.)
Makes 6 servings.

title: rich sweet potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put into greased casserole.
Mix topping and spread over mixture.
Bake at 375° until browned.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes and at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: ketchup
directions: Boil down tomato juice 1/3 way.
Add onions, salt and vinegar; boil down 1/2.
Add 20 drops each of cinnamon and clove oils. Combine the sugar and cornstarch; add slowly.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes.
Can in pint jars.
Process 20 minutes in boiling water bath.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: Sift flour with soda and salt.
Cream shortening with sugars and add eggs.
Beat well.
Add hot water and vanilla.
Mix in dry ingredients, nuts, chocolate chips and oatmeal.
Drop by teaspoons on greased cookie sheet; bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes large batch.

title: cooked chocolate frosting
directions: Combine all ingredients, except vanilla.
Boil 2 minutes.
Add vanilla.
Beat until spreading consistency.

title: chicken pot pies
directions: In a big pot, put chicken, broth, 1 can of water and salt.
On low heat, cook for 2 hours or until chicken is done.
Take chicken out of pot and put on plate to cool.
With the broth make gravy. Add chicken (cut into small pieces) to gravy.
Put in pie shells and cook in a 350° oven until top crust is brown, about 1 hour. Careful, chicken is hot inside!

title: chinese cole slaw
directions: Put cabbage and onion in a large bowl; set aside.
In a skillet, melt butter and brown the noodles, sesame and sunflower seeds.
Combine with cabbage mixture.

title: crab rangoon
directions: Filling:
In medium mixing bowl, blend crabmeat with cream cheese and steak sauce.
Add garlic powder, salt, pepper and egg yolk; blend thoroughly until light and fluffy.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash and decap mushrooms.
Mince stems and garlic, put in pan with rest of ingredients except paprika.
Make sure bread crumbs are added last so they don't soak up too much of the soy sauce. Saute till paste-like consistency.
Spoon mixture into each cap and sprinkle with paprika.
Lay in pan and cook at 350 F till brown on top.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter.
Mix other ingredients with butter and stir well. Place in preheated oven at 350° for about 1 hour or until brown.

title: homemade orange sherbet
directions: Beat together and freeze in a one gallon ice cream freezer. It's ready to eat!!!

title: raisin (poor man's) cake
directions: Bake at 375° in an 11 x 15-inch pan for 45 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger; drain and let cool.
Mix all the ingredients together.

title: veggie casserole
directions: Cook and drain vegetable of your choice; pour into ungreased casserole dish.
Add soup and milk; stir.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese and Ritz cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
(Do not cook macaroni.)
Place in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350°, covered, for 30 minutes and uncovered, for 30 minutes.
It makes approximately 6 to 8 servings for a side dish or 4 to 6 servings for a main dish.

title: four layer chocolate delight
directions: Step 1: Mix together first 3 ingredients.
Press into 9x13 inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.	Cool.

title: baked cheese grits
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix eggs, cheese, butter, mustard, salt and garlic.
Stir into grits and pour into well buttered 4 to 6 cup casserole. Bake, uncovered, 50 minutes.
Serve immediately, directly from casserole.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: shrimp fondue
directions: In a small saucepan, slowly melt cream cheese.
Slowly add remaining ingredients until hot (not boiling).
Place in a serving pot.
Serve with Italian bread.

title: chocolate hershey pie
directions: Melt marshmallows in milk.
Break up Hershey bars in milk and melt.
Cool.
Whip the cream; fold into cooled Hershey mixture. Pour into crust.
Chill.

title: creole cabbage
directions: Combine ingredients and cook until done.
Use pimento for colors.

title: hidden valley pea salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except bacon bits.
Chill.
Garnish and add bacon bits before serving.

title: seven layer salad
directions: In a 3-quart serving bowl, layer the ingredients, spreading mayonnaise to edges to seal.
Refrigerate until chilled.
May be tossed before serving.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar well. Add eggs, beating well after each one. Add dry ingredients alternately with milk. Bake in a greased bundt pan. Put the cake in a Cold oven, bake at 325° for 1 hour 30 minutes.

title: cas' chess pie
directions: Mix sugar, butter and eggs yolks.
Add salt, nutmeg, vanilla and milk.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake at 350 degrees in unbaked pie shells.

title: marshmallow delights
directions: Separate crescent rolls into 8 triangles.
Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Dip each marshmallow into melted margarine.
Roll in cinnamon/sugar mixture and place on crescent triangle.
Pinch dough around marshmallows, sealing off edges.
Dip tops of dough in remaining butter, then cinnamon/sugar mixture.
Place, sugar side up, in greased muffin cups.
Bake at 375° for 13 to 15 minutes. Serve warm.

title: old-fashioned lemon pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar; beat in egg yolks.
Add water with meal, mixed.
Add lemon juice and grated rind of one.
Last, fold in beaten whites.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, until brown and done.
Makes 2 large pies.

title: company potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes until not quite done. Grate after cool.
Combine all ingredients (save 1/2 tablespoon of margarine for over top). Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: five bean salad
directions: Rinse beans and drain.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour over beans and mix.

title: steak rolls
directions: You will need a ball of thin cord.

title: claudia's squash casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Soften butter.
Pour squash over butter.
Mix in rest of ingredients.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes in sprayed casserole dish.
Delicious!

title: blueberry cheese cake
directions: Cream together the cream cheese and sugar with mixer.
Fold in Cool Whip and sour cream.
Fold in lemon juice.
Pour into crust. Top with blueberry pie filling.

title: peanut butter raspberry toast
directions: Thaw frozen raspberries.
Toast bread.
Spread peanut butter on toasted side of toast.
Put raspberries on top of peanut butter.
Enjoy!

title: jean's cold oven pound cake
directions: Cream together butter and Crisco; add sugar and beat well. Add one egg at a time, beating well after each.
Sift flour and baking powder together and add to mixture alternately with milk, mixing well after each addition.
Stir in flavorings.
Beat well.

title: eggnog french toast
directions: Mix eggs and eggnog together.
Put French bread in pan or casserole.
Cover with egg mixture.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and nutmeg.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Grill both sides in frying pan in butter, then put in casserole.
Bake 15 minutes in 350° oven.
Makes 14 slices of French bread.

title: apple crisp microwave
directions: Place apples in 8 x 8-inch microwave pan.
Put 2/3 cup sugar over the apples.
Mix all the other ingredients together, then mix well together.
Put over the top of apples.
Microwave 9 to 12 minutes on High.

title: spiced rice, korean style
directions: Heat 2 oil in saucepan large enough for cooking rice.
Add rice; stir and cook for 5 minutes, or until rice is dry and begins to stick to the pan.
Add beef and remaining oil; cook with rice until beef is no longer pink.
Soften onion in water; add, along with mushrooms.
Saute until onion is limp and transparent.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover; bring to boiling point over high heat.
Reduce heat to slow; cook for 20 minutes, or until rice is tender.

title: old-fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
In another bowl, cream butter; gradually add sugar and cream well.
Stir in egg, cream and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients gradually.
Mix well.
Chill if necessary.
Roll out one-third at a time on a floured surface to 1/8-inch thickness.
Cut into desired shapes.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 400° for 5 to 8 minutes until delicately brown. Decorate.
Makes about 6 to 7 dozen.

title: cherry nut squares
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add vanilla.
Stir in eggs, one at a time.
Add flour and mix well.
Spread 3/4 of batter in an ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Top with cherry filling.
Dot with remaining batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin-pecan cheesecake
directions: For crust, combine crushed graham crackers, crushed gingersnaps, the 2 tablespoons pecans, flour, powdered sugar and melted butter or margarine in a medium bowl. Press evenly onto the bottom of a 9-inch spring-form pan. Set aside. Beat cream cheese and granulated sugar in a large mixing bowl with an electric mixer on medium speed until fluffy. Add the 3 eggs all at once, beating on low speed just until combined. Place 1 cup of cream cheese mixture in a medium bowl. Add pumpkin, the 1 egg, milk, cinnamon, ginger and nutmeg. Beat on low speed just until combined. Pour pumpkin mixture into prepared spring-form pan. Top with cream cheese mixture. With a knife or thin metal spatula, gently swirl through the layers to marble.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix together in top of double boiler the caramels, 1/2 cup evaporated milk and 1/2 stick margarine.
Heat until caramels are melted.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.
Serve with fresh vegetables.

title: sex in a bowl
directions: Crumble 1 layer of cake and put it in a large bowl.
Pour half of Kahlua on top, half pudding, half Cool Whip and half candy. Repeat layers.
Refrigerate.
(You can substitute Hershey syrup for Kahlua if serving to kids.) Top with stemmed cherries.

title: chicken ole casserole
directions: Season chicken with poultry seasoning; saute in oil and garlic powder until lightly browned.
Drain and set aside.
Cook broccoli and rice according to package directions.
Mix rice, broccoli, cheese, soup and chicken.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Put in casserole dish and top with bread crumbs and melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chili dip
directions: Pour can of Ro-Tel in pan.
Mash tomatoes up and add the cheese and melt.
Add soup and stir until smooth.
Add can of chili and heat.
Serve dip warm.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown good quality beef.
Add a little water and simmer until tender.
Add mushroom soup and sour cream.
Simmer another 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve over noodles.

title: eva's scalloped pineapple
directions: Grease casserole.
Combine all ingredients.
Place in prepared casserole. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: cheese and macaroni, my way
directions: Following the directions on package, cook macaroni in salted water.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream oleo and shortening.
Add sugar and yolks.
Add flour, salt and soda alternating with buttermilk.
(If you do not have buttermilk, make it by adding one tablespoon vinegar to 1 cup whole milk.)
Add vanilla, coconut and chopped nuts.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into greased and floured cake pans (three 9-inch pans).
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: may's whole wheat rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix first 3 ingredients.
Let cool. Mix sugar, yeast and 1 cup water.
Let stand while first mixture cools.
Sift flour.
Mix all liquids together.
Add flour, one cup at a time until all liquids and dry ingredients are combined. Place in large, greased bowl.
Cover and let rise in warm place until double.
Punch down and let rise.
Sprinkle surface with ground graham crackers.
Roll out and cut.
Bake on greased baking sheet until browned.

title: viennese walnut bars
directions: Cream together 1 stick margarine, white sugar and cream cheese.
Blend in 1 1/4 cups flour.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan. Combine 1 cup walnuts and chocolate chips.
Sprinkle over pastry. Cream together 1/2 stick margarine, brown sugar, eggs and coffee. Sift together 1 cup flour, baking powder and salt.
Blend flour mixture into brown sugar mixture.
Spread over chocolate chips and nuts.
Sprinkle on remaining 1/2 cup walnuts.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes, until firm on top.

title: blackberry cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter together; beat eggs and add to creamed mixture.
Combine flour, spices, baking soda and baking powder. Stir into creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Carefully fold in blackberries.
Bake at 350° in 3 greased and floured 8-inch cake pans for 30 minutes.
Cool and frost with icing.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Brown ground beef in vegetable oil.
Add beef broth, cabbage, potato, onion, tomato sauce, salt and pepper.
Cook on medium-low for 30 minutes until vegetables are tender.
Add kidney beans and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: punch
directions: Combine all ingredients in punch bowl.

title: turkey or chicken pot pie
directions: Beautiful maiden pause ere you wed.
Learn to boil coffee, learn to bake bread; learn, oh, sweet girl, that one road to man's heart lies through his stomach; they're not far apart.
He loves your sweet face, he praises your eyes, has a tooth for your pudding, dotes on your pies.
Then beautiful maiden, be sure ere you wed, that you learn to make coffee, learn to bake bread.

title: tara's favorite birthday cake
directions: Follow the recipe on the package, substituting orange juice for the water.
I used the high altitude in Colorado.
Bake as directed in two 9-inch round pans.
Cool.
Spread a generous amount of apricot preserves on the first layer.
