Now smooth Cool Whip on top of the preserves.
Top the cake with the second layer. Ice only the top of the cake with a thick layer of Cool Whip. Make a nest in the center of the cake with a spoon and fill this area with fresh blueberries.
This cake is showy, delicious and easy!!! Betty Crocker SuperMoist lemon cake was used.

title: pumpkin torte
directions: Mix first layer ingredients and press into 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake 7 minutes at 350°.

title: pancake mix
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, sugar and salt together.
Combine egg, milk and vegetable oil.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring just until flour is moistened.
Batter will be slightly lumpy.

title: bacon-tomato dip
directions: In skillet cook the bacon until crisp; remove.
Drain on a paper towel and crumble.
In a mixing bowl combine the softened cream cheese, prepared mustard and celery salt.
Stir in the crumbled bacon, the finely chopped tomato and the finely chopped green pepper.
Transfer to a serving bowl.
Cover and chill until cold.
Serve with vegetables.
Makes 2 cups.

title: pita bread
directions: Combine 2 cups flour, yeast,
sugar
and salt in a large mixing bowl.
Stir in water
and oil.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in enough remaining flour to make
soft dough.
Turn out onto a floured surface; continue to work in flour until dough is stiff enough to knead.
Knead about
5 minutes.
Place in oiled bowl, turn to oil top of dough.
Cover,
let
rise
in
a
warm place until double in bulk, about
minutes.
Punch down dough and divide into 12 to 16 equal
parts.
Roll into a ball.
Let rest 5 minutes.
Roll into
8-inch
round
1/8-inch thick.
Sprinkle baking sheets with cornmeal.
Place
on
baking sheets.
Cover, let rise 30 minutes.
Bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes or until puffed and brown.
Cut in half.

title: oatmeal date bars
directions: Place first 3 ingredients in saucepan and cook until thick. Cool.
Blend the remaining ingredients until the mixture is crumbly. Divide into 2 parts.
Pack half the mixture in the bottom of a greased pan about 7 1/2 x 11-inches in size. Cover with the cooked date mixture and top with the rest of the dough.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Cool and cut into bars.
Frost with confectioners icing, if desired.

title: buttermilk cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar well.
Add remaining ingredients and beat until smooth.
Pour into oblong cake pan.
Bake at 325° for one hour.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Brown beef in a large pot and add other ingredients.
Cook, covered, until meat falls apart.
Cool thoroughly.
Separate meat from fat and bones.
Put meat back in sauce.
Heat when ready. Serve on buns.

title: roasted eggplant salad
directions: Rub
eggplants with oil.
Place on pan and bake at 400° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Slit skin and scrape out flesh; cut in chunks and
put
in serving bowl.
Mix with other ingredients and
stir. Serve at room temperature or chilled.
Contains 40 calories per 1/2 cup.

title: polish sauerkraut
directions: Saute mushrooms, onions and bell pepper in butter.
In crock-pot or Dutch oven, cook smoked sausage until heated thoroughly.
Add sauteed vegetables, kraut, tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Cook in crock-pot on high for 3 or 4 hours or in Dutch oven about 1 1/2 hours.

title: green vegetable salad
directions: Mix peas, green beans, corn, celery, green pepper and onions until well mixed.
Stir salt, sugar, vinegar and salad oil together until sugar dissolves.
Pour over vegetables and chill overnight before serving.

title: chaote pickles
directions: Heat to dissolve sugar; add drained chaote slices.
Bring to boil; simmer 7 or 8 minutes.
Chaote slices will change color. Pack in jars with some of the spices and enough juice to cover slices.
Set aside for a week or so.
Try to use young tender chaote squash, more mature squash need to be peeled.

title: spaghetti pizza
directions: Cook spaghetti as directed on package.
In a bowl, blend milk and egg.
Add spaghetti; toss to coat.
Spread spaghetti in a jelly roll pan that has been coated with nonstick spray.
In a large skillet, brown the ground beef.
Add onion, green pepper and garlic.
Drain off the fat.
Add seasonings and tomato sauce. Simmer 5 minutes.
Spoon meat mixture over spaghetti; top with mushrooms and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Serves 8.

title: poor man's cake
directions: Boil all ingredients together except last 3, stirring occasionally; let cool.
Add cooled ingredients to flour.
Mix with spoon; add baking soda and vinegar.
Mix thoroughly.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in 9 x 12-inch greased pan.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Combine soup and water.
Mix all ingredients together and bake in buttered casserole at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix the cake mix, poppy seed and pudding mix together thoroughly by hand.
Add other ingredients and stir with spoon. Do not use mixer.
Pour in 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese, pineapple, onion and seasoned salt.
Shape into a ball and roll in pecans. Wrap in plastic wrap and refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: homemade rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast, sugar and salt in warm water.
Add egg and oil.
Mix in 2 cups of flour at a time until all mixed.
Lightly grease bowl; put dough in bowl.
Cover and refrigerate for 24 hours.
(Can keep in refrigerator for up to 2 weeks.)
Remove dough 2 to 3 hours before baking.
Grease muffin pan and shape dough into medium size balls.
Rub tops of balls with butter-flavored Crisco and let rolls raise for 2 to 3 hours.
(Can cover with light weight towel.)
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 18 to 24 rolls.
(Makes great pizza dough, too!)

title: banana dumplings
directions: Use sufficient flour to roll out biscuits thin.
Place 1/2 sliced banana on each biscuit.
Combine cinnamon/sugar and sprinkle 1 teaspoon of mix and small slice of margarine on banana.
Fold over edges of biscuits, pinching to seal.
Place on a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Pour milk over and around biscuits.
Sprinkle remaining cinnamon/sugar mixture, flour and margarine over biscuits and milk.
Bake at 425° for 35 minutes.
Sliced apples or grated coconut can be substituted for bananas.

title: lead bellies
directions: Bake potatoes until well done.
Do not use foil.
Cut open and push up potato.
Butter potato.
Place thinly sliced turkey, ham and beef.
Next put sauteed onion and green pepper (optional).
Top with a slice of Swiss cheese.
Broil until cheese melts.

title: cheater's lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet, seasoning as desired.
Drain and set aside.
Cook noodles until tender; place half into bottom of baking dish.
Take ground beef and add seasoning packet and enough water to simmer adequately.
Spoon half of mixture over noodles in baking dish.
Layer with grated Mozzarella cheese.
Next, layer with noodles, then meat sauce and top with cheese slices, filling in with any remaining grated cheese.
Cottage cheese may be inserted, as desired.
Place in a 325° to 350° oven until bubbly, then place under broiler until cheese begins to turn brown.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine first 3 ingredients and set aside.
Cream with a fork room temperature margarine and sugars. Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly.
Stir in 1/3 of flour mixture until completely moistened.
Repeat until all flour mixture is gone, mixing until all flour is moistened.
Add in chocolate chips.
Nuts are optional.
With a teaspoon, drop a scoop of dough onto cookie sheet, approximately a dozen to a sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.

title: bacon dip
directions: Combine ingredients.
Chill at least 3 hours before serving. Serve with a variety of raw vegetables, or cherry tomatoes may be hollowed out and stuffed with the mixture.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Toss macaroni in oil.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Pour into lightly greased crock-pot.
Stir well. Cover and cook on low 3 to 4 hours.
Stir occasionally.
Can also bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pepper steak
directions: Brown meat in hot oil.
Add water with bouillon cubes and bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer until meat is tender.
Add peppers and simmer for 5 minutes.
Blend cornstarch, soy sauce and 1/2 cup water.
Add to meat mixture and cook; stir until thickened.
Serve with rice, also good with potatoes.

title: salsa dip
directions: Brown sausage and drain off fat. Cut cheese into small pieces. Place in small crock-pot. Heat until cheese melts.
Small amount of water may be added to thin.

title: cherry squares
directions: Cream together butter and sugar; add eggs one at a time, beating well after each one.
Add vanilla and almond extract; mix well.
Stir in flour and salt.
Spread batter on jelly roll pan, saving approximately 1/4 of batter.
Cover with cherry pie filling.
Drop remaining batter by spoonfuls over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Time may vary.
You can drizzle a thin coating of icing over cooled bars.

title: frosty cranberry cocktail
directions: In a blender container, combine cranberry juice, rum, banana and lemon juice. Cover and blend until smooth. Add half the ice cubes. Cover and blend until smooth. Add remaining ice cubes. Cover and blend until slushy.
Pour into glasses. Garnish each with banana slices, if desired.

title: spoon bread
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Stir boiling water into cornmeal.
Stir in rest of ingredients except egg whites.
Beat egg whites to soft peak.
Then fold into mixture.
Pour in greased 2-quart casserole. Bake 45 to 50 minutes.
Makes 8 servings, 155 calories.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Combine butter, syrup, sugar and salt in an 8 cup glass measuring cup or a 3 quart mixing bowl.
Bring to a boil and them cook 2 1/2 minutes.
Stir in baking soda.
Pour over popped corn in a large grocery bag that has been sprayed with a pan coating.
Stir lightly to combine.
Put the bag in the microwave and cook 2 1/2 minutes stirring after 1 minute.
Remove from microwave and spread out on a cookie sheet to cool.
Break apart.

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix ingredients well together.
Bake for 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Put cooked chicken in a buttered 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Mix soup and sour cream; spread over chicken.
Top with cracker crumbs and poppy seed.
Pour melted margarine over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until bubbly.
Serve over rice.

title: cabbage and ground beef
directions: In a large skillet heat oil, cook onion and ground beef until brown.
Add chopped cabbage, cook until tender.
(May cover to speed cooking.)
When cabbage is done, add sour cream, salt and pepper to taste.

title: hot hominy casserole
directions: Drain hominy and place in 8 x 8-inch casserole dish.
Melt oleo, cream of mushroom soup (undiluted) and Cheez Whiz together. Pour over hominy.
Crush Fritos and place on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: *Or block candy chocolate, melted in microwave.

title: slush punch
directions: Bring water and sugar to a boil; cool to tepid.
Add juices and vodka or gin; mix together.
Put in a plastic covered container and freeze.
When serving, put a couple scoops into a glass and cover with ginger ale, half and half or some other mix.

title: "peach ice cream"
directions: Put cream, half and half and sugar in ice cream freezer. Process peaches in blender for a few seconds, then add to freezer. Add vanilla and finish filling freezer with milk. Freeze. Makes 1 gallon.

title: homemade pizza sauce
directions: Mix and break up tomatoes.
Simmer to sauce.

title: bran muffins
directions: Beat the eggs and sugar with an electric mixer.
Add the oil and buttermilk.
Mix together the dry ingredients, then add to above mixture.
Stir the dry ingredients in with a spoon; do not use mixer for this addition.
Refrigerate overnight before using. Can be kept 6 weeks in refrigerator.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes in greased muffin tins.
Makes 5 dozen regular muffins or 8 dozen tiny muffins.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle coconut into pan, then add pecans.
Mix cake according to directions on box.
Pour cake batter over coconut and pecans.
In a mixing bowl mix together cream cheese, margarine and powdered sugar.
Spoon this mixture over cake batter.
Don't try to smooth mixture, it will run together.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until cake pulls away from sides of pan.
Cake will have a crack in it.

title: "sugar free" apple crisp
directions: Stir apples, cinnamon, tapioca, oil and apple juice concentrate together and place in a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix flour, oats, margarine and cinnamon.
Sprinkle on apple mix.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mom lambert's spaghetti
directions: Melt
butter in frying pan.
Put in peppers and onions. Brown for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add 2 pounds ground beef, browned. Salt and pepper to taste.
Drain.
Add tomato paste and tomato paste can half full of water.
Let simmer until water is taken up.
Then add
more
butter
and
fry
for
10 minutes.
Cook spaghetti
and rinse
in
cold
water.
Add
meat mixture and serve.

title: sweet and sour carrots
directions: Slice carrots and parboil in salt water.
Cook until tender. Let cool.
Mix together all ingredients and pour over carrots. Let stand 24 hours.

title: mama's soup surprise
directions: Stir them all together.
It's Mama's Soup Surprise.

title: lasagne con uvetta(lasagne with breadcrumbs)
directions: For lasagne noodles, heap the flour on a board and make a well in the center.
Bread in the eggs and work onto a smooth, soft ball.
Roll it out thinly and cut into 4-inch square.
Fry the breadcrumbs in half the butter until they begin to color.
Stir in the cinnamon and sugar.
Soak the raisins in lukewarm water to cover for about 30 minutes.
Bring a large pot of salted water to boil, drop in noodles and cook al dente.
Melt the remaining butter in a small skillet.
Lift the lasagne out of the water with a slotted spoon and arrange on a serving plate or dish. Scatter the raisins on top.
Sprinkle with the melted butter and breadcrumbs and serve.

title: cauliflower soup(blumenkohlsuppe)
directions: Microwave the cauliflower whole in a little water with the sugar added in a glass pie plate or other microwave-safe dish covered with plastic wrap on High for 10 to 15 minutes until very tender.
(Or, the cauliflower may be cut into pieces and cooked in a little water with the sugar added in a pan on the stove until very tender.)
Cut the cooked cauliflower into pieces and place in a food processor.
Add enough of the cream to puree easily (or the cauliflower may be mashed until fine).
Melt oleo in a large pot, preferably Teflon-coated; sprinkle in flour.
Stir over low heat until mixture is well-blended and bubbly.
Remove from heat and add 3 cups of milk all at once.
Stir constantly over higher heat until thickened.
Stir in the pureed cauliflower.
Add cream and seasonings and heat until hot, but do not boil.
(Add remainder of milk if soup is thicker than desired.)

title: seacoast salad
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese as directed.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix lightly.
Chill.
Add additional salad dressing before serving, if desired.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cottage cheese and pineapple salad
directions: Mix all together and add whipped cream last.
Chill.

title: watergate salad
directions: Blend
pudding
and whipped topping until well blended. Add pecans and fruit cocktail.
Mix well.

title: five hour stew
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Put all ingredients, raw into large casserole with a tight fitting lid.
Boil covered 4 1/2 to 5 hours.
Don't peek.
Add a can of English peas the last 5 minutes before serving.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Mix together first four ingredients.
Dot with butter and cinnamon.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: cheesy potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle with paprika, if desired.
Bake uncovered at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: jalapeno cornbread casserole
directions: Mix cornmeal, milk, eggs, corn, beans, salt and oil together. Batter will be thin.
Cook ground beef and drain.
In a large bowl combine meat, onion, peppers and cheese.
Pour 1/2 of the batter into a well greased cast-iron pan.
Spread filling evenly over batter.
Pour remaining batter over filling.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: aunt jean's apple cake
directions: Combine apples, 3 tablespoons sugar and cinnamon and set aside.
Mix sugar, oil and eggs well.
Add orange juice and vanilla and mix.
Add flour, baking powder and salt and mix.
In large oblong pan (greased and floured) pour 1/2 batter then 1/2 chopped apples and repeat.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: nutty cheese spread
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients in saucepan.
Stir until thick.
Add cream cheese to hot mixture.
Add pimiento and mix well, then add pecans.
Place in bowl; cover well.
Let stay in refrigerator at least 24 hours.
Really delicious! Serve in a pretty bowl with assorted crackers.

title: taco salad
directions: Chop lettuce.
Add all other ingredients except dressing. Just before serving, add dressing and toss.

title: homemade candy
directions: Put the first 4 ingredients in a pan and boil until you can take some out and test it by putting some in a cup of water.
If it comes to a lump, then it is ready to put the peanut butter in. Beat it until it is stiff.
After that, put it on a meat platter until it is hard.

title: party bread
directions: Mix cheese, bacon, olives, onion, Worcestershire sauce, salt and mayonnaise.
Mix well.
Place 1 teaspoon on each bread square. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Cover.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.
Put in freezer containers.
Freeze.
Makes 7 (1/2 pound) butter bowls.

title: crumb cake
directions: In mixing bowl, combine sugar, flour and salt.
Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Remove 1 cup mixture and combine with cinnamon and nuts.
Set aside.
To remaining crumb mixture, add milk and baking powder.
Spread into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle the reserved crumb mixture over batter. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cut into squares.
Garnish with whipped cream or serve plain.

title: hot pepper jelly
directions: Boil chopped peppers, sugar, vinegar and salt for 4 to 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; add Certo and food coloring (if desired).
Pour into jars.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg, cloves, ginger and salt. Combine with molasses and pumpkin; add milk. Beat 2 eggs and 1 egg yolk; add. Beat 1 egg white stiff; fold in. Pour into pastry shell. Bake at 425 for 45 minutes or until inserted knife comes out clean.

title: teenagers special spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.
Serve in a hollowed out loaf of pumpernickel bread.
Add various kinds of cut breads as options for dip.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Layer as listed.
Cover tightly and store overnight in fridge.

title: brunswick mini-stew
directions: Boil meats together.
When well cooked, drain liquid until meat is just covered.
Bone meat.
Add to vegetables.
Stir in catsup and barbecue sauce.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Cook until onion is done.

title: chicken adobo
directions: Clean chicken and cut into desired serving size.
Let it drain to remove excess water for about 15 minutes.
Saute garlic in fat trimmings from the chicken until golden brown.
Add black pepper and bay leaves.
Add vinegar, soy sauce and sugar.
Add chicken and let simmer for 20 minutes.
Add 1/2 cup water if chicken is not yet tender.
Boil for another 15 minutes.
Serve with steamed rice with fried bananas on the side.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Soak tortillas in boiling chicken broth and drain.
Cover bottom of dish with tortillas.
Add boned, chopped chicken.
Then add layer of onion, bell pepper, cheese, chili powder and garlic salt.
Top with undiluted soups and tomato mixture.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: milk shakes
directions: Combine milk and favorite syrup.
Add vanilla ice cream; mix just to blend.
Makes 3 1/3.

title: champagne punch(servings:  24)
directions: Mix and serve at once.
Sugar is optional.

title: squash and carrots
directions: Steam the zucchini and squash for 10 minutes.
Combine the soup and sour cream; stir in the carrots.
Fold in the steamed vegetables.
Melt 1 stick of oleo; add to the stuffing mix.
Line dish with 1/2 of the stuffing mix.
Spread vegetables over stuffing.
Cover with the rest of the stuffing.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Boil broccoli with 1/4 cup onion until tender. Drain and place in casserole dish. Mix grated cheese and 1/4 cup onion; add soup mixed with 1/2 cup milk. Pour mixture over broccoli. Roll crackers and mix with butter. Sprinkle over top. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cranberry dessert
directions: Grind cranberries. Add sugar and let stand 1 hour.
Whip the cream and add to cranberries. Stir in marshmallows.
Let stand 1 hour. Combine with pineapple.
Let set overnight.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix.
Pour in loaf pan and bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash in a small amount of boiling, salted water until squash is tender.
Drain well and mash.
Cook bacon until crisp. Drain well, reserving drippings, and crumble.
Combine all ingredients, stirring well.
Spoon into a lightly greased casserole dish (1-quart) and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Pour other ingredients over meat and mix well.
Simmer over low heat for about 15 minutes.
Serve on buns.
Makes approximately 4 servings.

title: freezer slaw
directions: Boil 1 minute and cool.
Place in containers and freeze.
Can be refrozen without changing quality.
Also can eat fresh (very good).

title: french market soup
directions: Soak overnight or parboil beans.
Drain off old water; add 2 quarts of water and the next 3 ingredients.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Simmer until beans are tender.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 30 minutes.

title: whacky cake
directions: Grease and flour an 8-inch square pan.
Sift the sugar, cocoa, salt, flour and soda together in the pan.
Add the vinegar, vanilla and oil.
Pour 1 cup water over all and stir with fork until lumps are gone.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: scripture cake
directions: Season to taste with 2 Chronicles 9:9, a pinch of Leviticus 2:3 and 6 of Jeremiah 17:11.
Follow Solomon's advice for making a good boy and you will have a good cake!

title: green bean corn casserole
directions: Cook green beans as directed.
Drain beans and corn.
Mix in a casserole dish.
Mix soup, sour cream and onions.
Pour over beans and corn mixture.
Crush crackers; melt margarine.
Stir in cracker crumbs and cheese.
Sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake 35 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: five layer mexican dip
directions: In 9
x
13-inch
pan or glass dish, layer dip starting with refried beans
and
finishing
with
sliced black olives. Refrigerate until ready to use.
Serve with Doritos chips.

title: sweet rice with red beans
directions: In a kettle combine red beans with 1 quart fresh water and bring to a boil.
Discard water and boil red beans with 1 quart fresh water for 20 minutes.
Wash sweet rice and soak it with the above water for 30 minutes.
Combine red beans and sweet rice into steamer and cook it for 1 hour.
Sprinkle toasted black sesame seed and salt over rice before serving.

title: sour cream raisin pie
directions: Rinse raisins in cold water before putting through the food chopper.
Beat eggs and then add all other ingredients.
Put in unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: beet au vin
directions: Mix together; put in covered casserole with tight lid and bake at 300° for 3 to 4 hours.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: grilled summer chicken
directions: Or you may use herbs from Prevence instead of individual herbs.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix all together in bowl.
Pour into 1 deep dish graham cracker shell.

title: baked cranberry relish
directions: Mix sugar and cranberries; put in a baking dish.
Mix brown sugar and flour.
Dice apples and mix with sugar and flour.
Put on top of cranberries.
Add nuts; top with melted oleo.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: oriental casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place rice in 2-quart casserole and set aside.
In medium skillet, melt 1 tablespoon butter.
Add onion, carrot, celery and garlic.
Cook and stir over medium heat until tender.
Add to rice.
In medium skillet, cook beef over medium heat until browned.
Drain fat.
Add beef and water chestnuts to rice mixture.

title: quick hot cross buns
directions: In blender, mix cream cheese and sugar or blend well by hand. Stir in raisins.
Set aside.
Press 2 biscuits together.
Flatten on breadboard to make 4-inch square.
Repeat to make nine more squares.
Spoon filling onto centers of dough.
Pull diagonal corners together over filling and pinch to seal.
Repeat with other two corners.
Arrange buns on greased 9-inch pie plate or square cake pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool slightly.

title: mock entenmann's danish pastry
directions: Mix flour and margarine in bowl with fork.
Add few drops of water.
Make 2 balls.
On ungreased pan, form 5 x 12-inch rectangle.
Will make two.

title: tropical turkey salad
directions: Cut turkey in cubes and mix with celery and pineapple chunks. Add raisins, nuts and green onion.

title: company potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix ingredients and pour into glass casserole dish.
Bake for 2 hours.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: blueberry pizza
directions: Mix and pat into a 15-inch pizza pan the first 3 ingredients. Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: raisin pie
directions: Cook all ingredients except cornstarch.
When it boils, add cornstarch and cook until clear and thickened.
Use as filling for 9-inch double crust pie.
Bake at 425° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: hot orange tea
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients; cook over low heat, stirring until dissolved. Add remaining ingredients; mix well. Serve hot. If tea is too strong, add hot water. Makes 10 servings. Preparation time: 0:30.

title: chili
directions: Mix all ingredients, except meat, into a large pot.
Brown the hamburger and sausage in a separate pan and add to the sauce. Cook for several hours.

title: pick-a-dilly
directions: Grind tomatoes, pepper and onion.
Set over colander and drain.
Discard liquid.
Put mixture in pot.
Add 2 quarts vinegar.
Boil uncovered for 30 minutes.
Stir.
Drain in colander and discard liquid.
Put mixture in pot again.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 3 minutes.
Seal and process in pint jars 10 minutes.
Makes 12 pints.

title: slaw eternal
directions: Chop cabbage, pepper, onion and carrot. Pour 1 cup
sugar and salt over vegetables, mixing well.
Heat other ingredients. Cool and pour over the slaw mixture. Pack in a gallon jar and refrigerate.

title: onion pie
directions: Mix the crackers and butter together and put in 10-inch pie plate.
Put onions in skillet.
Cover with water and simmer 15 minutes until transparent.
Drain well.
Put into crust.
Stir eggs and milk.
Pour over onions.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Mix well margarine, sugar and cream cheese.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add pinch of salt, flour, vanilla and baking powder.
Mix well.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: celtic oysters rockefeller
directions: In blender, combine all ingredients except spinach, oysters and rock salt.
Blend, scraping sides, until smooth.
Cover each oyster with spinach.
Top with one rounded teaspoonful of paste from blender.
Place oysters on a bed of rock salt on ovenproof platter.
Bake in preheated 450° oven for 10 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease a 2-quart baking dish. Combine flour, sugar and salt; add kernel corn and stir, coating all kernels. Add creamed corn to mixture.

title: beef tenderloin marinade
directions: Marinate for 2 hours.
Preheat oven to 400° and bake whole tenderloin 25 to 30 minutes, regardless of size.

title: kay's raspberry custard pie
directions: Brush unbaked pie shell with butter.
Mix ingredients together, except for raspberries.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Place raspberries which have been sprinkled with flour on top of custard.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes to set crust.
Then bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes until custard sets.

title: strawberry nut salad
directions: Use stale or fresh bread, cutting into small cubes.
Place in pan.
Sprinkle with garlic powder.
Place in oven at 250° for about 30 minutes.
Turn oven off and let them stay for another hour.
Delicious!

title: vegetable bake
directions: In a shallow 1-quart casserole toss together first 4 ingredients.
In a 1-quart saucepan mix cornstarch, salt and pepper.
Gradually stir in milk until smooth; add margarine. Stirring constantly, bring to a boil over medium heat and boil 1 minute.
Stir in lemon juice and tarragon.
Pour over vegetables. Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Serves 6.

title: pineapple-cottage cheese salad
directions: In a saucepan bring Jell-O, buttermilk and pineapple to boil; stir 1 minute.
Dump into large bowl and mix in Cool Whip, nuts and cottage cheese.
Chill 4 to 5 hours.
Serves 8.

title: tex-mex dip
directions: Mix taco seasoning with sour cream.
Layer ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch pan in the following order:
Refried beans, sour cream and taco seasoning mixture, avocado dip, green onions, tomatoes and cheese.
Refrigerate until chilled.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: lime jello dessert
directions: Mix cottage cheese and pineapple together.
Stir in lime jello, Cool Whip and nuts as desired.
After folding in all ingredients, cool and serve.

title: ham and tater bake
directions: Arrange potatoes in a layer on bottom and sides of casserole dish 13 x 9-inches.
Heat at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes or until potatoes are lightly browned.
While potatoes are cooking, combine soup and milk over low heat.
Stir until blended.
Add ham and broccoli.
Add most of cheese; stir.
Pour mixture into casserole over potatoes.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes, until cheese is melted and mixture is bubbly.
Let stand a few minutes before serving.

title: barbecue tuna
directions: Mix together in saucepan.
Cook on low heat until almost dry.

title: praline-sweet potato casserole
directions: Boil or bake sweet potatoes.
Peel and mash. Place potatoes in mixing bowl. Add butter and remaining ingredients.
Beat thoroughly.

title: tomato yogurt soup
directions: Put tomatoes and cucumber in blender; puree.
Pour into large bowl; leave half in blender.
Add yogurt and season; mix.
Stir into tomato mixture; heat until warm.

title: pork spareribs
directions: Mix soy sauce, sugar and ajinomoto in a bowl.
Marinate pork spareribs in the mixture overnight.
Keep covered in the refrigerator.
Remove spareribs from the marinade and bake or broil, baste spareribs all the while with the marinade.
Serve hot.

title: pasta primavera
directions: In saucepot, prepare spaghetti as label directs; drain.
Return spaghetti to saucepot, keep warm.
Meanwhile, in 2-quart saucepan over high heat, in 1-inch boiling water, heat broccoli pieces to boiling.

Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 2 to 3 minutes, stirring occasionally, until broccoli is tender-crisp; drain. While broccoli is cooking, in 12-inch skillet, over high heat, in hot olive oil or salad oil, cook mushrooms, onion and carrot, stirring frequently, until vegetables are golden and tender-crisp. Add red pepper strips and cook, stirring until vegetables are tender.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add 1 egg and pumpkin.
Sift together flour, soda, baking powder, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and ginger.
Add lemon juice and vanilla.
Add nuts and raisins.
On greased cookie sheet, drop by teaspoons.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Makes approximately 2 dozen.

title: stuffed eggplant
directions: Scoop middle out of eggplant.
Save shell halves.
Saute pepper, celery and onion in butter. Add raw diced eggplant.
Add ground beef. Add bread crumbs, egg and a little water.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Put mixture in shell of eggplant and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to one hour.
Top with grated cheese.

title: quick-n-easy chicken casserole
directions: Put rice, soup, water and onion soup mix in bottom of 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Mix together.
Place chicken pieces on top in single layer.
Sprinkle salt and pepper (or any favorite seasoning) over top of chicken.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: pineapple bread stuffing
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Beat well, add bread cubes and then crushed pineapple.

title: kugel
directions: Boil noodles and drain.
Beat eggs.
Add milk, sugar, vanilla and 1/2 of measured butter.
Add noodles.
Mix together.
Use remaining butter to grease 13 x 9-inch Pyrex dish.
Pour in noodle mixture.
Top with cornflakes and cinnamon sugar.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serve warm or cold.

title: hamburger stew
directions: Brown hamburger.
Drain fat from hamburger.
Add the diced potatoes, sliced carrots and diced onion to the hamburger.
Season with salt, pepper and garlic powder (not garlic salt).
Add water to just cover veggies.
Cover and simmer until veggies are tender and broth has thickened.
Serve with salad and hot rolls.

title: surprise cupcakes
directions: Mix cake according to package directions.
Fill paper bake cups in muffin pans 2/3 full.
Cream cream cheese with sugar; beat in egg and salt.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop 1 rounded teaspoonful cheese mixture into each cupcake.
Bake as package directs.
Oh so good!

title: exotic turkey salad
directions: Use turkey breast (2 1/2 to 3 pounds).
Slice or dice water chestnuts, grapes and celery.
Add 1 1/2 to 2 cups almonds.
Mix mayonnaise, curry powder and soy sauce and 2 tablespoons lemon juice, if desired.
Combine with turkey.
Chill several hours. Serve.
Spoon onto lettuce leaves; sprinkle with almonds and pineapple chunks.
Serves 25.

title: easy breakfast
directions: In large skillet, brown sausage; drain.
In large bowl, beat eggs.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Spoon into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cover; refrigerate for 8 hours or overnight. Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: calico bean hot dish
directions: Brown ground beef and saute onion together.
Drain in a colander to remove excess fat.
Combine all ingredients.
Bake in a casserole dish at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: zucchini bake
directions: Press mixture out of zucchini.
Combine all ingredients.
Top with 1/4 cup cheese.
Place in oiled 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until brown.
Serves 6.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Turn into mold and chill several hours.
Serve on crisp lettuce with a little salad dressing.

title: salsa
directions: Let tomatoes sit 1 hour; drain.
Combine all ingredients. Heat to boiling; simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.
Place in a water bath for 15 minutes.
Makes about 6 pints.

title: corn salad
directions: Drain corn and mix all together.
Use low-fat or regular Ranch salad dressing over the mixture.

title: lemon bread
directions: Cream the margarine, sugar and eggs.
Add rest of ingredients. Add nuts last.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: impossible zucchini pie
directions: Mix together the zucchini, tomatoes, onion, green peppers and grated cheese.
Pour into lightly greased pie plate.
Blend together the milk, Bisquick mix, salt and pepper.
Pour Bisquick mixture over the vegetables in the pie plate.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: almost pizza
directions: Place sliced potatoes in a greased 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish; set aside.
In a large skillet, cook ground beef.
Drain grease.
Meanwhile heat cheese soup and milk until smooth and heated.

title: veggie squares
directions: Press dough on jelly roll pan.
Bake to package directions. Mix cream cheese and mayonnaise and spread on crust.
Sprinkle on vegetables and chill.

title: fudge frosting
directions: Melt butter in pan; add remaining ingredients.
Stir over low heat until sugar dissolves.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat; beat until creamy enough to spread.

title: christmas acorn cookies
directions: Mix melted butter, sugar, vanilla and nuts together.
Add dry ingredients.
Using a teaspoonful of dough, shape to resemble an acorn.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: fiesta enchiladas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Drain 1 can of tomatoes; reserve juice.
Blend drained tomatoes into chicken; set aside.
Wrap tortillas in moist paper towels.
Place on microwave-safe plate; heat on High for 45 to 60 seconds or until warm and softened. Remove from oven; keep wrapped.
Fill each tortilla with 2 tablespoons cheese and 1/4 cup chicken mixture.
Roll up; place seam side down in a 1 x 9-inch baking dish.
Repeat with remaining tortillas.
Blend reserved juice, remaining diced tomatoes and tomato sauce together.
Pour evenly over filled tortillas; sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Cover with foil.
Bake for 30 minutes or until cheese melts and sauce bubbles.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Drain and rinse shrimp in cold water; set aside.
Warm tomato soup (just contents of can) and gelatin; set aside.
Mix cream cheese and mayonnaise until creamy.
Add shrimp, onion and celery to cream cheese mixture.
Combine tomato soup to mixture.
Grease a 1-quart mold.
Pour mixture in; refrigerate for at least 1 day to blend flavors.
Unmold; put parsley around.
Serve with crackers.

title: mama's salmon patties
directions: Mix all ingredients very well and shape into oval patties and fry until golden brown, about 10 minutes.
May also bake in oven until brown.

title: rabbit (or chicken) sauce piquante
directions: In a Dutch oven over medium heat, brown rabbits or chicken in half the oil. Remove and set aside.
Using remaining oil and flour, make a golden brown roux. Add onions, celery and bell pepper and saute.
Allow vegetables to simmer for 10 minutes. Add tomato soup, tomato sauce, tomato paste and water. Cook, uncovered, 45 to 60 minutes, stirring frequently.
Place browned meat back into sauce. Add olives, mushrooms and seasonings. Allow mixture to come to a boil, lower temperature and then simmer until meat is very tender, about 2 hours.
Add parsley and green onions the last 15 minutes of cooking time.
Serve over spaghetti or steamed rice. Makes 8.

title: gennie's never fail white cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add flour and milk alternately.
Add baking powder; fold in whites.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 350° until cake springs back when touched.

title: mama louise's bleu cheese salad dressing
directions: Remove 1 cup mayonnaise from the original jar.
Set this aside for other dishes.
In the hollowed cavity of the mayonnaise, add all the ingredients.
Cap and mix well.
It is best if allowed to stand for 24 hours.
It gets even better in 2 to 3 days.
Will last 3 to 4 weeks.

title: pineapple muffins
directions: Cream oil, butter and sugar.
Add eggs and mix.
Sift together flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add dry ingredients to sugar mixture and then add crushed pineapple with its juice, mixing until well blended.
Add vanilla.
Pour into paper lined or greased muffin pans and bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.
Yields 3 dozen muffins.

title: canned okra
directions: Cut
okra as desired; place in large pot and cover with water, salt and vinegar.	Cook just until okra changes color. Pack
in hot
jars
and
seal.
Drain and rinse before using. Excellent for frying, soups, etc.

title: raised buckwheat cakes
directions: Pour boiling water over the cornmeal and let stand until it swells.
Soften yeast in lukewarm water. After cornmeal is cool, add molasses, salt, yeast and flour.
Beat thoroughly and set in a warm place to rise overnight.
It should rise and fall again in the morning.
Add soda dissolved in hot milk.
Stir well. Bake on a hot griddle.

title: pumpkin sheet cookies
directions: Blend sugar and salad oil.
Add pumpkin and eggs and blend well; add flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon, baking powder and chopped nuts.
Mix well.
Pour onto greased jelly roll sheet pan (10 x 15-inch) and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: make-ahead mexican casserole
directions: Saute ground beef and onion until lightly browned, stirring to crumble meat.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except tortillas and cheese.
Alternately layer meat mixture and tortillas, beginning and ending with meat mixture in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover with aluminum foil; seal securely and freeze.

title: mrs. field's cookies
directions: Cream together the margarine, sugar and brown sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix together the flour, oatmeal, salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Mix together all ingredients.
Add chocolate chips, Hershey bar and chopped pecans.
Stir by hand.
Bake at 375° for 6 to 9 minutes on ungreased cookie sheets (2-inches apart).
Can drop by teaspoon or tablespoon.

title: summertime cooler
directions: Combine sugar and water; heat until sugar is dissolved.
Cool. Stir in other ingredients and serve over block of ice or frozen ring in punch bowl.
Yields 2 gallons.

title: death by chocolate(feeds up to 24, or 1 serious chocoholic!)
directions: Preheat oven according to brownie package directions.
Bake brownies according to package directions; let cool.
Prick holes in the tops of brownies with a fork and pour the coffee liqueur over brownies; set aside.

title: no bake chocolate cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook until boiling over medium heat. Take off of stove and add 1 tsp. of vanilla and 2 1/2 cups of oatmeal.
Drop onto waxed paper.
Makes about 35 to 40 pieces.

title: beef noodle casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain well.
Add sour cream, corn, soups and egg noodles.
Pour into buttered dish.
Sprinkle with 1 cup bread crumbs and 2 tablespoons butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: walnut chicken
directions: Mix 1 tablespoon oil, 2 teaspoons soy sauce and 1 teaspoon cornstarch in a small bowl.
Stir in chicken to coat.
Cover and refrigerate 30 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Melt unsweetened chocolate and shortening.
Beat in sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Sift and stir in flour, baking powder and salt. Pour in greased 6 x 6-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: sweet bread or roll dough
directions: Add 3 cups flour to the first 3 ingredients; mix well.
Add the eggs and shortening to the first mixture; beat well.
Let stand until double in bulk.
Make into rolls or buns.
Bake rolls at 400°.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni as directed, drain and cool.
Place in a bowl and add other ingredients.
Mix well.
Blend in coleslaw dressing.

title: 15 minute stroganoff
directions: Trim fat from meat and reserve.
Cut meat diagonally across grain in very thin strips.
Heat fat (or use oil) in skillet until you have 3 tablespoons.
Remove trimmings.
Brown meat.
Add 2/3 cup water and mushrooms.
Stir in soup mix.
Heat to boiling. Blend sour cream and flour.
Add to mixture.
Cook and stir until thickened.
Sauce will be thin.
Serve over noodles.
Serves 5 to 6 people.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Cook sugar, cocoa, salt, corn syrup, butter, milk and water to soft ball.
Remove from stove and add nuts and vanilla.
Place pan in cold water to aid cooling process; stir occasionally.
As candy loses its shine, pour into a buttered pie pan.
Cut candy while still a little soft.

title: deep dish coconut pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter well.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each.
Add flour and salt, then milk and vanilla.
Stir in coconut.
Pour into well buttered pie plate.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Turn off oven and let set 10 minutes in oven.

title: corn flake balls
directions: Melt sugar and Karo together on low heat until sugar is not so grainy.
Don't boil or they will be too hard to chew.
Drop out on buttered wax paper in big spoonfuls. As they cool, form into balls. Makes about 20.

title: sherry cake
directions: Beat egg yolks well.
Add sherry and 1/2 cup sugar.
Cook in double boiler until like custard.
Soak gelatin in milk and stir into hot custard.
Let cool.
Whip egg whites stiff.
Whip 1/2 pint cream into 1 cup sugar.
Fold into custard.
Crumble cake and place a layer of crumbs in bottom of a greased spring pan, alternating layers of cake and custard.
Let stand in refrigerator 12 hours.
Turn out and ice with 1/2 pint whipped cream.

title: broiler chuck roast
directions: Put beef in an oven broiling bag.
Pour mushroom soup, dry onion soup and a little salt on top. Close bag.
Punch holes in top of broiling bag.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes per pound.

title: spinach and artichoke casserole(serves 6)
directions: Combine ingredients and put in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: no crust pumpkin pie
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine pumpkin, evaporated skim milk, low cholesterol eggs and egg whites; beat until blended and smooth. Mix in sugar, cinnamon, allspice, ginger and salt, blending well. Stir in crumbs. Spray deep-dish 9-inch pie plate with nonstick cooking spray. Pour pie filling into pie plate. Bake in preheated 325° oven 45 to 55 minutes until a knife inserted near center comes out clean. Cool pie on wire rack and refrigerate overnight. Serve in wedges with small dollop of low-fat whipped topping. Makes 8 servings.

title: kentucky pecan pie
directions: In medium size pan, melt butter or margarine.
Remove from heat, stir in corn syrup and sugar.
Cool slightly.
Stir in eggs and bourbon until well mixed.

title: hamburger dressing
directions: Cook onions and celery in margarine.
Soak bread and press out the water.
Mix bread with onions and celery; add sage.
Line a 2-quart casserole dish with hamburg by patting it on sides and bottom; add dressing.
Blend soup with 1/2 can water or milk; pour over dressing.
Make dents in dressing with spoon so the soup gets through the dressing.
Bake for 45 minutes or until it bubbles up in the center.

title: date balls
directions: Combine dates, margarine, sugar and egg in heavy saucepan. Cook over low heat until thickened and creamy, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in pecans and cereal.
Shape into balls.
Roll in confectioners sugar.
Place on waxed paper. Let stand until cool.
Store in airtight container.
Yield:
32 servings.

title: crunchy boysenberry pie topping
directions: Cream first 3 ingredients together.
Fold in chopped pecans. Spoon topping over frozen pie.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes until lightly browned and bubbly.

title: easy oven baked potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes and onions into 1/4-inch slices.
Alternate slices, slightly overlapping, in a single layer in a 13 x 9x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine next 5 ingredients; drizzle over potato and onion slices.
Cover and bake at 400° for 40 minutes. Sprinkle with paprika and bake, uncovered, for 20 additional minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: In a 10-inch skillet, heat the oil and add the onion.
Cook gently until wilted.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer, stirring occasionally, for 15 minutes.
Makes 2 cups.
Store in the refrigerator.
Keeps well.

title: easy chocolate fudge
directions: Mix chocolate chips and sweetened condensed milk.
Microwave until chips are melted.
Mix in walnuts and vanilla.
Pour in a buttered 9-inch pan.
Cool and cut into serving pieces.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Beat egg slightly with fork.
Stir in all other ingredients. Pour into 1-quart baking dish.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: never fail refrigerator hot rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in warm water.
Let rise in container.
In a large pan or bowl, combine hot water, sugar, shortening and salt.
Cool and add yeast mixture, egg and flour. Blend well.
Oil top of dough and cover with dry cloth to let double in bulk.
Mash down and knead on flour covered board.
Then make into rolls of your choice.
These may be covered and stored in refrigerator until needed, or cut off desired amount and let rise and make as needed.
Will keep for a week.
Just allow extra time for chilled dough to rise.
Bake in 400° oven until golden brown.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Grease bottom of 9 X 13 in. pan. Save 1/2 c. cake mix. Beat remaining cake mix, butter, eggs and sour cream for two minutes. Spread 1/2 of batter in pan. Mix brown sugar, cinnamon, pecans and the 1/2 cup reserved cake mix. Spread over batter. Spread remaining batter over brown sugar layer. Bake
at 350 degrees for 30 minutes. Poke holes with fork in warm cake. Make icing of powdered sugar, milk and vanilla. Pour over cake and cool for one hour.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Butter casserole dish.
Layer sliced potatoes, onion and mushrooms, then sprinkle in cheese.
Make several layers, ending with cheese.
Pour soup on top.
You may dilute soup with a little water.
Cover with foil and bake at 275° to 300° for 3 hours.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Cool cake layers thoroughly. Prepare pudding mix according to package instructions. Place 1 cake layer in bottom of bowl. Add in layers, half each of the pudding, pie filling, fruit cocktail, pineapple, nuts, coconut and Cool Whip. Top with second layer and repeat layering of remaining ingredients, using some of the cherries, nuts and coconut for garnish. Store in a cool place until ready to serve. Dip through layers.

title: lo-cal marinated vegetable salad
directions: Chop raw vegetables and place in mixing bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and marinate 3 hours or more.
Makes 6 servings.
One serving equals 25 calories.

title: spinach salad with sweet and sour dressing
directions: Prepare ahead the dressing by combining the sugar, vinegar and oil to allow sugar to dissolve; mix well. Clean and tear spinach; chill. When ready to serve, add 2 to 3 sliced hard-boiled eggs and 1 can French fried onion rings. Toss with dressing and serve immediately.

title: uncooked nut fudge
directions: Put butter, milk and chocolate in saucepan and melt.
Remove and add vanilla, salt, confectioners sugar and nuts (if desired). Place in 8 x 8-inch buttered pan and chill.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix thawed lemonade mix with Eagle Brand milk.
Blend in thawed Cool Whip.
Pour in graham cracker pie crust.
Garnish with graham cracker crumbs and slice of lemon, if desired.
Allow to set in refrigerator until firm.
Very good, very rich.

title: fruit pizza pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Roll out cookie dough like a pie crust and place in a pie pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool.

title: friendship tea
directions: Combine ingredients and keep in a closed jar or container.

title: chicken jalapeno
directions: Mix chicken, Doritos and soup together.
Add onion, margarine and peppers.
Reserve some cheese to sprinkle on top.
Mix rest of cheese in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: carrot cake
directions: Place lightly packed shredded carrots, raisins, sugar, water and butter in a 3-quart saucepan and bring to a simmer over medium heat.
Continue to simmer for 5 minutes, uncovered.
Remove from heat and let cool.

title: old fashion chocolate fudge
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa until well blended.
Add cream and salt. Cook in saucepan on medium heat until hard ball forms, approximately 8 minutes of hard boiling.
Add vanilla.
Mix well. Pour onto buttered dish.
Let cool, slice into small pieces. Spread nuts over the top.

title: crumb top apple pie
directions: Butter a deep, glass pie pan.
Slice apples into pan to make a thick layer.
There is no bottom crust.
Sprinkle over apples the first 4 ingredients (sugar, butter, cinnamon and nutmeg).
Cut the chilled butter into the flour and sugar to make a crumb mixture. Spread over apples in pan, pressing gently.
Bake in a moderate 350° oven until apples are tender and pie is nicely browned.
This takes from 40 to 50 minutes, depending on apples used and their degree of ripeness.
The sugar melts down through the apples and when done, the pie can be cut in wedges.
Serve plain or with ice cream.

title: southern oven "fried" chicken(weight watchers)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray a large baking sheet with nonstick cooking spray.

title: no sugar strawberry pie
directions: In a saucepan, combine cornstarch and water until smooth. Bring to a boil; cook and stir for 2 minutes until thickened. Remove from heat; stir in gelatin until dissolved. Put sweetener over berries; stir into gelatin. Pour into crust and refrigerate for 2 hours or until firm. Garnish with reduced-fat whipped topping, if desired.

title: ham loaf
directions: Add bread crumbs, eggs and milk to meat.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 10.

title: apple 'n spice peanut butter cookies
directions: Set measured cookie mix aside while tossing together chopped apple and cinnamon.
Thoroughly mix into cookie dough.
Roll about a teaspoon of dough into ball and place on ungreased cookie sheet. Flatten with a fork.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chocolate chip bundt cake
directions: Mix the cake mix, pudding, water, oil and eggs.
Stir in sour cream and chocolate chips.
Spray Bundt pan with Pam.
Pour mixture into pan and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool slightly before removing from pan.
Very moist and sinfully delicious!

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Stew chicken; when cool, remove bones.
Arrange chicken pieces in baking dish.
Add Veg-All.
Mix soup and broth together and pour over Veg-All.
Then mix melted butter, milk and flour together.
Pour on top of chicken and Veg-All.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: roast beef yorkshire pudding
directions: Combine large bowl until consistency of thick cream. Refrigerate several hours.
When you put roast in oven, put in extra pan to heat.
Half hour before roast is done, put just enough roast pan drippings into extra pan to cover bottom.
Pan must be very hot!
Pour pudding in; roast and pudding will be done at same time.
Pudding should be high, brown, crisp and hollow inside.

title: ice cream sandwich cake
directions: Mix Cool
Whip	and cream cheese with mixer.
Layer pan with 6 ice
cream
sandwiches.
Spread
1 cup of cream cheese mixture over sandwiches. Add remaining 6 ice cream sandwiches and
top with
remaining
cream
cheese mixture. Freeze until ready to serve.

title: golden glow salad
directions: In a bowl, dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Add lemon juice and enough cold water to pineapple juice to make 1 cup.
Add salt, if desired.
Stir into gelatin.
Chill until slightly set.
Stir in pineapple and carrots.
Pour into an oiled 4-cup mold; cover and chill until firm.
Yields 6 servings.

title: apple dapple
directions: Mix all ingredients, except apples and walnuts.
Mix well, then fold in apples and walnuts.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° in tube pan.

title: marinated salad
directions: Mix vegetables in large bowl.
Mix dressing ingredients and pour over vegetables.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serve chilled.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Mix asparagus and soup.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Crumble crackers on top of cheese.
Bake in 350° oven until crackers brown.

title: crab spread
directions: Heat soup.
Dissolve gelatin in water and put into hot soup. Cool slightly.
Combine with the rest of the ingredients.
Put into mold. Chill at least overnight.
Serve with petite rye bread or pumpernickle.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix last 3 ingredients well.
Roll each biscuit in melted margarine and then in brown sugar mixture.
Place biscuits on their sides in a Bundt pan.
If any margarine or mixture is left over, pour on top of biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: barbecued meatballs
directions: Mix everything except the catsup, brown sugar, liquid smoke, 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder and 1/2 cup chopped onion.
Shape into balls.
Place in flat pan, one layer to each pan.

title: macaroni beef skillet
directions: Brown beef with onion and green pepper over medium heat in large skillet.
Pour off excess fat.
Add uncooked macaroni and remaining ingredients; mix well.
Cover; simmer 25 minutes or until macaroni is tender.
Stir occasionally; add more water if necessary.
Serve immediately.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: shrimp jambalaya
directions: Fry ham, shrimp and sausage until brown.
Add bell pepper, onion, garlic powder, parsley, bay leaves, sugar, salt, pepper, tomato sauce and Ro-Tel if desired.
Cook about 15 minutes until shrimp almost done.
Add rice and stir well.
Cook until rice is done, stirring frequently.

title: chocolate cheese balls
directions: Melt chocolate.
Add honey, goat cheese, vanilla and lemon. Cool several hours.
Form 24 small balls; roll in cocoa.

title: grapefruit pie
directions: Remove all white skin on grapefruit sections and allow fruit to drain for 5 minutes, saving juice.
Melt marshmallows with 1/4 cup grapefruit juice, over low heat in saucepan.
Remove from heat and cool, then lightly stir in grapefruit sections.
Whip cream and fold into grapefruit mixture.
Turn filling into pie shell and chill several hours before serving.
Enjoy!

title: chicken pie 2
directions: Place stewed, boned chicken in baking dish.
Add chicken soup on chicken, then add batter on top (batter is flour, milk and butter).
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: potato pie
directions: Boil potatoes.
Mash and let steam escape.
Mix all ingredients.
Grease a pie pan and fill with mixture.
Dab on top with butter.
Cook at 350° for 1/2 hour (covered with foil), then 1/2 hour uncovered.
(May wish to broil last few minutes to brown top.)

title: green limas with bacon dressing
directions: Brown bacon lightly in skillet.
Add onion and cook over low heat until tender, but not brown.
Add remaining ingredients except beans and simmer 5 minutes.
Serve over hot limas.
Makes 4 servings.

title: caesar italian pasta salad
directions: Boil water to cook noodles only for 8 to 10 minutes. Meanwhile, boil water in a small pot and then cook green beans only for a couple minutes, just until the green beans turn bright green. Drain and immediately rinse with cold water to stop the beans from cooking any longer.
(Let the beans stand in a bowl of cold water until the noodles are done so that they'll be cold enough to add to the salad.)
Wash and drain the grape tomatoes.
(You can probably use cherry tomatoes if they're small enough.)

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in ovensafe dish.
Bake covered at 325° for 1 hour.

title: green pea salad
directions: Rinse peas in hot water (steam, if fresh).
Combine vegetables, nuts and bacon with sour cream.
Mix dressing, mustard and garlic together.
Pour over salad. Toss gently.
Chill. Serves 4.

title: vegetable tempura
directions: Mix together and dip the vegetables in mixture before deep frying.

title: pan-fried venison
directions: Dip steaks into cream or milk and dredge in flour.
Brown in hot margarine and season with salt, pepper and garlic salt to taste.

title: gourmet meat loaf
directions: Drain 1/4 cup of tomato juice from tomatoes and reserve for making
sauce.
Combine
beef,
salt,
pepper, sage, eggs, cracker crumbs,
remaining tomatoes and onions.
Shape in loaf pan and bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: licuados
directions: Mix all together at your desired amounts.

title: fat free stuffed manicotti(vegetarian)
directions: Cook pasta; drain and cool in single layer on foil. In large bowl, combine spinach, 5 ounces mozzarella cheese, cottage cheese, egg whites and seasonings. Spoon about 2 tablespoons filling into each pasta tube. Heat oven to 350°. Spray 9 x 13 pan with Pam. Spread 1/4 cup of sauce mixed with with water in bottom of pan. Arrange filled pasta tubes in a single layer in pan. Pour remaining sauce over top. Cover with foil. Bake 40 minutes. Remove foil and sprinkle remaining mozzarella cheese on top. Bake 5-10 minutes until cheese has melted. Makes 7 servings.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Bake according to package directions; punch holes into hot cake and pour coconut cream over hot cake.
Refrigerate 30 minutes.
Mix Eagle Brand and lemon juice; pour over cake and refrigerate 2 hours.
Mix Cool Whip and coconut; spread over cake and refrigerate until serving.

title: dill buns
directions: Soften yeast in water, combine in mixing bowl the cottage cheese, sugar, onion, butter, dill seeds, salt, soda and egg to soften yeast.
Add flour to form a stiff dough, beating well after each addition.
Cover and let rise in warm place, 85° or 90°, until light and double in size 50 or 60 minutes.
Stir down dough into well greased sheets.
Make buns.
I use a large empty peach can for rounds.
Let buns rise and bake in 350° oven about 25 or 30 minutes.
Brush hot buns with soft butter and sprinkle with salt.

title: strawberry shortcake bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in microwave.
Let cool 5 minutes.
Mix butter with sugar and flour.
Pat 3/4 of mix in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread preserves over mixture.
Cover with remainder of mixture sprinkled over preserves.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: chunky peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Into large
bowl, measure all ingredients.
With mixer at low speed, beat ingredients until well mixed, occasionally scraping bowl.
Drop batter by level tablespoonfuls 2 inches apart onto cookie sheet.
Bake 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
With pancake turner, immediately move cookies to wire rack.
Cool.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: chocolate pie
directions: In saucepan, stir together dry ingredients; gradually add the milk.
I use one large can of milk and if not quite enough for 2 cups, add water to make 2 cups.
Place on low heat, stirring constantly, to make a smooth mixture.
Break egg yolks into a cup and beat until blended.
Add a little of warm mixture to egg yolks and then stir into mixture in pan.
Cook and continue to stir until thick.
Remove from heat; add butter and vanilla.
Stir to blend. Pour into baked pie shell.
Cover with meringue.

title: polk salad with eggs
directions: Wash
and stem polk salad.
Bring to a boil in a generous amount
of	water.	Cook about 3 minutes; pour off water. Add about 2 cups water, then cook until tender.
Strain water from greens.

title: sour cream chicken enchiladas
directions: About 1 hour before serving:
In a 13 x 9-inch pan, spread 1 cup of sour cream; set aside.
In a 2-quart saucepan, flake chicken.
Add 1/2 cup sour cream, green chilies, onion, chili powder, salt, garlic powder and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, just until heated.

title: flaky pie crust
directions: In a mixing bowl sift together flour and salt.
Cut in Crisco with pastry blender, fork or 2 knives.
Sprinkle water, 1 tablespoon at a time over flour mixture just enough to moisten. Pat dough into a ball.
Wrap in wax paper and chill.
When ready to use, divide into 2 parts and roll out.
Makes 2 (9-inch) pie crust shells.

title: super baked beans
directions: Brown onions with ground beef, drain and add to beans.
Brown bacon, drain and crumble; add to beans.
Add rest of ingredients to bean mixture and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Use a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Makes enough for 16 to 18 people.

title: southern waffles
directions: Combine flour, cornmeal, baking powder and sugar; mix well. Combine egg yolks, buttermilk, milk and butter; add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Beat egg whites (at room temperature) at high speed of an electric mixer until stiff peaks form.
Fold into batter.
Pour about 1/4 of batter into a preheated lightly oiled waffle iron.
Cook 5 minutes or until steaming stops and waffles are done.

title: chicken corn soup
directions: Have ready canned corn; sprinkle salt and cornstarch over chicken.
Set aside in small bowl; beat egg whites until foamy. Then beat in the milk; set aside.
In saucepan, boil chicken broth.
Add corn; let boil 1 minute.
Add minced chicken.
Bring to a boil and let boil 2 minutes.
Add egg whites and milk.
Stir and then remove from heat.
Add ham and serve immediately.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Mix all together; form	into
small balls.
Place balls on ungreased cookie sheet and	press
down with fork.	Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yield: 100.

title: marinated shrimp
directions: Boil shrimp in shrimp boil until done.
Peel and devein shrimp.
In a large bowl, layer shrimp and onion slices.
Mix bay leaves, salad oil, vinegar, capers and juice, celery seed, salt and Tabasco sauce together and pour over layered shrimp and onion slices.
If mixture does not cover shrimp and onion slices, fill to top with Wish-Bone Italian dressing.
Marinate 8 hours in refrigerator before serving.

title: dewberry cobbler
directions: For fresh dewberries, add enough water to make 2 cups juice. Heat to boiling; drain fruit.
Mix cornstarch and sugar into juice and cook until just thickened, stirring constantly with a wire whisk.
Add the butter, lemon juice and salt, then the drained fruit.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Drain shrimp.
Mix all ingredients together and chill overnight.

title: honey blueberry bread
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Cut in shortening (like coarse cornmeal).
Mix eggs, honey, water, coffee and lemon rind.
Add mixture to dry ingredients all at once.
Stir until just blended. Fold in nuts and berries.
Pour into well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans (2 pans).
Bake at 350° for about 55 to 65 minutes until well browned and firm to touch.

title: pimiento cheese spread
directions: Grate cheese on fine grater.
Chop pimientos and combine with cheese and moisten to spreading consistency with several tablespoons mayonnaise and milk.
This is very good on wheat crackers.

title: banana cake
directions: Sift together
dry
ingredients,
cream shortening, add sugar and eggs and
beat	until
creamy.	Add
dry ingredients alternately with mashed bananas and milk.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan that has been greased
and	floured.
Bake	in a 350° preheated oven for 50 minutes or until done.

title: doris' blueberry pudding
directions: Cream the shortening and stir in 1/2 cup sugar gradually. Sift the dry ingredients together and add alternately with the milk to first mixture.
Fold in the stiffly beaten egg whites. Add vanilla.
Mix blueberries with the remaining 1/4 cup sugar. Place in bottom of greased pudding dish.
Pour batter over them and bake
at moderate heat (350°) for 1 1/4 hours.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: mother's molasses raisin rye bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Combine yeast mixture, liquid, raisins, rye flour, oats, honey and caraway seed.
Add enough all-purpose flour (about 2 cups) to make batter of sponge consistency.
Let rise until fluffy.
Stir in molasses, oil and salt.
Add enough additional all-purpose flour, 1 cup at a time, to make workable dough.
Knead until soft and elastic.
Divide dough into 3 parts.
Form into round loaves; place on greased baking sheets.
Let rise, covered, in a warm place for 1 hour, or until doubled in bulk.

title: shrimp celery bisque
directions: Combine water with celery and diced potatoes.
Add onion, salt and a good size pinch of white pepper.
Bring the vegetables and spices to a boil in a medium sized saucepan.
Reduce the heat, cover the pan and allow the mixture to simmer for 15 minutes or until the potatoes are done.
Mix milk with all-purpose flour until smooth.
Stir the flour and milk into the vegetables.
Add shrimp.
Add butter.
Stir and cook until thickened and bubbly. Serve with a sprinkle of parsley on top.

title: refrigerator pineapple pie
directions: Fold pineapple and dry pudding into sour cream (or yogurt). Place into cooled, baked shell.
Refrigerate for 1 hour or more. Serve with whipped cream (and maybe a maraschino cherry for color!).

title: easy chicken wings
directions: Spread chicken wings on broiler pan.
Shake lemon pepper generously over wings.
Broil for approximately 8 minutes (until very brown).
Turn and repeat procedure.

title: dutch apple pie
directions: Pare and slice apples to fill a 10-inch pie pan lined with crust.
Mix sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over apples.
Cream oleo with brown sugar.
Add flour.
Spread over apples and sprinkle with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: turkey tetrazzini(microwave)
directions: In 2-quart casserole, place butter, mushrooms, onion and lemon juice.
Microwave at High 2 to 3 minutes, stirring after 1 minute. Stir in flour, salt and paprika until smooth.
Microwave at High 1 minute.
Stir well.
Gradually stir in broth.
Microwave at High 5 to 6 minutes, stirring after 3 minutes.
Mix in half and half and turkey.

title: crabmeat pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a bowl, reserving the grated cheese.
If mixture seems too thick, add a little milk.
Pour into pie shells; sprinkle grated cheese on top of pies.
Finally, sprinkle paprika on top.
Bake at 350° in preheated oven for approximately 45 to 50 minutes.
Let stand at room temperature for about 30 to 40 minutes before cutting.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or cream of shrimp soup

title: low fat cheesecake
directions: Combine cracker crumbs and margarine in bowl with 1/2 cup sugar.
Press on bottom and up 2 1/2-inches of side of 8-inch spring-form pan, set aside.
In bowl, with mixer at high speed, beat cream cheese, remaining sugar and vanilla until creamy.
Beat in egg whites.
Blend in yogurt.
Spread in pan with graham cracker crust.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes or until center is set. Turn off oven.
Leaving door slightly ajar, leave cheesecake in oven 1 hour.
Remove from oven and cool completely.
Chill 4 hours or overnight.
Remove side of pan; top with fruit.
Slice and serve.

title: manhattan clam dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and mayonnaise with mixer until smooth.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Chill.
Serve with raw vegetables or crackers.

title: casserole dill bread
directions: In a large bowl, mix 1/4 cup flour, sugar, salt, instant onion, dill seed, baking soda and undissolved yeast. Add soft margarine. Gradually add teaspoon of hot water to dry ingredients. Beat 2 minutes, scraping bowl. Add cottage cheese, egg and 1/2 cup flour to make stiff batter. Beat at high speed 2 minutes, scraping bowl. Stir in enough flour to make stiff batter. Cover. Let use 1 hour and 15 minutes. Stir batter down and turn into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole. Cover. Let rise 50 minutes. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Remove and let cool on wire rack.

title: snow fingers
directions: Mix all ingredients together to form a stiff dough.
Pinch off and roll into tiny fingers.
Bake slowly at 325° until lightly brown.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: eygee (egg souffle)
directions: Heat oil in pan.
Beat egg, mint, salt and pepper and sprinkle of water.
Beat and fry, then turn it over until done.

title: melanie frazier's watergate salad
directions: Mix pineapple (with juice) and Jell-O pudding.
Add pecans and marshmallows.
Mix well and fold in Cool Whip.
Garnish with additional pecans and/or marshmallows.
Chill well.

title: parmesan american fries
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease cookie sheet.
In a small bowl, combine cheese and salt.
Brush potato wedges with margarine. Place on cookie sheet.
Sprinkle wedges with cheese mixture to coat.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until potatoes are tender and lightly browned.
Serve warm with ketchup, or barbecue sauce or melted cheese for dipping.
Makes 32 appetizers.

title: butterfinger bars
directions: Mix the corn syrup, melted margarine and brown sugar.
Stir in the oatmeal and vanilla.
Pour into a "Pammed" or greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.
Remove from oven.
Top with the chocolate chips and peanut butter, melted together in microwave.
Let cool; cut into squares.

title: sweet vidalia onion dip spread
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl. Pour into a glass baking dish (deep pie dish or 8-inch square). Top with a generous amount of paprika (optional). Bake at 350° until golden brown on top or bubbly. Cool 3 to 4 minutes before serving. Serve on Triscuits, Ritz chips or Ritz crackers.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes.
Cut into slices like French fries.
Mix sugar, flour, water, salt, butter and cinnamon.
Bring to boil. Pour over potatoes.
Bake 45 minutes, uncovered, at 350°.

title: kentucky pioneer washday cake
directions: Cream
molasses,
butter
(shortening)	and sugar until well blended.
Combine
milk with well beaten eggs.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with egg-milk
liquid.
Stir only until smooth.	Divide batter into 6 equal
amounts
about
1 cup batter each.
Spread batter in well greased
9-inch
cake
pans.
Makes 6 layers.
Bake in a moderate oven (325°) for 12 to 15 minutes.
Stack layers with applesauce between
layers, use 3 to 4 cups applesauce sweetened
and	spiced to taste.	Serve plain or with whipped topping.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage; drain and save 2 tablespoons drippings in pan. Brown onion and celery in drippings.
Mix everything in casserole. Sprinkle with 1 cup toasted almonds.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: bonnie's pilaf
directions: Saute until tender celery, onions, mushrooms and pimentos. Add paprika, vegetable color, chicken stock and rice.
Bring to rolling boil, stirring often.
Place in casserole, cover and place in oven at 400° for 20 minutes.
Allow to sit after out of oven about 10 minutes.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Mix and form into balls. Roll in chopped pecans.

title: lime jell-o salad
directions: Stir 2 cups hot water to dissolve Jell-O.
Add 1 cup cold water to Jell-O.
Add sugar and salt.
Let Jell-O jell, and add rest of ingredients.

title: congeal salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water on stove; add marshmallows and cream cheese. Stir until dissolved (use egg beater), then remove from stove. Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Let congeal. Delicious with baked ham.

title: tangy green beans
directions: In 1-quart casserole, combine beans and water.
Microwave on High for 5 to 6 minutes or until nearly tender.
Drain.
Let stand, covered, 2 minutes.

title: fruit punch
directions: Place 1
tea
bag in 1 cup boiling water.
Steep 3 to 5 minutes.
Remove
tea bag.
Cool tea.
Combine tea with sugar, orange
juice,
pineapple juice and lemon juice.
Chill.
Just before
serving,
add ginger ale.
Place in punch cups and top with
a
cool spoonful of refreshing sherbet, any flavor, take your pick.
Makes 14 servings.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli flowerets into smaller than bite-sized pieces. Cut off tough outer layer of stalks and chop tender part into small pieces (8 cups broccoli).
In small skillet, saute bacon until crisp.
Set aside.
Slice onion lengthwise, then cut into julienne strips.
In large bowl, combine broccoli, onion, raisins and crumbled bacon.

title: my favorite chocolate chip cookie
directions: Mix everything, except the flour and chocolate chips, until creamy.
Stir in flour and chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 9 minutes.	Cookies will look like they aren't done, but take them out of the oven and allow to cool 2 minutes on cookie sheet.
Transfer onto brown paper bag to finish cooling.

title: pizza sauce
directions: Cook all vegetables until tender; add everything else.
Cook 2 hours and then seal.
Makes 25 pints.

title: chess pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add meal and vinegar; cream together until well blended.
Add eggs, one at a time, and mix well after each addition.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Pour into uncooked pastry shell and bake in a 450° oven for 10 minutes. Turn oven to 325° and cook for 24 minutes or until done.

title: rhubarb kuchen
directions: Mix together the first 7 ingredients.
Add rhubarb and mix until combined.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Combine 1/2 cup of sugar and cinnamon and sprinkle over the batter.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until done.
Can be served with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: cheddar potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes in water until tender.
Reserve 1 cup water. Drain potatoes.
In large saucepan fry bacon, drain on paper towel.
To drippings add celery, onion, mushrooms, salt and pepper; saute until tender.
In saucepan combine potatoes, "potato water," crumbled bacon, saute mixture and milk.
Heat.
Take flour and add to a small amount of milk to form paste.
Add to pan. Heat to boiling.
In individual bowls place cheese; cover with soup.
Serve.

title: summer sausage
directions: Mix all ingredients together and shape into 8 ounce logs. Wrap in plastic wrap and store in refrigerator for 24 hours.
Bake on rack in oven for 1 hour at 300°.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli and drain (don't overcook). Arrange in greased casserole dish and place chicken on top.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Pour over chicken. Sprinkle with cheese and then crumbs. Drizzle melted margarine on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes, until brown and bubbly. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch, Jell-O and water; bring to a boil. Remove from heat and cool.
Bake pie crust.
Wash and remove stems from strawberries.
Place strawberries in pie shell; pour cool liquid over berries.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.
Top with Cool Whip, if desired.

title: chicken wings bella
directions: Rinse and dry wings quickly.
Place wings in nonmetallic bowl. Pour on lemon juice; rub salt into wings.
Combine honey, oil, mustard, curry powder, soy sauce, wine and garlic.
Pour this marinade over the wings; mix at least twice.
Dissolve chicken cube in the hot water.
Place wings on rack in shallow baking pan. Pour marinade over wings.
Add 1/4 cup consomme liquid.
Dot each wing with small piece of butter.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Baste wings with pan liquid every 20 minutes.
Add the rest of consomme liquid at the end of 40 minutes and turn wings twice during cooking.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Drain pineapple and orange segments.
Mix all together.

title: tex-mex dip
directions: Peel, pit and mash avocado with lemon juice, salt and pepper. Set aside.
Combine sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning together.
Set aside.
Spread all the bean dip on a large, shallow serving dish.
Layer the remaining ingredients on the beans in this order:
avocado, sour cream mixture, scallions, tomatoes, olives, cheese.
Chill for 30 minutes and serve with tortilla chips or fresh vegetables.
May be kept in refrigerator for 2 days.

title: pea salad
directions: Tear lettuce into bite-size pieces and layer ingredients in order given.
Sprinkle crumbled bacon over all.
Mix mayonnaise with sugar and spread over salad.
Let set overnight.
Before serving, stir in cheese and mix mayonnaise into salad.

title: hot water banana chocolate cake
directions: Sift together last 4 ingredients.
Cream sugar and butter; add eggs and mashed bananas.
Add sour milk alternately with flour mixture.
Last, add 1 cup boiling water.
Batter will be very thin. Bake at 300° about 50 minutes.
Yields 3 layers, one 9 x 13-inch or a 12 cup Bundt cake.

title: saturday night special
directions: Brown meat in hot dry skillet (no fat); add beans, tomatoes and salt.
Pour half of mixture into baking dish; cover with chopped onion.
Add remaining meat mixture; cover with strips of bacon.
Sprinkle top with brown sugar (optional).
Bake 1 hour at 375°.
Serves 6.

title: taco dip
directions: Spread each of the ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: easy cherry salad
