directions: Mix cherry pie filling, crushed pineapple, milk and pecans well. Fold in Cool Whip and chill. Makes a large salad and freezes well. Easy for children to make.

title: date triangles
directions: Grease 7-inch square shallow baking pan.
Place dates, walnuts and water in a saucepan and cook gently until soft enough to spread.
Place oats, flour and sugar in a bowl and add margarine. Mix until fat is absorbed.
Put half the cookie mixture into the pan and press well down.
Cover with the date mixture.
Cover with reserved half of cookie mixture, crumble if desired.
Bake for 55 minutes in a 350° oven.
When cool, cut into triangles.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli (not too done).
Stir in 1 can mushroom soup. Put in casserole dish; sprinkle
with plenty of cheese and bake in moderate oven, 350°, for about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine ingredients, except chips.
Sprinkle with chips.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix well.
Form small balls and roll in chopped pecans.

title: fried dill pickles
directions: Drain pickles, reserving 2 tablespoons pickle juice. Press pickles between layers of paper towels. Set aside. Pour oil to depth of 3-inches into a Dutch oven; heat to 370°. Combine flour and next 3 ingredients in a medium bowl. Stir in club soda and reserved 2 tablespoons pickle juice, stirring just until combined. (Batter will be lumpy.) Dip pickles into batter, letting excess drip off. Fry pickles, in batches, 2 1/2 minutes or until golden brown. Drain on wire racks over paper towels and serve immediately.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients; press in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
In a large mixing bowl, mix eggs, oleo and powdered sugar.
Beat no less than 15 minutes and spread over crust.
Cover the top of the cake with sliced bananas.
Spread crushed pineapple over this.
Cover with Cool Whip and top with nuts and cherries.
Chill.

title: kraut dumplins
directions: Boil the pork.
Cut into small pieces and leave in broth. When done, add the sauerkraut and mix well.

title: grilled chicken pasta
directions: Thaw out desired amount of chicken and cut into bite size pieces. Cook desired amount of pasta according to directions; rinse. Thaw vegetables; set aside. Mix chicken, pasta and vegetables; stir in Italian dressing, enough to coat. Sprinkle Nature's Seasons and toss. Enjoy warm or cold.

title: ritz pork chops
directions: Dip pork chops in beaten egg; coat with crumbs.
Brown on both sides in oil in skillet.
Arrange in single layer in a 9 X 13-inch pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: "easy" key lime pie
directions: Prepare a graham cracker crust, mixing chopped pecans with other ingredients.
Mix together by hand.
Pour mixture into crust.
Chill 2 or 3 hours before serving.
Just before serving, cover top of pie with Cool Whip and sprinkle with coconut.

title: shaker corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Once or twice during baking, stir pudding.

title: easy salisbury steak
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Shape into patties.
Brown on both sides in a small amount of oil.
Drain well.
Stir in soup and 1/2 soup can of water.
Simmer covered for several minutes.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Heat applesauce and add soda.
Sift flour with spices.
Add to mixture alternately with applesauce.
Add dates, etc.
Use Pam/Baker's Joy to grease tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.

title: honey dijon chicken
directions: Mix together honey and mustard.
Coat chicken breasts with mixture.
Roll in bread crumbs and place in shallow baking dish. Sprinkle with parsley.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven.
Brush melted butter on chicken and bake an additional 15 minutes.

title: three bean salad
directions: Combine beans, green pepper and onion in a large bowl and toss lightly.
Combine remaining ingredients, except onion slices, and pour over tossed vegetables.
Cover and refrigerate overnight. Garnish with onion slices. Yields 10 servings.

title: dill pickles
directions: Keep vinegar and water stirred.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Put cucumbers in jars, then add spices.
Pour boiling vinegar-water and salt mixture over cukes.
Seal good.

title: venison tips
directions: Brown beef in shortening in a 12-inch skillet.
Stir in consomme, cranberry juice, soy sauce, garlic and onion salt. Bring mixture to a boil, then simmer, covered, for 1 hour or until tender.
Stir in mushrooms.
Combine cornstarch and water in cup; gradually add to meat mixture.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture is thickened and bubbly.
Boil for 1 minute.
Serve on hot rice or noodles.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: nuts and bolts party mix
directions: Mix cereals, pretzels and nuts in large container; pour mixture into 3 large baking pans.
Sprinkle with celery and garlic salts, then sprinkle with margarine and Worcestershire sauce, combined.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour.

title: hearty chicken noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles as pkg. directs; drain.
Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
In large skillet over medium heat cook celery, green peppers, and onion in butter until tender.
Stir in soup and milk, then chicken, cheese and pimento.
Cook and stir until cheese melts.
Remove from heat.
Stir in noodles.
Spoon into greased 13x9 in. baking dish.
Top with crumbs.
Bake uncovered 35 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter in casserole dish; mix in all ingredients, except fruit.
Pour fruit over batter.
Do not stir!
Bake at 450° for 30 minutes.
Batter will rise over fruit.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together.
Add water and mayonnaise. Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: miss wanda's biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients; let stand for 10 minutes.
Drop with tablespoon onto lightly greased sheet.
Bake at 425° until brown on bottom.
Broil if necessary at the end to brown tops.

title: egg salad
directions: Peel eggs and mash; mix with mayo, pickle relish, salt and pepper.

title: iced lemon butter bars
directions: Prepare oven to 350°.
Combine 1 1/3 cups sifted flour, 1/4 cup sugar and butter in bowl.
Blend until dough forms a ball.
Pat into ungreased 9-inch square baking pan.
Bake 15 minutes.
Combine eggs, remaining 3/4 cup sugar, 2 tablespoons flour, lemon peel and lemon juice in bowl; blend well.
Pour over partially baked crust. Bake 18 to 20 minutes or until filling is set.
Sift confectioners sugar over top.
Cool in pan on wire rack.
Cut into bars.

title: "english pea casserole"
directions: Drain peas and asparagus using 1/2 of each ingredient. Put a layer of peas, asparagus, sliced boiled eggs and sprinkle with 1/2 of pimento. Then add 1/2 of mushroom soup. With remaining half, follow the steps again. Sprinkle cracker crumbs over the top. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Mix all ingredients in pan and heat until bubbly.
Prepare dumplings and place sealed edges down in soup mixture.
Spoon soup over dumplings.
Cover tightly and cook over medium heat 15 to 20 minutes, until no longer doughy.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, coloring, water, vanilla and salt, mixing well after each.
Add
a
mixture
of the soda and vinegar.
Add sifted
flour and buttermilk alternately. Bake in 2 (9-inch) layer or 9
x
13-inch loaf pan at 350°.
Cool and ice with Vanilla Cream Cheese Icing.

title: sunny apple cider
directions: In Dutch oven, combine all ingredients.
Cook over medium heat until heated through and flavors are blended (about 15 minutes). To keep cider warm, hold in crock-pot on low.

title: arizona chili
directions: Soak dry beans in water overnight.
Save ground beef and drain off excess fat.
Add chopped onion, tomato puree and the soaked beans.
Mix chili powder and cumin.
Add to bean mixture.
Bring to a boil; turn down heat and cook slowly until onion and beans are tender, adding water if needed, and salt to taste.

title: tasty sausage tidbits
directions: Shape sausage into 1-inch balls.
Place on rack.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until done.
Mix remaining ingredients. Heat just until cheese has melted, stirring occasionally.
Pour sauce over sausage balls.
Garnish with grated cheese and coarse black pepper, if desired.
Yield: about 100 sausage balls.

title: deep south hush puppies
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add beaten egg, onion, buttermilk and sugar.
Mix well.
Melt enough shortening in a saucepan or deep skillet to make it 2 1/2-inches deep.
Drop batter by teaspoon into hot (350° to 380°) oil.
Fry 4 to 6 hush puppies at a time. Cook until golden brown on both sides.
Drain on brown paper.

title: applesauce cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream margarine and sugars. Add eggs and beat well. Add applesauce and then all sifted dry ingredients. Beat until smooth. Add chopped nuts and raisins. Bake in a tube or bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 45-60 minutes. Sift powdered sugar on top if desired. Yield 12 to 14 servings.

title: chocolate drops
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop on cookie sheet and bake at 350°. Frost while warm.

title: never fail custard pie
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, salt and vanilla.
Add scalded milk and pour into pastry lined tin.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake 10 minutes in a 450° oven, then 10 minutes in 425° oven until filling is set.

title: peanut butter fingers
directions: Mix all ingredients except chocolate chips, peanut butter, confectioners sugar and milk.
Bake in greased pan at 350° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle chocolate chips on mixture.
Mix rest of ingredients and spread on top.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix well and form in small balls.
Place on cookie sheet and freeze.
Place in plastic bags in freezer until needed.
Bake frozen in preheated 375° oven for 20 minutes.
These are perfect with any meal.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Bake brownies according to directions.
When warm, poke holes with a fork in brownies and pour on Kahlua.
Make pudding according to directions.
In a very large bowl, layer the following:
1/2 brownie mixture (broken into bite sizes), 1/2 chocolate pudding, 1/2 candy (broken into pieces) and 1/2 Cool Whip.
Repeat layers.
Reserve 1 tablespoon candy bar pieces to sprinkle on top; refrigerate.
A very tasty dessert.

title: calico beans
directions: Mix; bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: tropical cake
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine the cake and pudding mixes, oil and eggs. Beat on low speed until smooth. Add soda. Beat on medium speed for 2 minutes. Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2 baking pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes until toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean. Place on wire rack.

title: pineapple frozen yogurt salad
directions: Blend cream cheese and sugars.
Stir in yogurt, pineapple and pecans.
Pour into 9-inch square pan (or molds) and freeze.
To serve, cut into squares and place on lettuce cups.

title: lemon cake
directions: Prepare cake as directed on package.
Pour into prepared pan (greased and floured) Bundt pan.
Bake 350 degrees for 40 minutes or until wooden toothpick inserted into center comes out clean.

title: salmon ball
directions: Mix all ingredients, except parsley.
Shape the mixture into ball.
Cover and refrigerate at least 8 hours.
Coat ball with chopped parsley.
Garnish with pimiento, if desired.
Serve with crackers.
Serves 12 people.

title: international casserole
directions: Mix first four ingredients together.
Add soup and water.
Put in casserole (greased) and sprinkle with nuts and potato chips. Bake at 325° for about 1 hour.
Extra nice if crab or shrimp are used in place of tuna.

title: five cup salad
directions: Drain the pineapple and oranges.
Gently mix together as much of certain things as you desire.

title: enchiladas
directions: Brown and drain hamburger; add chili and heat thoroughly.
Add catsup.
On each tortilla, place about 3 tablespoons meat mixture and 2 tablespoons cheese.
Roll up and place in casserole dish. Add water to remaining meat mixture and pour over enchiladas.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 30 to 45 minutes until hot.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: zebra pudding
directions: Dip cookies in milk.
Layer in a casserole dish; layer Cool Whip over cookies.
Continue layers until dish is full. Refrigerate overnight.

title: mincemeat cookies
directions: Sift together flour, salt and soda. Cream shortening. Add sugar gradually. Cream together until fluffy. Add eggs. Beat until smooth. Stir in mincemeat. Gradually add flour mixture, mixing well. Add pecans last. Drop by teaspoons, 2-inches apart on greased baking sheet. Bake in moderately hot oven at 400° about 12 minutes.

title: rhubarb cheesecake pie
directions: Mix the 1/2 cup sugar with flour and rhubarb.
Turn onto the baked pie crust and bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Beat the softened cream cheese with the remaining 1/2 cup
sugar until fluffy.
Beat in eggs one at a time until creamy smooth.
Pour over the hot rhubarb layer and continue baking at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from the oven and spread immediately with the following: 1 cup sour cream, 1 teaspoon vanilla, 2 tablespoons sugar.
Blend thoroughly; spread over hot pie and chill.
May be served with whipped cream.

title: sensational double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and 1 tablespoon half and half with whisk until smooth.
Gently stir in Cool Whip.
Spread on graham cracker crust and set aside.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: Cook beef, salt, pepper, bouillon cubes and onion until beef is tender.
Add mixed vegetables and potatoes.
Continue cooking until potatoes are tender.
Add tomato soup and continue cooking until soup is well blended.

title: bowers' best bubbles
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Can be used right away, but better if allowed to set overnight.
Put in large tub.
Blow bubbles through a funnel, straw or an old thread spool.
Also, use hangers bent into a circle.

title: bamee(okra)
directions: Wash okra; cut off tops of stem.
Fry or broil okra in a small amount of butter or oil.
Brown lamb in butter.
Add water, spices, tomato sauce and garlic.
Cook slowly in covered saucepan until meat is tender, stirring occasionally.
Add browned okra, juice of lemon and cook slowly 5 minutes.
Serve with rice (Shiriah).

title: cornbread salad
directions: Bake cornbread following directions on cornbread mix box.
Cool and crumble up a bowl.

title: crockery cooker beans
directions: Place beans in enough boiling water to cover.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Drain.
Then combine beans, 6 cups of water and salt in crock-pot and cook on low 12 hours.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook 6 more hours.
Serves 6.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Boil sugar, water and Karo syrup until it reaches 240°.
Add peanuts and boil until 300°.
Remove from heat and add butter, salt and vanilla.
Add soda and quickly spread on 2 cookie sheets.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Stir in beef and next 6 ingredients.
Saute 5 minutes.
Add soup; simmer, uncovered 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream, add parsley.
Makes 4 to 6 servings. Serve over mashed potatoes, rice or noodles.

title: hash brown quiche
directions: Mix first four items in skillet, cook over medium heat until water is absorbed.
Press into ungreased 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes.
Combine cooked bacon, cheese, and green pepper.
Spoon over crust.
In small bowl beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over all.
Reduce heat to 350°.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Allow to stand 10 minutes before cutting.
Serves 6.

title: beet pickles
directions: Make liquid mixture with vinegar, water, brown sugar, white sugar and salt.
Bring to a boil.
Take 6 or 7 pounds of beets and cook in a hot water bath until skins come off easily.
Cut up and put in jars.
Pour liquid mixture over beets and seal.

title: e z casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Defrost and drain frozen broccoli. Grease large casserole dish or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine all ingredients.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pork chop-potato casserole
directions: Grease a large casserole dish.
Place potato slices, onion slices and cheese in layers on bottom of casserole dish.
Sprinkle each layer lightly with flour, salt and pepper.
Pour enough milk over layers to fill 1-inch deep.
Top with pork chops.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes, until pork chops are browned.

title: swiss steak
directions: Pound mixture of flour and salt into round steak.
Heat a small amount of shortening in skillet and brown meat.
Place meat in a baking dish.
Add 2 tablespoons flour to drippings in skillet and blend.
Add remaining ingredients except cheese and cook until mixture boils while stirring constantly.
Pour mixture over meat. Cover and bake in a 350° oven for 2 hours.
Top with cheese and bake until cheese melts.

title: zucchini lasagna(microwave cooking)
directions: Place zucchini in baking dish.
Add water.
Cook on High 6 to 7 minutes.
Drain and set aside.
Crumble beef into 2-quart mixing bowl.
Cook on High 4 minutes, stirring halfway through cooking time.
Pour off drippings.
Combine tomato sauce, mushrooms, onion, garlic, basil, oregano, thyme, salt and pepper.
Cook on High 6 to 8 minutes.
Stir halfway through cooking time.

title: tropical tuna melt
directions: Thoroughly drain pineapple, reserving 1 teaspoon juice.
Stir together the reserved juice, salad dressing and mustard.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes until done.
Drain off most of broth.
Add onions, celery and carrots while potatoes cook.
When potatoes are done, add cream of celery and cream of mushroom soups and milk.

title: christmas cheese ball
directions: Beat
cheeses,	milk,
Worcestershire
sauce, salts and olives until smooth.
Shape into a ball or cone; roll in dried beef. Wrap
in foil; chill in refrigerator for several hours. Serve with assorted crackers.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Stir quick oats into water and set aside.
Cream sugars and butter.
Add hot oats.
Add unbeaten eggs and vanilla.
Mix flour, salt, soda, cocoa and cinnamon.
Add alternately with oat mixture. Blend well after each addition.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam and pour batter into pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: lemonade cake
directions: Beat eggs and oil.
Add cake mix and beat well.
Dissolve Jell-O in warm water.
Add Jell-O and extract to cake mixture and beat well.
Line tube pan with wax paper at bottom.
Pour well beaten mixture in greaseless pan.
Cook 1 to 1 1/4 hours at 325°.

title: easy strawberry shortcake
directions: Mix gel and strawberries together.
Tear cake in little pieces.
Put strawberry mixture on top of cake.
Spread Cool Whip on top.

title: beef jerky
directions: Trim all fat from meat.
Semi-freeze meat and slice with the grain making strips 2 inches long and 1/2 inch wide.
Place meat in shallow baking dish.
Combine all other ingredients and pour over meat:
marinate overnight.
Preheat oven to 140° to 150°. Lay strips of meat in single layer on oven rack with baking sheet or foil underneath to catch drippings.
Leave oven door open a crack and bake 8 to 10 hours, or until meat is chewy.
Test by tasting occasionally.
Serve as appetizers or snacks.
Store in plastic bag or airtight container on pantry shelf.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Cut spareribs in pieces and brown well in a large pan in oven for 30 minutes at 400°, turning once. Combine ingredients and pour over ribs.
Cover and bake 2 hours in a 350° oven. Spoon sauce over ribs 2 to 3 times during baking.
Uncover the last 1/2 hour.

title: fudge cake
directions: Heat the chocolate and water in a saucepan until thick.
Add 1/2 cup sugar; continue cooking for 2 minutes.
Cool to lukewarm. Sift together the cake flour, soda and salt.
Cream the shortening.
Gradually add 1 1/4 cups sugar; cream until fluffy. Add the eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Beginning and ending with dry ingredients, add the milk to the creamed mixture.
Beat well after each addition.
Add cooled chocolate mixture.
Bake in a 350° oven until tests done.

title: strawberry shortcut cake
directions: Generously grease bottom only of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle marshmallows evenly over bottom.
Combine strawberries and juice with jello.
Set aside.
Combine all other ingredients.
Beat for 3 minutes.
Pour batter evenly over marshmallows.
Spoon strawberry mixture evenly over batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: brunch eggs
directions: Grate cheese.
Brown and drain sausage.
Place croutons in a greased oblong baking dish.
Sprinkle cheese and sausage over croutons.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour into baking dish. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until set.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: bread pudding
directions: Place bread in lightly greased 9 x 13 pan. Add milk and let stand for 10 minutes.
Blend mixture well, using your hands. Stir in eggs and next 5 ingredients. Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes. Raisins may also be added to this recipe.
Top with custard of your choice.

title: oriental-style broccoli
directions: Cut chicken into thin slices 2 inches long by 1/4 inch wide. Heat the oil until very hot, add chicken and saute very quickly, stirring constantly.
Add the broccoli and season with salt and pepper.
Combine the rest of the ingredients and pour over the chicken and broccoli.
Combine well.
Bring to a boil and simmer for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Serve with brown rice.
Serves 6.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger; add taco seasoning mix according to directions.
Cool.
Layer chips (may want to crush into smaller pieces) in a 9 x 13-inch pan (approximately), then meat mixture, salsa, lettuce, tomatoes and last the cheese.
You can serve as is or put under broiler to melt cheese.

title: crawfish etouffee
directions: Heat oil over low heat in heavy pot; gradually add flour and stir constantly until a medium brown roux is formed.
Add green pepper, onion, celery and garlic and continue cooking until glazed and tender.
Add crawfish tails, green onion tops, parsley, pepper, lemon juice, picante sauce, salt and sugar.
Mix well. Add water and bring to boil.
Lower heat and simmer for 15 minutes or until crawfish are tender.
Add beef broth to make gravy. Serve over boiled rice.
Serves 10.

title: cajun seasoning
directions: Mix all of the ingredients and store in a tightly covered shaker container.
Use on meat, poultry, fish and vegetables. Makes 1 cup.

title: company bread
directions: Trim crust on top and sides of bread; don't trim bottom.
Cut X's in the bread without cutting into the bottom (XXXXX).
Fill the X's with shredded Swiss or Cheddar.
Place bread in foil boat. Melt margarine on low heat.
Add mustard, onion, poppy seed, lemon juice and garlic.
Pour over bread.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: lasagne
directions: Cook noodles.
Brown meat and drain.
Combine meat with Ragu sauce and cottage cheese.
Layer noodles, then sauce, then cheese. End with cheese.
Make 2 layers of each.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: nutcracker pie
directions: Beat egg whites foamy with cream of tartar.
Add sugar and beat until stiff.
Add baking powder and beat.
Fold in nuts and graham cracker crumbs.
Pour into greased 9 or 10-inch pie plate. Bake at 350° for 3 minutes.
Cool and top with whipping cream. Grate and shave two Heath bars on top.
(Freeze bars and they will shave easier.)

title: mandarin pie
directions: Use brownie mix for chewy brownies.

title: cheese 'n' bacon ball
directions: Combine cheeses with bacon and onion in a large bowl.
Cover and chill for 1 hour.
Shape into a ball.
Combine reserved bacon and nuts.
Roll ball in bacon/nut mixture.
Chill several hours to blend flavors.
Serve with crackers.

title: donna's pineapple cheese cake
directions: Spread pineapple on top of cooled cake.
Spread whipped topping on top of pineapple.
Sprinkle coconut and nuts on top of whipped topping.
Freeze overnight.
Defrost about 3 hours before serving.

title: vanilla custard for cream pies
directions: Stir the first 3 ingredients together in saucepan.
Blend the milk and egg yolks.
Gradually stir into sugar mixture.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thickens and boils.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Blend in butter and vanilla. Immediately pour into baked shell.
Press plastic wrap onto filling.
Chill at least 2 hours.

title: watergate cake
directions: Combine first six ingredients, beat 4 minutes at medium speed. Pour batter into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: vegetable salad mold-knox gelatine
directions: Heat together the first 4 ingredients.
Add cabbage, carrots, celery and salt.
Mix and pour into mold.
Cool until firm.

title: squash pie
directions: Wash, slice and cover squash in water.
Cook until tender; drain off water.
Mash squash thoroughly and mix in rest of ingredients.
Place in unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° until a knife stuck in middle comes out clean or until top is golden brown.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash and onion in water until tender.
Drain. Mash and drain again.
Add butter, eggs, milk and seasoning.
Blend well. Pour into greased 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Top with cheese and cracker crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies(granny roberts' recipe)
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, salt, baking powder and cinnamon. Mix in oats and raisins.
Combine egg, milk, flavoring and fat; add to first mixture.
Stir only until ingredients are moistened. Drop dough by teaspoonfuls onto greased baking sheets.
Bake at 375° for about 20 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.
These are the old fashion soft cookies.
They are better if made with real butter.

title: icebox pie
directions: Beat cream cheese with powdered sugar.
Add vanilla and Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Add nuts.
Pour into graham cracker crust and top with 1 can of blueberry or cherry pie filling.
Chill.

title: reese's cup peanut candy
directions: Melt butter and add peanut butter; mix until smooth.
Add sugar and form into balls.
Melt 3/4 block wax and 3 (6 ounce) bags chocolate chips and dip.

title: california chicken
directions: Shake chicken in flour and spices.
Brown in frypan.
Pour in some of the wine.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Add more wine.
When chicken is tender, add mushrooms and onions (approximately 20 to 25 minutes).

title: 7-up cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
In a separate bowl, mix other ingredients.
Combine the two.
Use a heavy Bundt pan.
Bake at 375° until done, approximately 1 hour.
Use the toothpick.

title: meat loaf
directions: Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes before slicing.

title: corn relish
directions: Cook vegetables in 1 quart of vinegar for 15 minutes after it reaches boiling point.
Mix together dry ingredients.
Add gradually other quart of vinegar.
Bring to a boil, stirring.
Can hot.

title: ladyfinger candy
directions: Melt butter.
Mix with all ingredients.
Shape into balls or squares.

title: fig cookies
directions: Cook figs with water, stirring frequently, until thickened, about 5 minutes.
Set aside to cool.
Beat butter with both sugars until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg and vanilla to blend well. Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix into creamed mixture, then stir in cooled figs.
Drop by teaspoon 2 inches apart on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: snow ice cream
directions: We would make this usually after the first big snow. The first thing we had to do was make sure Mom didn't have plans for the cream.
Boy that could cause trouble if we used all or too much of the cream.

title: crab puffs
directions: Blend all ingredients in bowl.
Spread on English muffins. Cut in 1/4's.
Freeze on tray.
When frozen, move to Ziploc bag. To serve:
Broil until hot and bubbly.

title: french cherry pie
directions: Mix pudding,
milk, sour cream and almond extract.
Put into pie shell.
Spoon cherries on top of pie.

title: cherry winks
directions: Crush corn flakes into crumbs.
Sift together dry ingredients. Measure margarine and sugar into mixing bowl.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and beat well.
Stir in milk and vanilla.
Add sifted dry ingredients together with nuts, dates and finely cut cherries.
Mix until combined.
Shape tablespoons of dough into balls.
Roll balls in crushed flakes.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Top each with a cherry quarter.
Bake at 375° for about 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove immediately from sheet. Yields 6 dozen (2-inch) cookies.

title: cabbage lasagna
directions: Boil cabbage until tender and cool.
Break leaves apart. Combine all cheeses and egg; mix well.
Brown meat and add sauce. In baking pan, alternate sauce, cabbage, cheeses and meat to fill pan.
Bake at 350° until bubbly, about 30 minutes.

title: quick yeast biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in the 1/2 cup water.
Add mix and egg; mix well.
Turn out on floured board and knead 5 minutes.
Pat with hands to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with biscuit cutter and put on greased cookie sheet.
Let raise in warm place until double.
Bake at 400° until lightly browned.

title: pineapple pickle
directions: Drain juice from pineapple and add to vinegar, brown sugar and spices.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add pineapple and simmer 15 more minutes.
Chill and serve.

title: german caraway meatballs
directions: Combine ground beef, salt, pepper and poultry seasoning, bread crumbs, milk, parsley and egg; mix lightly.
Shape into twenty-four 1 1/2-inch balls.
Brown in pan or oven.
Add condensed beef broth, mushrooms and chopped onion.
Blend sour cream mixture.
Stir into meatballs.
Bring to a boil and cool five minutes.
Serve with potatoes or noodles.

title: microwave no fail fudge
directions: Combine sugar, butter and milk in a buttered glass mixing bowl. Cover with plastic wrap.
Microwave on Roast for 10 minutes.
Stir and continue on Roast for 5 or 6 minutes or until mixture forms a soft ball in cold water.
Stir in chocolate chips until melted. Fold in Marshmallow Creme, nuts and vanilla.
Pour into a buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
Chill and cut into pieces.
Makes about 72 squares.

title: sour dough starter
directions: Soften yeast in 1/2 cup warm water.
Stir in flour, 2 cups water and sugar.
Beat until smooth.
Cover and let stand at room temperature until bubbly.
This may take more than one day, so stir 2 or 3 times daily, then refrigerate.
This needs to be renewed every 4 to 10 days.

title: bran muffins
directions: Combine the ingredients in a stone crock or glass pottery bowl.
Beat well.
Cover with cheesecloth and follow directions.

title: pineapple icebox dessert
directions: Line a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan with half of the wafer crumbs.
In a bowl, cream the butter and sugar well. Add beaten egg yolks slowly.
Mix well.
Spread butter, sugar and egg mixture over crumbs. (Be sure to seal well so pineapple juice will not drain through to crumbs.)
Drain pineapple well and spread over butter mixture. Whip the cream and spread over the pineapple.
Sprinkle chopped pecans over the cream. Spread remaining half of the wafer crumbs on top.
Let stand in icebox 24 hours or at least overnight.
Cut into squares and top with whipped cream and cherry, if desired.

title: apple-green grape pie
directions: Bake 45 minutes at 400°.

title: cabbage stroganoff
directions: In a large heavy skillet, heat drippings or oil.
Saute onions until limp.
Add beef and cook until browned.
Add cabbage and 3/4 cup water.
Cover and simmer over medium heat until cabbage is wilted.
Sprinkle with onion soup mix and stir, mixing thoroughly. Add mushroom soup.
Rinse can with remaining water and add to skillet.
Stir in sour cream.
Cover and simmer over low heat until cabbage is tender (30 to 45 minutes).
Serve plain or with mashed potatoes, rice or noodles.

title: fruit slush punch
directions: Mash bananas, adding lemon juice.
Dissolve sugar in water. Add bananas and juices to sugar water.
Freeze.
Two hours before serving, remove from freezer.
To 2 quarts of frozen mixture, add 16 ounces ginger ale.
Stir until punch is slushy.
Serves 12.

title: stuffed chicken breast
directions: Salt and pepper chicken.
Stuff hollow of breast with dried beef.
Roll 1 slice of bacon around to hold together.
Mix sour cream and soup together.
Pour mixture over chicken.
Bake at 250° for 3 hours or 350° for 2 hours covered.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Keep in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: colorful coleslaw
directions: Combine first seven ingredients in a bowl and set aside.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Sift together first four ingredients.
Add butter and blend with 2 knives or pastry blender.
Save some candied fruit for decoration.
Measure and mix coconut, raisins and candied fruit. Add to flour mixture.
Mix well.
Beat egg whites stiff but not dry.

title: dreamy vanilla ice cream
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, flour and salt in blender container. Blend well. Heat milk to lukewarm in a large saucepan. Gradually add about 1 cup of warm milk to egg mixture, blending constantly. Stir egg mixture into remaining warm milk. Cook over low heat for 5 minutes, stirring constantly, until slightly thickened. Remove from heat and stir in sweetened condensed milk and vanilla. Pour custard into freezer can of 1-gallon hand-turned or electric freezer. Stir in half and half. Freeze ice cream according to manufacturer's directions. Yields 1 gallon.

title: smothered steak
directions: Cut round steak into pieces.
Cut onion into cubes.
Combine flour, salt, pepper and paprika.
Dredge steak in flour mixture. Add Worcestershire sauce to dissolved bouillon cube in 1 cup water. Layer round steak, alternating with onion and mushrooms in a crock-pot.
Pour liquid over steak, onion and mushrooms.
Cook on low for 8 hours.

title: western snapper
directions: Cut fish in serving size pieces, if necessary. On plate, combine oregano, chili powder, cayenne, flour, cornmeal and salt. On another plate, mix melted butter and lemon juice.
Dip fish into butter mixture first, then press in cornmeal mix.
Place in lightly buttered dish.
Pour any remaining butter over fillets. Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes, until fish flakes when touched.

title: watergate cake
directions: Mix altogether and beat for about 2 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Boil sugar, syrup and water until soft ball; then add peanuts and stir until they turn yellow (about 15 minutes).
Remove from heat and stir in salt, soda and butter; then pour out immediately.

title: super chicken soup
directions: Bring water, chicken, carrots, celery, onion, bouillon cubes and salt to boil in large saucepot.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 15 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken; cool slightly.
Cut chicken into bite size pieces and return to pot.
Add peas and corn; bring to a boil.
Add noodles and reduce heat to low.
Simmer, uncovered, 8 minutes or until noodles are tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: meliton casserole
directions: Chop fine the bell peppers, onions, green onions, parsley and garlic.
Fry in margarine until transparent.
Add cleaned shrimp. Cook for 5 minutes.
Add pulp from cooked meliton (about 8 cups). Continue to cook.
Add Progresso bread crumbs.
Pour in baking dish and bake at 400° until done.
Boil melitons before peeling, until a fork can pierce.

title: chicken almond a casserole
directions: Heat together mushroom soup and milk.
Drain noodles and put in well-greased casserole.
Mix chicken, 1/2 of almonds, 1/2 of green onions, 1/2 of olives, salt, pepper and curry powder into soup and pour over noodles, mixing well.
Put rest of onions, olives and almonds on top.
Bake 40 minutes in 350° oven.

title: black cherry dessert
directions: Make Jell-O according to directions.
Put in refrigerator for 1 1/2 hours.
Add drained cherries and mix together.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: texas quiche
directions: Cut and remove the seeds from the chillies. Line baking dish with chillies; sprinkle cheese on top.
Pour beaten eggs and salt over cheese.
Bake 25 minutes or until set.
Let cool for 30 minutes; cut into small squares.
This is good served warm or cold and freezes well.

title: sweet salad
directions: Open cream cheese to soften 45 minutes before starting salad. Drain fruit.
In saucepan, melt marshmallows in 4 tablespoons water, stirring constantly, over low heat.
Next, add small pieces of cream cheese to marshmallows, stirring constantly over low heat with hand beater; beat until smooth.
Add fruit; blend and add pinch of salt.

title: mushrooms florentine
directions: Brown mushrooms; set aside.
Use a shallow 10-inch casserole dish; line with spinach which has been seasoned with salt and pepper, onion and melted butter.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup grated cheese.
Arrange the mushrooms over the spinach.
Season with garlic salt.
Cover with remaining cheese.
Bake for 20 minutes, until cheese is melted and browned.

title: chili: with or without beans
directions: Start meat slowly in heavy pot.
If meat is very lean add 1/4 cup olive oil, stirring occasionally until meat loses red color. Add bay leaves and water (more water can be added anywhere along the line).
Cook on simmer for an hour, covered.

title: boneless chicken
directions: Cut chicken into small pieces.
Wrap with bacon.
Cut up beef. Put in bottom of casserole.
Lay wrapped chicken on top of beef. Mix remaining together.
Spread over chicken.
Bake in slow oven (300°) for two hours.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: spinach supreme
directions: Cook and drain spinach.
Add other ingredients.
Bake in a greased casserole at 325° for 30 minutes, covered, then 15 more minutes uncovered.

title: cheese-olive balls
directions: Blend cheese and butter.
Sift flour, salt and paprika.
Mix flour and cheese mixture until well combined.
Wrap small amount around each well drained olive.
Roll in hand.
Freeze on baking sheet until firm.
May be baked immediately without freezing. These do not have to be thawed, if frozen, before baking.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Beat margarine, sugar, egg and mashed bananas; beat well.
Add dry ingredients alternately in 4 additions with buttermilk.
Fold in walnuts.
Bake in greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan for 1 hour.
Turn onto wire rack and turn right side up to cool.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix together mayonnaise, sugar and water, first, stirring well.
Add flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Bake in greased and floured 9 x 13 x 2-inch loaf pan at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes, or 2 (8-inch) cake pans.

title: oil and garlic pasta
directions: Heat oil in frying pan over medium-low heat.
Add garlic and cook 2 minutes.
Add red pepper and cook a few minutes more.
Pour over cooked pasta.
Add basil for color.

title: eclair cake
directions: Butter 9 x 13-inch pan.
Line a layer of crackers (do not crumble).
Mix pudding and milk and beat well.
Add Cool Whip and mix.
Pour 1/2 mixture over crackers.
Add another layer of crackers.
Pour other half of mixture over crackers.
Another layer of crackers.

title: potato salad
directions: Wash
potatoes, leave on skins.
Cover with water.
Add salt. Cook
minutes
or
until
done.
Let potatoes cool. Peel and cut into cubes.
Add onions, egg, celery, pepper and mayo.	(If too dry, add little milk.) Garnish with sliced egg. (Better when made 2 days ahead.)

title: girl scout cookies
directions: Cream margarine or butter and sugar; add eggs (beaten), add milk and flavoring.
Then add flour, salt and baking powder. Knead dough.
Roll out and cut and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake in quick oven (475°).

title: old-fashioned apple crisp
directions: Place sliced apples in 9 x 13 x 2-inch greased pan.
Combine cinnamon and brown sugar.
Sprinkle apples with half of this mixture.
Combine granulated sugar, flour, egg, salt and baking powder and spread over apple slices.
This will act like pie crust dough.
Sprinkle remaining cinnamon and brown sugar over contents. Pour melted butter or margarine over top and bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until done.
Can be frozen after preparation and cooked after being frozen.
Also can be frozen after baking, then thawed and warmed in oven before serving.
